window.SHADOWING_DATA = {"interview":[{"id":1,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"Okay, let’s kick things off.","literal_zh":"好吧，让我们开始吧。","audio":"audio/0001_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.126},{"id":2,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"Can you tell us a little bit about yourself and what you do?","literal_zh":"你能告诉我们一点关于你自己的事情吗？","audio":"audio/0002_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.422},{"id":3,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"Sure.","literal_zh":"当然","audio":"audio/0003_perrin.mp3","duration":1.91},{"id":4,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"My name is Perrin, and my husband is Jeff.","literal_zh":"我叫Perrin，我丈夫叫Jeff","audio":"audio/0004_perrin.mp3","duration":3.926},{"id":5,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"We run a YouTube channel called Paired and Powered Up.","literal_zh":"我们经营一个名为Paired和Powered Up的YouTube频道.","audio":"audio/0005_perrin.mp3","duration":3.974},{"id":6,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"It is focused on home gym equipment reviews.","literal_zh":"重点是家庭体育器材审查。","audio":"audio/0006_perrin.mp3","duration":3.734},{"id":7,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"What makes our reviews a little different is that we test everything from two perspectives.","literal_zh":"使我们的评论稍有不同，就是我们从两个角度检验一切。","audio":"audio/0007_perrin.mp3","duration":5.654},{"id":8,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"I am 5'5\" and about 120 pounds.","literal_zh":"我身高5英尺5，体重120磅左右","audio":"audio/0008_perrin.mp3","duration":4.934},{"id":9,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"Jeff is 5'11\" and about 200 pounds.","literal_zh":"Jeff身高5英尺11 体重约200磅","audio":"audio/0009_perrin.mp3","duration":4.862},{"id":10,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"So we can show how the same piece of equipment works for two very different body types.","literal_zh":"因此，我们可以显示同一件设备如何适用于两种非常不同的身体类型。","audio":"audio/0010_perrin.mp3","duration":5.798},{"id":11,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"We both use every product we review.","literal_zh":"我们都使用我们审查的所有产品。","audio":"audio/0011_perrin.mp3","duration":3.398},{"id":12,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"We usually test it for at least three weeks and work it into our normal workout routine.","literal_zh":"我们通常至少测试三个星期 然后把它做成正常的锻炼","audio":"audio/0012_perrin.mp3","duration":5.822},{"id":13,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"That way the review feels real, not just like a first impression.","literal_zh":"这样一来，评论感觉是真实的，而不仅仅是第一印象.","audio":"audio/0013_perrin.mp3","duration":4.886},{"id":14,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"After that, we put together a full review for our audience.","literal_zh":"之后，我们为观众整理了完整的评论.","audio":"audio/0014_perrin.mp3","duration":4.646},{"id":15,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"We started the channel about a year and a half ago, and it has grown a lot since then.","literal_zh":"我们大约在一年半前开始这个频道，从那时起它发展了很多.","audio":"audio/0015_perrin.mp3","duration":5.726},{"id":16,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"We are starting to review bigger pieces of equipment now, and JabX came up as something we would be interested in testing.","literal_zh":"我们开始审查更大的设备， JabX作为我们有兴趣测试的东西。","audio":"audio/0016_perrin.mp3","duration":7.574},{"id":17,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"Nice.","literal_zh":"不错","audio":"audio/0017_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.19},{"id":18,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"And just so we understand the scale, how big is your audience right now?","literal_zh":"我们了解这个尺度 你的观众现在有多少人？","audio":"audio/0018_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.142},{"id":19,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"We have about 2,600 subscribers on YouTube right now, and it is growing steadily.","literal_zh":"我们目前在YouTube上约有2600个订户，并且正在稳步增长。","audio":"audio/0019_perrin.mp3","duration":6.542},{"id":20,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"Our Instagram following is smaller, but I would need to check the exact number.","literal_zh":"我们的Instagram跟随较小， 但我需要检查确切的数字。","audio":"audio/0020_perrin.mp3","duration":5.39},{"id":21,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"Got it.","literal_zh":"明白吗？","audio":"audio/0021_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.126},{"id":22,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"Where in the U.S. are you based?","literal_zh":"你在美国在哪里？","audio":"audio/0022_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.366},{"id":23,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"We are in New Hampshire, right on the border of Vermont and New Hampshire.","literal_zh":"我们在新罕布什尔州 就在佛蒙特州和新罕布什尔州的边境","audio":"audio/0023_perrin.mp3","duration":5.03},{"id":24,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"So we are up in New England.","literal_zh":"所以我们在新英格兰。","audio":"audio/0024_perrin.mp3","duration":2.846},{"id":25,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"访谈开场与频道背景","english":"We are in the Eastern time zone.","literal_zh":"我们在东部时区。","audio":"audio/0025_perrin.mp3","duration":3.014},{"id":26,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"I saw in the survey that boxing is not really part of your regular routine yet.","literal_zh":"我在调查中看到 拳击并不是你常规的一部分","audio":"audio/0026_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.646},{"id":27,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Is that fair?","literal_zh":"公平吗？","audio":"audio/0027_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.574},{"id":28,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Not as a regular routine.","literal_zh":"不是例行公事","audio":"audio/0028_perrin.mp3","duration":2.918},{"id":29,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"I have done some footwork and a few small boxing-style movements, but I have never trained in boxing consistently.","literal_zh":"我做了一些脚踏实地的工作和一些小的拳击风格的动作，但我从来没有一贯地训练拳击.","audio":"audio/0029_perrin.mp3","duration":7.31},{"id":30,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"My husband has not really done it either.","literal_zh":"我的丈夫也没有真正做到这一点。","audio":"audio/0030_perrin.mp3","duration":3.35},{"id":31,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"But I have always been interested in it.","literal_zh":"但我一直很感兴趣","audio":"audio/0031_perrin.mp3","duration":3.206},{"id":32,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"I know boxing is good cardio.","literal_zh":"我知道拳击是好心术。","audio":"audio/0032_perrin.mp3","duration":3.086},{"id":33,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"It is also good for agility and coordination.","literal_zh":"这也有利于灵活和协调。","audio":"audio/0033_perrin.mp3","duration":3.878},{"id":34,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Another reason I am interested is personal.","literal_zh":"我感兴趣的另一个原因是个人原因。","audio":"audio/0034_perrin.mp3","duration":3.638},{"id":35,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Both of my parents had Parkinson's disease.","literal_zh":"我父母都得了帕金森氏症","audio":"audio/0035_perrin.mp3","duration":3.71},{"id":36,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Boxing is often recommended for people with Parkinson's because it can help with coordination and movement.","literal_zh":"拳击经常被推荐给有帕金森症的人，因为它可以帮助协调和运动.","audio":"audio/0036_perrin.mp3","duration":6.734},{"id":37,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"So if JabX could also be positioned as a tool for people with Parkinson's, that would be a very strong angle for me.","literal_zh":"所以，如果JabX也可以被定位为 帕金森症患者的工具， 那对我来说是一个非常强烈的角度。","audio":"audio/0037_perrin.mp3","duration":7.598},{"id":38,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"My parents have both passed away, and they never really had the chance to get into boxing.","literal_zh":"我的父母都去世了， 他们从来没有真正的机会 进入拳击。","audio":"audio/0038_perrin.mp3","duration":6.038},{"id":39,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"But if they had had something like JabX at home and could have used it often, I think it would have been a great tool for them.","literal_zh":"但如果他们在家里有类似JabX的东西，并且可以经常使用，我想这对他们来说是一个伟大的工具.","audio":"audio/0039_perrin.mp3","duration":7.214},{"id":40,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"That is actually a super helpful angle.","literal_zh":"这实际上是一个超级有益的角度。","audio":"audio/0040_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.75},{"id":41,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Can you walk us through why boxing is useful for people with Parkinson's?","literal_zh":"你能告诉我们为什么 拳击对帕金森的人有用吗？","audio":"audio/0041_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.238},{"id":42,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Parkinson's is a neurological disease.","literal_zh":"帕金森氏症是一种神经病.","audio":"audio/0042_perrin.mp3","duration":3.566},{"id":43,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"It affects the nervous system and the body's ability to control movement.","literal_zh":"它影响神经系统和身体控制运动的能力.","audio":"audio/0043_perrin.mp3","duration":4.982},{"id":44,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Boxing works on coordination, and coordination is one of the hardest things for people with Parkinson's.","literal_zh":"拳击工作在协调方面，而协调是帕金森(英语:Parkinson)的人最难处理的事情之一.","audio":"audio/0044_perrin.mp3","duration":6.998},{"id":45,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"You are using your hands, your feet, your eyes and your timing all at once.","literal_zh":"你用手、脚、眼睛和时间","audio":"audio/0045_perrin.mp3","duration":5.75},{"id":46,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"That kind of training can help activate those movement patterns.","literal_zh":"这种培训可以帮助激活这些运动模式。","audio":"audio/0046_perrin.mp3","duration":4.622},{"id":47,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"I do not know all the research in detail, but I know boxing is commonly encouraged for Parkinson's patients.","literal_zh":"我不知道所有的详细研究， 但我知道拳击是帕金森的病人普遍鼓励的。","audio":"audio/0047_perrin.mp3","duration":7.214},{"id":48,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Michael J.","literal_zh":"迈克尔·J.","audio":"audio/0048_perrin.mp3","duration":2.222},{"id":49,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"Fox, the actor, also has a foundation for Parkinson's research, and they have a lot of information on this topic.","literal_zh":"演员福克斯也为帕金森的研究打下了基础，他们对这个话题有不少信息.","audio":"audio/0049_perrin.mp3","duration":8.006},{"id":50,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"For me, the key point is access.","literal_zh":"对我来说，关键是进入。","audio":"audio/0050_perrin.mp3","duration":3.638},{"id":51,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"A lot of people may not have a place nearby where they can do boxing.","literal_zh":"很多人可能在附近没有可以进行拳击的地方.","audio":"audio/0051_perrin.mp3","duration":4.958},{"id":52,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"拳击与帕金森病的推广角度","english":"If they can do it safely at home, that could make a big difference.","literal_zh":"如果他们能在家里安全地做，那会有很大的不同。","audio":"audio/0052_perrin.mp3","duration":4.814},{"id":53,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"What about your area?","literal_zh":"那你的地盘呢？","audio":"audio/0053_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.934},{"id":54,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"Is boxing something people around you are into, or is it still pretty niche?","literal_zh":"拳击是你周围的人喜欢的东西， 还是它仍然相当适合？","audio":"audio/0054_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.742},{"id":55,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"Boxing is one of those things that can intimidate people, but it also gets them excited.","literal_zh":"拳击是一种能吓人的东西，但也让他们兴奋.","audio":"audio/0055_perrin.mp3","duration":6.038},{"id":56,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"We live in a rural area, so there are not many places nearby where people can do it.","literal_zh":"我们生活在一个农村地区，所以附近没有多少地方是人们可以做到的.","audio":"audio/0056_perrin.mp3","duration":5.798},{"id":57,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"That is a big reason we built a home gym.","literal_zh":"那是我们建家用健身房的一个大原因","audio":"audio/0057_perrin.mp3","duration":3.614},{"id":58,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"We would have to drive about 20 minutes to get to a gym.","literal_zh":"我们得开车20分钟才能到健身房","audio":"audio/0058_perrin.mp3","duration":4.262},{"id":59,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"At the end of a long day, that is not always something you want to do.","literal_zh":"在漫长的一天结束时，这并不总是你想做的事情。","audio":"audio/0059_perrin.mp3","duration":4.862},{"id":60,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"You do not want to drive 20 minutes there, work out for an hour, and then drive 20 minutes back.","literal_zh":"你不想在那里开车20分钟， 工作一个小时，然后开车20分钟回来。","audio":"audio/0060_perrin.mp3","duration":6.734},{"id":61,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"So we are big believers in at-home fitness.","literal_zh":"所以我们是在家里健身的大信徒。","audio":"audio/0061_perrin.mp3","duration":3.782},{"id":62,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"A product like JabX could make boxing easier to bring into a home routine.","literal_zh":"像JabX这样的产品可以让拳击更容易带入家常便饭.","audio":"audio/0062_perrin.mp3","duration":5.438},{"id":63,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"The variety is also important.","literal_zh":"品种也很重要。","audio":"audio/0063_perrin.mp3","duration":3.11},{"id":64,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"People get bored doing the same workout every day.","literal_zh":"人们每天都会厌倦同样的锻炼","audio":"audio/0064_perrin.mp3","duration":3.926},{"id":65,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"If they can add boxing into the mix, it keeps things fresh.","literal_zh":"如果他们能把拳击加进混音中，它能保持事物新鲜.","audio":"audio/0065_perrin.mp3","duration":4.622},{"id":66,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"It is not just a bag hanging from the ceiling.","literal_zh":"这不仅仅是吊在天花板上的袋子。","audio":"audio/0066_perrin.mp3","duration":3.662},{"id":67,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"居家健身场景与拳击普及度","english":"If the product gives guidance and helps you through the workout, that is much more appealing.","literal_zh":"如果产品能指导你 帮助你通过锻炼，那就更有吸引力了。","audio":"audio/0067_perrin.mp3","duration":5.75},{"id":68,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"When it comes to training, are you more of a solo-workout person, or do you and your husband like doing it together?","literal_zh":"在训练方面，你比较喜欢独修，还是你和你丈夫喜欢一起做？","audio":"audio/0068_interviewer.mp3","duration":6.326},{"id":69,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"We do both.","literal_zh":"我们都是","audio":"audio/0069_perrin.mp3","duration":2.222},{"id":70,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"My husband is a UPS driver, so his schedule is not always predictable.","literal_zh":"我丈夫是UPS司机，所以他的行程并非总能预测.","audio":"audio/0070_perrin.mp3","duration":5.582},{"id":71,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Some days we can work out together.","literal_zh":"有时候我们可以一起工作","audio":"audio/0071_perrin.mp3","duration":3.278},{"id":72,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Some days we cannot.","literal_zh":"有时候，我们不能。","audio":"audio/0072_perrin.mp3","duration":2.63},{"id":73,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"I also have a friend who comes over and works out with me in the home gym.","literal_zh":"我也有个朋友过来 跟我在健身房工作","audio":"audio/0073_perrin.mp3","duration":4.91},{"id":74,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"So it depends on the day.","literal_zh":"故视日.","audio":"audio/0074_perrin.mp3","duration":2.774},{"id":75,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Sometimes Jeff and I are in the same room, but we are doing different workouts or using different equipment.","literal_zh":"有时Jeff和我在同一间房 但我们在做不同的锻炼 或者使用不同的设备","audio":"audio/0075_perrin.mp3","duration":6.782},{"id":76,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Other times we do the same workout together.","literal_zh":"其他时候我们一起做同样的锻炼。","audio":"audio/0076_perrin.mp3","duration":3.662},{"id":77,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"We like switching things up so it does not get boring.","literal_zh":"我们喜欢换东西 这样才不会无聊","audio":"audio/0077_perrin.mp3","duration":4.022},{"id":78,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Have you ever tried BodyCombat or those boxing-style online classes at home?","literal_zh":"你试过拳击或那些拳击式的在线课程吗？","audio":"audio/0078_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.79},{"id":79,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"We do some aerobic work, but I probably do more of that than Jeff.","literal_zh":"我们做一些有氧工作 但我可能做的比Jeff多","audio":"audio/0079_perrin.mp3","duration":5.078},{"id":80,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"He is more focused on building muscle right now.","literal_zh":"他现在更注重肌肉建设","audio":"audio/0080_perrin.mp3","duration":3.71},{"id":81,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"I like to include more cardio.","literal_zh":"我喜欢包括更多的心肌。","audio":"audio/0081_perrin.mp3","duration":3.11},{"id":82,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"That said, he is open to different types of cardio if they are useful.","literal_zh":"尽管如此，他愿意接受不同类型的心电图，如果它们有用的话。","audio":"audio/0082_perrin.mp3","duration":5.078},{"id":83,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"If something works on mobility, dexterity or hand-eye coordination, he is more interested in it.","literal_zh":"如果有东西在机动性，机敏性或手眼协调上起作用，他对此更感兴趣.","audio":"audio/0083_perrin.mp3","duration":6.878},{"id":84,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"He wants cardio that still feels like it is helping his overall fitness.","literal_zh":"他想要的心肺 仍然觉得这能帮助他身体健康","audio":"audio/0084_perrin.mp3","duration":5.006},{"id":85,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"What does a normal workout week look like for you?","literal_zh":"正常的锻炼周对你来说是什么样子？","audio":"audio/0085_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.038},{"id":86,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"We work out almost every day.","literal_zh":"我们几乎每天都工作","audio":"audio/0086_perrin.mp3","duration":2.966},{"id":87,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Jeff lifts five days a week.","literal_zh":"Jeff每周举5天","audio":"audio/0087_perrin.mp3","duration":3.062},{"id":88,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"I lift three days a week, sometimes four.","literal_zh":"我每周抬三天，有时四天","audio":"audio/0088_perrin.mp3","duration":3.878},{"id":89,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"I also try to add cardio two or three days a week.","literal_zh":"我还试着每周增加两三天的心跳。","audio":"audio/0089_perrin.mp3","duration":4.358},{"id":90,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Jeff uses the treadmill for hiking sometimes.","literal_zh":"Jeff有时会用跑步车徒步旅行","audio":"audio/0090_perrin.mp3","duration":3.902},{"id":91,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Even when we are not lifting, we are usually doing some type of fitness.","literal_zh":"即使我们没有升起，我们通常也在做某种健身。","audio":"audio/0091_perrin.mp3","duration":5.198},{"id":92,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"We may take one day off.","literal_zh":"我们可以休息一天","audio":"audio/0092_perrin.mp3","duration":2.846},{"id":93,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"We usually work out in the evening.","literal_zh":"我们通常晚上一起工作","audio":"audio/0093_perrin.mp3","duration":3.086},{"id":94,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"We are not really morning people.","literal_zh":"我们不是真的早上的人。","audio":"audio/0094_perrin.mp3","duration":3.014},{"id":95,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"单人/双人训练与日常习惯","english":"Most of our workouts are around an hour.","literal_zh":"我们大部分的锻炼时间都在一小时左右","audio":"audio/0095_perrin.mp3","duration":3.47},{"id":96,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Besides the treadmill, what else do you use for cardio at home?","literal_zh":"除了跑步车，你在家里还用什么做心跳？","audio":"audio/0096_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.806},{"id":97,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Anything like a Peloton bike?","literal_zh":"像是皮洛顿自行车吗？","audio":"audio/0097_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.342},{"id":98,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"We used to have a Peloton bike, but we did not use it much.","literal_zh":"我们曾经有一辆皮洛顿自行车，但是没有怎么使用.","audio":"audio/0098_perrin.mp3","duration":4.646},{"id":99,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"It was uncomfortable, and it was mostly lower-body work.","literal_zh":"感觉很不舒服，而且大多是下体工作.","audio":"audio/0099_perrin.mp3","duration":4.526},{"id":100,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"I prefer equipment that gives more full-body engagement.","literal_zh":"我更喜欢更能全身心投入的设备","audio":"audio/0100_perrin.mp3","duration":4.286},{"id":101,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"We also had a rower for a while, but we still used the treadmill more than anything else.","literal_zh":"我们还有一个划船的一段时间， 但我们仍然使用 跑步机比任何其他。","audio":"audio/0101_perrin.mp3","duration":5.966},{"id":102,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Right now, we are reviewing some cardio-focused equipment.","literal_zh":"现在，我们正在审查一些以心肺为重点的设备。","audio":"audio/0102_perrin.mp3","duration":4.694},{"id":103,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"We have used Concept2 products, like the SkiErg, StrengthErg and RowErg.","literal_zh":"我们使用了Concept2产品，如SkiErg，FriendErg和RowErg.","audio":"audio/0103_perrin.mp3","duration":5.798},{"id":104,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"We also have a machine that feels like a mix between a rower and an elliptical because it uses both the hands and feet.","literal_zh":"我们还有一台机器，它感觉像划船和椭圆形的混合体，因为它同时使用手和脚.","audio":"audio/0104_perrin.mp3","duration":7.358},{"id":105,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"The biggest issue is space.","literal_zh":"最大的问题是空间。","audio":"audio/0105_perrin.mp3","duration":2.918},{"id":106,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"We cannot keep everything we review.","literal_zh":"我们不能保留我们审查的一切。","audio":"audio/0106_perrin.mp3","duration":3.182},{"id":107,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"If we really like something and know we will use it all the time, we keep it.","literal_zh":"如果我们真的喜欢的东西，知道我们会一直使用它，我们保留它。","audio":"audio/0107_perrin.mp3","duration":5.318},{"id":108,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Otherwise, we usually sell it after the review.","literal_zh":"否则，我们通常在审查后出售。","audio":"audio/0108_perrin.mp3","duration":3.998},{"id":109,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"JabX is about 16 feet long, so it is not tiny.","literal_zh":"JabX长约16英尺，所以并不小.","audio":"audio/0109_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.854},{"id":110,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"In your setup, would that be realistic?","literal_zh":"在你的设定， 这是现实吗？","audio":"audio/0110_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.798},{"id":111,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"We actually have two gym spaces now.","literal_zh":"我们现在有两个健身房","audio":"audio/0111_perrin.mp3","duration":3.47},{"id":112,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"One is in a living room that we converted into a gym.","literal_zh":"一个在客厅里 我们把一个健身房改造了","audio":"audio/0112_perrin.mp3","duration":4.094},{"id":113,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"The other is in our garage, which we recently turned into a second gym space.","literal_zh":"另一个是在我们的车库， 我们最近变成了第二个健身房。","audio":"audio/0113_perrin.mp3","duration":5.534},{"id":114,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"So we would have a couple of options.","literal_zh":"所以我们有几种选择。","audio":"audio/0114_perrin.mp3","duration":3.23},{"id":115,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"The garage gym would probably be the best place for JabX.","literal_zh":"车库健身房可能是最好的 JabX。","audio":"audio/0115_perrin.mp3","duration":4.598},{"id":116,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Would an easy-move design matter to you?","literal_zh":"一个容易移动的设计对你很重要吗？","audio":"audio/0116_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.702},{"id":117,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Like wheels, so you can roll it out and tuck it away?","literal_zh":"像轮子一样，这样你就可以把它卷起来，把它盖起来？","audio":"audio/0117_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.23},{"id":118,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Absolutely.","literal_zh":"当然","audio":"audio/0118_perrin.mp3","duration":2.222},{"id":119,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"If it did not have wheels, I would probably add them.","literal_zh":"如果它没有轮子，我可能会加起来。","audio":"audio/0119_perrin.mp3","duration":4.142},{"id":120,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"In a home gym, being able to move equipment is really important.","literal_zh":"在家庭体育馆里，能够移动设备非常重要。","audio":"audio/0120_perrin.mp3","duration":4.958},{"id":121,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"If you can store it in a corner and pull it out when you need it, that helps a lot.","literal_zh":"如果你可以把它储存在角落里，并在你需要的时候把它拔出来，那会很有帮助.","audio":"audio/0121_perrin.mp3","duration":5.534},{"id":122,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Especially if the space is smaller.","literal_zh":"特别是如果空间较小。","audio":"audio/0122_perrin.mp3","duration":3.254},{"id":123,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"现有器械、空间与移动性需求","english":"Portability is a big deal.","literal_zh":"便携是大事.","audio":"audio/0123_perrin.mp3","duration":2.942},{"id":124,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"How do you usually plan your workouts?","literal_zh":"你平时是怎么安排运动的？","audio":"audio/0124_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.606},{"id":125,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Are you following your own plan, or does someone build it for you?","literal_zh":"你是在遵循你自己的计划 还是有人帮你建的？","audio":"audio/0125_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.214},{"id":126,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"I have a virtual trainer who builds my workouts for me.","literal_zh":"我有个虚拟的教练 帮我做锻炼","audio":"audio/0126_perrin.mp3","duration":4.07},{"id":127,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"He bases them on what I am trying to work on, and he also keeps me motivated.","literal_zh":"他以我努力的工作为基础，他也保持我的积极性。","audio":"audio/0127_perrin.mp3","duration":5.462},{"id":128,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"My husband is certified, so he writes his own workouts.","literal_zh":"我丈夫有认证，所以他写自己的锻炼。","audio":"audio/0128_perrin.mp3","duration":4.502},{"id":129,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"He usually does upper-body and lower-body splits.","literal_zh":"他通常进行上体和下体分裂.","audio":"audio/0129_perrin.mp3","duration":4.142},{"id":130,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"His workouts are more targeted.","literal_zh":"他的锻炼更具有针对性.","audio":"audio/0130_perrin.mp3","duration":2.942},{"id":131,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Mine are more full-body.","literal_zh":"我的身体更满满","audio":"audio/0131_perrin.mp3","duration":2.654},{"id":132,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"I do three full-body workouts a week.","literal_zh":"我每周做三次全身运动","audio":"audio/0132_perrin.mp3","duration":3.422},{"id":133,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"For cardio, I usually do whatever I am interested in at the time.","literal_zh":"对于心律，我通常做任何我感兴趣的时候。","audio":"audio/0133_perrin.mp3","duration":4.958},{"id":134,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Some days I run.","literal_zh":"有时候我跑。","audio":"audio/0134_perrin.mp3","duration":2.462},{"id":135,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Some days I walk.","literal_zh":"有时候我走路","audio":"audio/0135_perrin.mp3","duration":2.51},{"id":136,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Some days I hike.","literal_zh":"有时候我走了。","audio":"audio/0136_perrin.mp3","duration":2.534},{"id":137,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"We also have a Tonal, so I use some of its cardio features from time to time.","literal_zh":"我们还有一个Tonal， 所以我不时使用它的一些心肺功能。","audio":"audio/0137_perrin.mp3","duration":5.558},{"id":138,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"I usually like to warm up with about a 10-minute walk before I lift.","literal_zh":"我通常喜欢在升起前用10分钟的步行来取暖.","audio":"audio/0138_perrin.mp3","duration":5.054},{"id":139,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Jeff does something similar.","literal_zh":"Jeff做类似的事情。","audio":"audio/0139_perrin.mp3","duration":2.87},{"id":140,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Our strength training is hypertrophy-focused.","literal_zh":"我们的实力训练是超营养的","audio":"audio/0140_perrin.mp3","duration":3.878},{"id":141,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"So we do sets with rest periods in between.","literal_zh":"因此，我们确实安排了休息时间。","audio":"audio/0141_perrin.mp3","duration":3.854},{"id":142,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"The rest might be one, two or three minutes, depending on the movement and what we are trying to build.","literal_zh":"其余的可能是一、二或三分钟，这取决于我们的行动和我们试图建设的东西。","audio":"audio/0142_perrin.mp3","duration":7.046},{"id":143,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"What does personal training usually cost, at least from what you have seen?","literal_zh":"个人培训通常需要多少费用，至少从你所看到的情况来看？","audio":"audio/0143_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.238},{"id":144,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"It really depends on the setup.","literal_zh":"这真的取决于设置。","audio":"audio/0144_perrin.mp3","duration":2.966},{"id":145,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"If you go to a gym, a trainer is often around $75 to $100 an hour.","literal_zh":"如果你去健身房，一个教练经常是每小时75到100美元左右.","audio":"audio/0145_perrin.mp3","duration":6.71},{"id":146,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"If you train with them two or three times a week, that gets expensive quickly.","literal_zh":"如果你每周和他们一起训练两三次，那会很快变得昂贵.","audio":"audio/0146_perrin.mp3","duration":5.534},{"id":147,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"There are also group-style online programs.","literal_zh":"也有团体式在线程序.","audio":"audio/0147_perrin.mp3","duration":3.686},{"id":148,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"A trainer builds one program, and everyone who signs up follows it.","literal_zh":"训练员会建立一套程序 每一个签字的人都会遵守","audio":"audio/0148_perrin.mp3","duration":5.006},{"id":149,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"That might cost around $40 a month.","literal_zh":"这可能需要大约每月40美元。","audio":"audio/0149_perrin.mp3","duration":3.758},{"id":150,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"It is not personalized, but it gives you structure.","literal_zh":"它不是个性化的，但它给了你结构。","audio":"audio/0150_perrin.mp3","duration":4.094},{"id":151,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"My trainer is one-on-one.","literal_zh":"我的教练是一对一。","audio":"audio/0151_perrin.mp3","duration":2.798},{"id":152,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"He builds the program around me.","literal_zh":"他围绕我构建了程序。","audio":"audio/0152_perrin.mp3","duration":2.99},{"id":153,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"We communicate almost every day.","literal_zh":"我们几乎每天都在沟通","audio":"audio/0153_perrin.mp3","duration":3.302},{"id":154,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"I send him videos of my form so he can check whether I am doing the movements correctly.","literal_zh":"我给他发了我表格的视频 这样他就可以检查我是否正确行动了","audio":"audio/0154_perrin.mp3","duration":5.846},{"id":155,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"He also helps with meal planning.","literal_zh":"他还帮助制定膳食计划.","audio":"audio/0155_perrin.mp3","duration":3.11},{"id":156,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"It is all virtual.","literal_zh":"这都是虚拟的。","audio":"audio/0156_perrin.mp3","duration":2.462},{"id":157,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"We use Zoom, texting and things like that.","literal_zh":"我们使用Zoom，发短信和类似的东西。","audio":"audio/0157_perrin.mp3","duration":4.07},{"id":158,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"He costs around $400 a month, but it is a much more personal relationship.","literal_zh":"他每月花费约400美元，但这更是个人关系.","audio":"audio/0158_perrin.mp3","duration":6.302},{"id":159,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Are you seeing people use AI for workout plans now?","literal_zh":"你看见有人用人工智能做健身计划了吗？","audio":"audio/0159_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.494},{"id":160,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Definitely.","literal_zh":"当然","audio":"audio/0160_perrin.mp3","duration":2.15},{"id":161,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"A lot of people use ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini or other AI tools to build workouts.","literal_zh":"很多人使用ChatGPT，克劳德，双子座或其他AI工具来构建健身.","audio":"audio/0161_perrin.mp3","duration":6.902},{"id":162,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"They tell the AI their goal, how often they can work out and how much time they have.","literal_zh":"他们告诉AI他们的目标，他们能工作多久，还有多少时间.","audio":"audio/0162_perrin.mp3","duration":5.678},{"id":163,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"训练计划、私教模式与费用","english":"Then it gives them a plan.","literal_zh":"那就给他们一个计划","audio":"audio/0163_perrin.mp3","duration":2.678},{"id":164,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"That is exactly the direction we are thinking about for JabX.","literal_zh":"这就是我们为JabX考虑的方向。","audio":"audio/0164_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.022},{"id":165,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"The dream is to give people some of that personal-trainer feel, but built into the product.","literal_zh":"梦想是给人们一些 个人教练的感觉， 但是在产品中。","audio":"audio/0165_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.078},{"id":166,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"For example, JabX could track heart rate, punching speed and punching power through sensors.","literal_zh":"例如，JabX可以通过传感器跟踪心率，冲锋速度和冲锋功率.","audio":"audio/0166_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.75},{"id":167,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"The way we are thinking about it is pretty simple.","literal_zh":"我们的想法很简单。","audio":"audio/0167_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.062},{"id":168,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"There are three pieces to it.","literal_zh":"有三块.","audio":"audio/0168_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.15},{"id":169,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"First, data collection.","literal_zh":"一，数据采集.","audio":"audio/0169_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.03},{"id":170,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"The data could come from an app connected to Apple Watch, Samsung Watch or other wearables.","literal_zh":"数据可能来自与苹果卫视，三星卫视或其他可穿戴设备连接的应用程序.","audio":"audio/0170_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.582},{"id":171,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"It could also come from JabX sensors that track heart rate, punching speed, power and movement quality.","literal_zh":"也可以来自跟踪心率，拳击速度，功率和运动质量的JabX传感器.","audio":"audio/0171_interviewer.mp3","duration":6.542},{"id":172,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"Second is analysis.","literal_zh":"二是分析.","audio":"audio/0172_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.126},{"id":173,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"The system could look at movement correction, workout performance and heart rate zones.","literal_zh":"该系统可以研究运动矫正、锻炼性能和心率区。","audio":"audio/0173_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.838},{"id":174,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"Third is content generation.","literal_zh":"第三是内容生成.","audio":"audio/0174_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.39},{"id":175,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"Based on the user's data, it could create a 30-minute workout or even a longer plan, like a one-month program.","literal_zh":"根据用户的数据，它可以创建30分钟的锻炼甚至更长的计划，比如一个一个月的程序.","audio":"audio/0175_interviewer.mp3","duration":6.782},{"id":176,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"So it would create workouts that are customized to the person, based on their data and their level?","literal_zh":"这样它就能根据个人的数据和水平，创造适合个人的健身方案？","audio":"audio/0176_perrin.mp3","duration":6.158},{"id":177,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"Exactly.","literal_zh":"没错","audio":"audio/0177_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.502},{"id":178,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"We also want to use a camera for form correction, so the system can actually see how the user is moving.","literal_zh":"我们还想用相机进行形式校正，因此系统可以实际看到用户是如何移动的.","audio":"audio/0178_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.846},{"id":179,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"That is helpful.","literal_zh":"这很有帮助。","audio":"audio/0179_perrin.mp3","duration":2.342},{"id":180,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"If it can correct form and movement in real time, that is a strong feature.","literal_zh":"如果它能够实时纠正形式和运动，这是一个很强的特点。","audio":"audio/0180_perrin.mp3","duration":5.342},{"id":181,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"If the user is too slow, or their form is off, the system should tell them.","literal_zh":"如果用户速度太慢，或者其形式被关闭，系统应该告诉他们.","audio":"audio/0181_perrin.mp3","duration":5.51},{"id":182,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"It could also adjust to the user's height, so the pad positions and target path fit the person better during training.","literal_zh":"它还可以适应用户的高度，因此垫位和瞄准路径在训练期间更适合人.","audio":"audio/0182_interviewer.mp3","duration":6.782},{"id":183,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"That is really useful.","literal_zh":"这真的有用。","audio":"audio/0183_perrin.mp3","duration":2.678},{"id":184,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"It sounds like you are trying to put a lot of the personal-trainer experience into the machine.","literal_zh":"听起来你试图把很多 个人教练的经验投入机器。","audio":"audio/0184_perrin.mp3","duration":5.726},{"id":185,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"And because regular training can get boring fast, we also want to build in games, especially for beginners.","literal_zh":"并且由于常规训练可以变得无聊快，我们也想在游戏中建设，特别是初学者.","audio":"audio/0185_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.822},{"id":186,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"That makes sense.","literal_zh":"这有道理。","audio":"audio/0186_perrin.mp3","duration":2.462},{"id":187,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"Games can make boxing more competitive and more fun.","literal_zh":"游戏可以让拳击更具竞争力和乐趣.","audio":"audio/0187_perrin.mp3","duration":4.094},{"id":188,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练功能设想","english":"A lot of people are motivated by that.","literal_zh":"很多人都为此而奋斗.","audio":"audio/0188_perrin.mp3","duration":3.518},{"id":189,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"With your trainer, do you usually set a specific goal together?","literal_zh":"与你的教练， 你通常设置一个特定的目标在一起？","audio":"audio/0189_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.83},{"id":190,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"Like losing weight, building muscle or hitting a target by a certain date?","literal_zh":"比如减肥，建立肌肉或者在某个日期前击中目标？","audio":"audio/0190_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.31},{"id":191,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I do not really have a short-term goal like that.","literal_zh":"我并没有这样的短期目标。","audio":"audio/0191_perrin.mp3","duration":3.686},{"id":192,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I keep working with him because he motivates me and because he handles the planning.","literal_zh":"我一直和他合作 因为他激励我 并且他负责计划","audio":"audio/0192_perrin.mp3","duration":5.366},{"id":193,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I know a lot of the exercises.","literal_zh":"我知道很多练习。","audio":"audio/0193_perrin.mp3","duration":3.23},{"id":194,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I probably could figure it out myself.","literal_zh":"我也许能自己弄明白","audio":"audio/0194_perrin.mp3","duration":3.422},{"id":195,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"But I do not want to think about programming.","literal_zh":"但我不想考虑编程。","audio":"audio/0195_perrin.mp3","duration":3.446},{"id":196,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I already organize so much in the rest of my life.","literal_zh":"我已经组织这么多 在我的生活的余生。","audio":"audio/0196_perrin.mp3","duration":4.286},{"id":197,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"It is nice to have someone else build the plan so I can just show up and do it.","literal_zh":"让别人来做这个计划是件好事 这样我就可以亲自来做","audio":"audio/0197_perrin.mp3","duration":5.174},{"id":198,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"My main goal right now is building muscle.","literal_zh":"我现在的主要目标是建立肌肉。","audio":"audio/0198_perrin.mp3","duration":3.686},{"id":199,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I lost a lot of body fat over the last year, and now I want to build muscle.","literal_zh":"去年我失去了很多身体脂肪， 现在我想建立肌肉。","audio":"audio/0199_perrin.mp3","duration":5.582},{"id":200,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"That takes time.","literal_zh":"这需要时间。","audio":"audio/0200_perrin.mp3","duration":2.366},{"id":201,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"It does not happen overnight.","literal_zh":"它不会一夜之间发生。","audio":"audio/0201_perrin.mp3","duration":2.918},{"id":202,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"Right now, I am focused on eating enough calories and enough protein.","literal_zh":"现在，我专注于 吃足够的卡路里和足够的蛋白质。","audio":"audio/0202_perrin.mp3","duration":5.246},{"id":203,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"You cannot build muscle without that.","literal_zh":"没有它，你无法建立肌肉。","audio":"audio/0203_perrin.mp3","duration":3.206},{"id":204,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I also need balance.","literal_zh":"我还需要平衡","audio":"audio/0204_perrin.mp3","duration":2.678},{"id":205,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I need to balance strength training, cardio, other exercise and nutrition.","literal_zh":"我需要平衡力量训练，心肺，其他运动和营养.","audio":"audio/0205_perrin.mp3","duration":5.798},{"id":206,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"Eating is a huge part of being healthy.","literal_zh":"饮食是健康的一大部分.","audio":"audio/0206_perrin.mp3","duration":3.47},{"id":207,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"What you put into your body affects what you can do physically.","literal_zh":"你放进身体里会影响你的身体","audio":"audio/0207_perrin.mp3","duration":4.382},{"id":208,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I also need to make sure I am not doing so much cardio that it interferes with muscle building.","literal_zh":"我还得确保我没有做太多心肺病 以致于会妨碍肌肉建设","audio":"audio/0208_perrin.mp3","duration":6.11},{"id":209,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"If you do not mind me asking, how old are you?","literal_zh":"如果你不介意我问，你多大了？","audio":"audio/0209_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.966},{"id":210,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I am 48, and my husband is 53.","literal_zh":"我48岁，我丈夫53岁","audio":"audio/0210_perrin.mp3","duration":4.118},{"id":211,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"Do your kids work out too?","literal_zh":"你的孩子也会工作吗？","audio":"audio/0211_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.126},{"id":212,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"We have two sons.","literal_zh":"我们有两个儿子。","audio":"audio/0212_perrin.mp3","duration":2.558},{"id":213,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"One is 23, and one is 20.","literal_zh":"一个是23，一个是20。","audio":"audio/0213_perrin.mp3","duration":3.734},{"id":214,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"They both use our gym.","literal_zh":"他们都使用我们的健身房。","audio":"audio/0214_perrin.mp3","duration":2.678},{"id":215,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"My older son usually works out with my husband.","literal_zh":"我大儿子通常跟我丈夫一起工作","audio":"audio/0215_perrin.mp3","duration":3.974},{"id":216,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"My younger son likes to work out by himself because he does not like people watching him.","literal_zh":"我小儿子喜欢一个人工作 因为他不喜欢别人看他","audio":"audio/0216_perrin.mp3","duration":5.822},{"id":217,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"I think both of them would like the boxing product.","literal_zh":"我想他们俩都喜欢拳击产品","audio":"audio/0217_perrin.mp3","duration":3.734},{"id":218,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"My husband and my younger son are both very competitive.","literal_zh":"我丈夫和我小儿子都非常有竞争力","audio":"audio/0218_perrin.mp3","duration":4.502},{"id":219,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"个人训练目标与饮食平衡","english":"If JabX had a game mode where they could compete against each other, they would enjoy that.","literal_zh":"如果JabX有一个可以互相竞争的游戏模式，他们会享受这个.","audio":"audio/0219_perrin.mp3","duration":5.894},{"id":220,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"Be honest.","literal_zh":"老实说","audio":"audio/0220_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.478},{"id":221,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"Does indoor cardio ever get boring for you?","literal_zh":"室内心电图有没有让你觉得无聊？","audio":"audio/0221_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.966},{"id":222,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"Yes.","literal_zh":"对","audio":"audio/0222_perrin.mp3","duration":1.958},{"id":223,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"I usually watch cooking shows on the treadmill because treadmill cardio can get boring.","literal_zh":"我通常在跑步机上看烹饪节目 因为跑步机心跳会变得无聊","audio":"audio/0223_perrin.mp3","duration":5.774},{"id":224,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"I cannot just get on the treadmill and stare forward.","literal_zh":"我不能只上跑步机 向前看","audio":"audio/0224_perrin.mp3","duration":3.974},{"id":225,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"I need something to keep me engaged.","literal_zh":"我需要一些东西 保持我的订婚。","audio":"audio/0225_perrin.mp3","duration":3.254},{"id":226,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"Outside is different.","literal_zh":"外面不一样","audio":"audio/0226_perrin.mp3","duration":2.534},{"id":227,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"We live in a beautiful part of the country, so outdoor cardio feels better.","literal_zh":"我们生活在一个美丽的地方， 户外的心跳感觉更好。","audio":"audio/0227_perrin.mp3","duration":5.366},{"id":228,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"I can listen to music or an audiobook.","literal_zh":"我可以听音乐或听录音","audio":"audio/0228_perrin.mp3","duration":3.518},{"id":229,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"But indoors, you are just in one place.","literal_zh":"但是，室内，你只是在一个地方。","audio":"audio/0229_perrin.mp3","duration":3.806},{"id":230,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"室内有氧训练的无聊感","english":"If the treadmill has a screen, I might watch Netflix or something similar.","literal_zh":"如果跑步机有屏幕 我可能会看Netflix之类的","audio":"audio/0230_perrin.mp3","duration":5.246},{"id":231,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Let me show you how the JabX hardware works.","literal_zh":"让我告诉你JabX硬件是如何工作的","audio":"audio/0231_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.086},{"id":232,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"This is still a prototype, so think of it as the concept version.","literal_zh":"这仍然是一个原型，所以把它当作概念版本.","audio":"audio/0232_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.902},{"id":233,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"It has pads on the front and sides, including upper pads and stomach-level pads.","literal_zh":"它在正面和侧面都有垫，包括上垫和胃层垫.","audio":"audio/0233_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.366},{"id":234,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"There are lights inside the pads, and sensors can detect how hard the user punches.","literal_zh":"垫子内部有灯光，传感器可以探测到用户的拳击有多难.","audio":"audio/0234_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.222},{"id":235,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"There is also a large screen for classes, games and other content.","literal_zh":"还有一个大型屏幕，用于课堂，游戏和其他内容.","audio":"audio/0235_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.43},{"id":236,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"On the sides, there are two moving arms.","literal_zh":"侧面有两只移动的手臂.","audio":"audio/0236_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.726},{"id":237,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"They are designed to make it feel more like training with a real boxing coach.","literal_zh":"他们设计它是为了让感觉更像是训练 一个真正的拳击教练。","audio":"audio/0237_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.262},{"id":238,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"The user hits the pads, and the arms give feedback, so the user has to dodge, roll or move under them.","literal_zh":"用户点击垫子，手臂给出反馈，所以用户必须在垫子下躲避，滚动或移动.","audio":"audio/0238_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.87},{"id":239,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Are the pads farther out than the screen?","literal_zh":"垫子离屏幕还远吗？","audio":"audio/0239_perrin.mp3","duration":3.158},{"id":240,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Is the screen recessed so the user cannot accidentally hit it?","literal_zh":"屏幕是关闭的，所以用户不能不小心击中它吗？","audio":"audio/0240_perrin.mp3","duration":4.526},{"id":241,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Exactly.","literal_zh":"没错","audio":"audio/0241_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.502},{"id":242,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"The user hits the pads, and the screen guides them on where to hit.","literal_zh":"用户点击垫子，屏幕引导他们到哪里点击.","audio":"audio/0242_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.262},{"id":243,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Good.","literal_zh":"不错","audio":"audio/0243_perrin.mp3","duration":1.79},{"id":244,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"That is important.","literal_zh":"这很重要。","audio":"audio/0244_perrin.mp3","duration":2.39},{"id":245,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"So the idea is that JabX can mix boxing classes, aerobic-style classes and high-intensity workouts.","literal_zh":"因此，这个想法是JabX可以混合拳击课，有氧风格的课和高强度的锻炼课.","audio":"audio/0245_interviewer.mp3","duration":6.71},{"id":246,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"It can teach movements like the jab, cross, hook, uppercut and dodge.","literal_zh":"它可以教授动作如刺，交叉，钩，上切和躲避.","audio":"audio/0246_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.838},{"id":247,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Ideally, it feels a bit like a coach holding pads for you.","literal_zh":"理想的情况是，它感觉有点像 教练为你拿着垫子。","audio":"audio/0247_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.638},{"id":248,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"And after the workout, there is a relaxation feature.","literal_zh":"锻炼后有一个放松的功能。","audio":"audio/0248_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.566},{"id":249,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Think of it a bit like a massage cooldown.","literal_zh":"想想看 有点像按摩冷却。","audio":"audio/0249_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.822},{"id":250,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"That is interesting.","literal_zh":"这很有趣。","audio":"audio/0250_perrin.mp3","duration":2.462},{"id":251,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"For beginners, it should start by teaching what the movements look like.","literal_zh":"对于初学者来说，它应该从教导运动的样子开始。","audio":"audio/0251_perrin.mp3","duration":4.91},{"id":252,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Then, as the user gets better, it can build into more complex combinations.","literal_zh":"然后，随着用户的提高，它可以构建成更复杂的组合.","audio":"audio/0252_perrin.mp3","duration":5.822},{"id":253,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Does it teach footwork too?","literal_zh":"它也教脚活吗？","audio":"audio/0253_perrin.mp3","duration":2.726},{"id":254,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Yes.","literal_zh":"对","audio":"audio/0254_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.118},{"id":255,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"The screen can show a real-person tutorial, and the AI movement recognition can give form corrections during the class.","literal_zh":"屏幕可以显示真人辅导，AI运动识别可以在上课期间给出形式校正.","audio":"audio/0255_interviewer.mp3","duration":7.07},{"id":256,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"That is good.","literal_zh":"这是很好的。","audio":"audio/0256_perrin.mp3","duration":2.198},{"id":257,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Footwork matters.","literal_zh":"脚活很重要。","audio":"audio/0257_perrin.mp3","duration":2.486},{"id":258,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"Boxing is not just about the hands.","literal_zh":"拳击不仅仅是手。","audio":"audio/0258_perrin.mp3","duration":3.326},{"id":259,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"JabX 硬件演示与动作反馈","english":"It is also about where your feet are, how you move and how you coordinate the whole body.","literal_zh":"这也是关于你的脚在哪里 如何移动 如何协调整个身体。","audio":"audio/0259_perrin.mp3","duration":5.534},{"id":260,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"So, gut reaction: how does the product concept land for you?","literal_zh":"那么，肠道反应: 产品概念如何为您服务？","audio":"audio/0260_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.902},{"id":261,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"I think it sounds interesting.","literal_zh":"我觉得这听起来很有趣。","audio":"audio/0261_perrin.mp3","duration":2.894},{"id":262,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"The moving-arm feature is different, and I like that.","literal_zh":"移动臂的功能不同 我喜欢","audio":"audio/0262_perrin.mp3","duration":4.166},{"id":263,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Most people learn jabs and uppercuts, but they do not always learn evasion, blocking or how to get out of the way.","literal_zh":"大多数人学习刺拳和上切拳，但他们并不总是学会逃避，阻拦或如何摆脱障碍.","audio":"audio/0263_perrin.mp3","duration":7.358},{"id":264,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Unless you have a real coach, that can be hard to practice.","literal_zh":"除非你有真正的教练 否则很难练习","audio":"audio/0264_perrin.mp3","duration":4.622},{"id":265,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"So if the machine can teach those movements, that is valuable.","literal_zh":"所以，如果机器能教这些动作，那是有价值的。","audio":"audio/0265_perrin.mp3","duration":4.718},{"id":266,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Be honest with us.","literal_zh":"对我们说实话","audio":"audio/0266_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.838},{"id":267,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Would the moving arms feel exciting, or would they make you a little nervous?","literal_zh":"动动的手臂会感到兴奋 还是会让你有点紧张？","audio":"audio/0267_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.694},{"id":268,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"I think that should be more of an advanced feature.","literal_zh":"我认为这应该是一个更先进的特点。","audio":"audio/0268_perrin.mp3","duration":3.614},{"id":269,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Beginners should start with the basic movements first.","literal_zh":"初学者应先从基本运动开始.","audio":"audio/0269_perrin.mp3","duration":3.998},{"id":270,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Then, once they are comfortable, the moving arms can be added.","literal_zh":"然后，一旦它们舒适，就可以添加移动的手臂.","audio":"audio/0270_perrin.mp3","duration":4.79},{"id":271,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"As long as the arms are not too aggressive or unsafe, I would be fine with it.","literal_zh":"只要手臂没有太冲动或不安全，我就可以了。","audio":"audio/0271_perrin.mp3","duration":5.414},{"id":272,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"They are there to teach you how to move.","literal_zh":"他们在那里教你如何移动。","audio":"audio/0272_perrin.mp3","duration":3.062},{"id":273,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Of everything we just walked through, what stood out to you the most?","literal_zh":"我们所经历的一切中，你最突出的是什么？","audio":"audio/0273_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.758},{"id":274,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"I like the idea that the system tells me what to do.","literal_zh":"我喜欢系统告诉我该怎么做的想法。","audio":"audio/0274_perrin.mp3","duration":4.094},{"id":275,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"I do not have to think too much.","literal_zh":"我不必想太多。","audio":"audio/0275_perrin.mp3","duration":3.086},{"id":276,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"I can just follow along.","literal_zh":"我可以跟着你","audio":"audio/0276_perrin.mp3","duration":2.774},{"id":277,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"The lights that show where to hit are important, especially for beginners.","literal_zh":"显示击打地点的灯光很重要，特别是对初学者来说.","audio":"audio/0277_perrin.mp3","duration":5.102},{"id":278,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"But I also think users should be able to turn them off as they improve.","literal_zh":"但我也认为用户应该能够随着改进而关闭.","audio":"audio/0278_perrin.mp3","duration":4.814},{"id":279,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Once someone knows what they are doing, constant light prompts might become annoying.","literal_zh":"一旦有人知道他们在做什么， 恒定的光提示可能会变得烦人。","audio":"audio/0279_perrin.mp3","duration":5.462},{"id":280,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"A beginner may need them.","literal_zh":"初学者可能需要他们","audio":"audio/0280_perrin.mp3","duration":2.654},{"id":281,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"An intermediate user may still like them.","literal_zh":"一个中间用户可能仍然喜欢它们.","audio":"audio/0281_perrin.mp3","duration":3.566},{"id":282,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"But an advanced user may want less guidance.","literal_zh":"但高级用户可能想要较少的指导.","audio":"audio/0282_perrin.mp3","duration":3.662},{"id":283,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"I also like the evasion feature with the moving arms.","literal_zh":"我也喜欢用移动的手臂逃避","audio":"audio/0283_perrin.mp3","duration":3.998},{"id":284,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"Without another person there, it is hard to train that.","literal_zh":"没有其他人在那里，很难训练它。","audio":"audio/0284_perrin.mp3","duration":4.238},{"id":285,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"重点功能反馈：灯光、躲闪与进阶","english":"If the equipment can create that stimulus, the user does not have to guess.","literal_zh":"如果设备可以创造这种刺激，用户就不必猜测.","audio":"audio/0285_perrin.mp3","duration":5.39},{"id":286,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"For the AI coach, what would feel better to you: a male coach, a female coach or both?","literal_zh":"对AI教练来说，你感觉会更好:男教练，女教练还是两者兼而有之？","audio":"audio/0286_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.534},{"id":287,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"You should offer both.","literal_zh":"你应该提供两者。","audio":"audio/0287_perrin.mp3","duration":2.558},{"id":288,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"Some women may relate more to a female coach.","literal_zh":"一些妇女可能与女教练的关系更为密切。","audio":"audio/0288_perrin.mp3","duration":3.902},{"id":289,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"Leila Ali could be a good example of a well-known female boxer.","literal_zh":"莱拉·阿里(英语:Leila Ali)可以是一个著名的女性拳击手的好例子.","audio":"audio/0289_perrin.mp3","duration":4.91},{"id":290,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"For male coaches, people know names like Mike Tyson or Muhammad Ali.","literal_zh":"对于男性教练来说，人们知道麦克·泰森或穆罕默德·阿里等名字.","audio":"audio/0290_perrin.mp3","duration":5.438},{"id":291,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"Having both options is better because people connect with different types of coaches.","literal_zh":"拥有两种选择都更好，因为人们与不同类型的导师有联系.","audio":"audio/0291_perrin.mp3","duration":5.534},{"id":292,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"How much does the look of the machine matter to you?","literal_zh":"机器的外观对你有多重要？","audio":"audio/0292_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.086},{"id":293,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"Color, style, the whole vibe.","literal_zh":"颜色 风格 整个气氛","audio":"audio/0293_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.366},{"id":294,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"Some people like customization.","literal_zh":"有些人喜欢定制。","audio":"audio/0294_perrin.mp3","duration":3.182},{"id":295,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"They want a few color options.","literal_zh":"他们想要一些颜色选择。","audio":"audio/0295_perrin.mp3","duration":3.086},{"id":296,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"Black is always the safe choice.","literal_zh":"黑色总是安全的选择。","audio":"audio/0296_perrin.mp3","duration":3.254},{"id":297,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"It fits most home gyms.","literal_zh":"它适合大多数的家体育馆。","audio":"audio/0297_perrin.mp3","duration":2.87},{"id":298,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"White can look clean and modern, but it may not fit every gym as well as black.","literal_zh":"白色可以看起来干净和现代，但可能不适合每一个健身房和黑色.","audio":"audio/0298_perrin.mp3","duration":5.486},{"id":299,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"Our home gym has blue and red accents, so blue or red options would be interesting to us.","literal_zh":"我们家的体育馆有蓝色和红色的口音，所以蓝色或红色的选择对我们来说是有趣的.","audio":"audio/0299_perrin.mp3","duration":6.542},{"id":300,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"Some people design their gym around a certain color.","literal_zh":"有些人用某种颜色设计自己的健身房.","audio":"audio/0300_perrin.mp3","duration":3.926},{"id":301,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"AI 教练形象与设备外观","english":"But if you can only choose one color, I would go with black.","literal_zh":"但是如果你只能选择一种颜色， 我会用黑色的。","audio":"audio/0301_perrin.mp3","duration":4.406},{"id":302,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"We are also playing with a game mode that works more like a rhythm game.","literal_zh":"我们还在玩一种更像节奏游戏的游戏模式。","audio":"audio/0302_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.974},{"id":303,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"You hit the pads along with the music.","literal_zh":"你和音乐一起打垫子","audio":"audio/0303_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.702},{"id":304,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"I like that.","literal_zh":"我喜欢","audio":"audio/0304_perrin.mp3","duration":2.294},{"id":305,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"It reminds me of dance games where you step on the squares to the music, or VR games where you punch targets in the air.","literal_zh":"它让我想起了舞蹈游戏，你踩在广场上的音乐，或者VR游戏，你在空中打靶.","audio":"audio/0305_perrin.mp3","duration":7.67},{"id":306,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"That kind of game helps with hand-eye coordination.","literal_zh":"这种游戏有助于手眼的协调。","audio":"audio/0306_perrin.mp3","duration":3.878},{"id":307,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"Your eyes see the target, and your hands react.","literal_zh":"你的眼睛看到目标，你的手反应。","audio":"audio/0307_perrin.mp3","duration":3.926},{"id":308,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"I also like gamification in general.","literal_zh":"我也喜欢游戏一般。","audio":"audio/0308_perrin.mp3","duration":3.518},{"id":309,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"It makes the workout more exciting.","literal_zh":"这让锻炼更刺激.","audio":"audio/0309_perrin.mp3","duration":3.158},{"id":310,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"I am competitive, so if you give me a score based on how hard I hit, how many targets I hit or how I compare with my husband or kids, that sounds fun.","literal_zh":"我是有竞争力的，所以如果你给我一个分数 依据我打的多重，我打的多少目标， 或者我如何比较我的丈夫或孩子， 这听起来很有趣。","audio":"audio/0310_perrin.mp3","duration":9.926},{"id":311,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"In another version, you would hit the pads to the beat while the moving arms come in, so you have to duck or dodge too.","literal_zh":"在另一种版本中，你会在移动的手臂进来时撞到拍子上的垫子，所以你还必须躲开或躲避.","audio":"audio/0311_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.87},{"id":312,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"That sounds fun.","literal_zh":"这听起来很有趣。","audio":"audio/0312_perrin.mp3","duration":2.438},{"id":313,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"I would be interested in that.","literal_zh":"我对此有兴趣。","audio":"audio/0313_perrin.mp3","duration":2.87},{"id":314,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"We are also thinking about multiplayer.","literal_zh":"我们还在考虑多人游戏。","audio":"audio/0314_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.822},{"id":315,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"Picture one person on the left, one on the right, both playing at the same time.","literal_zh":"想象左边一人，右边一人，都同时演奏.","audio":"audio/0315_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.598},{"id":316,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"That could be cool, as long as the setup is safe for two people.","literal_zh":"那可能很酷 只要对两个人安全","audio":"audio/0316_perrin.mp3","duration":4.79},{"id":317,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"What about a phone-control mode?","literal_zh":"电话控制模式呢？","audio":"audio/0317_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.342},{"id":318,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"Say your son is on the app while you are training, and he can change the pads or moving arms in real time.","literal_zh":"说你儿子在接受训练时正在应用 他可以实时更换垫子或移动手臂","audio":"audio/0318_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.99},{"id":319,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"My sons would love that.","literal_zh":"我儿子会喜欢的","audio":"audio/0319_perrin.mp3","duration":2.75},{"id":320,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"They would enjoy controlling it and making the workout harder for us.","literal_zh":"他们喜欢控制它，让我们更难解决。","audio":"audio/0320_perrin.mp3","duration":4.622},{"id":321,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"游戏模式、多人互动与手机控制","english":"That could be a fun family feature.","literal_zh":"这可能是一个有趣的家庭特色。","audio":"audio/0321_perrin.mp3","duration":3.23},{"id":322,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I noticed the Apple Watch.","literal_zh":"我注意到苹果观察。","audio":"audio/0322_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.126},{"id":323,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"Are you using that mainly for fitness tracking, or more for everyday stuff?","literal_zh":"你主要用来追踪身体状况 还是用来做日常工作？","audio":"audio/0323_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.718},{"id":324,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I wear both an Apple Watch and a WHOOP.","literal_zh":"我戴着苹果表和WOOP","audio":"audio/0324_perrin.mp3","duration":3.23},{"id":325,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I charge my Apple Watch at night, so most of my sleep and heart-rate data comes from WHOOP.","literal_zh":"晚上我收取苹果表，所以我大部分睡眠和心率数据来自WHOOP.","audio":"audio/0325_perrin.mp3","duration":6.014},{"id":326,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I mostly use the Apple Watch for steps, texts, emails and notifications.","literal_zh":"我主要使用苹果观察 的步骤，短信，电子邮件和通知。","audio":"audio/0326_perrin.mp3","duration":6.182},{"id":327,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"For health data, I rely more on WHOOP.","literal_zh":"关于健康数据，我更依赖WHOOP.","audio":"audio/0327_perrin.mp3","duration":3.494},{"id":328,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"With WHOOP, I track sleep, heart-rate zones, strain and recovery.","literal_zh":"用WHOOP，我跟踪睡眠，心率区，紧张和复苏。","audio":"audio/0328_perrin.mp3","duration":5.414},{"id":329,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I start an activity for every workout, whether it is lifting, walking, running, swimming, cardio or boxing.","literal_zh":"我开始每个运动， 无论是举起，步行，跑步，游泳，心跳还是拳击。","audio":"audio/0329_perrin.mp3","duration":8.246},{"id":330,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"WHOOP uses my heart rate to calculate strain, and that affects my recovery score.","literal_zh":"WHOOP用我的心率来计算压力， 这影响了我的恢复分数.","audio":"audio/0330_perrin.mp3","duration":5.99},{"id":331,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"Every morning, I check my sleep, strain and recovery.","literal_zh":"每天早上，我检查我的睡眠，紧张和康复。","audio":"audio/0331_perrin.mp3","duration":4.766},{"id":332,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"If my recovery is in the red, I know I should not push as hard that day.","literal_zh":"如果我的康复是红色的，我知道我不应该 推那么用力的那一天。","audio":"audio/0332_perrin.mp3","duration":5.078},{"id":333,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I mostly look for patterns.","literal_zh":"我主要寻找规律","audio":"audio/0333_perrin.mp3","duration":2.99},{"id":334,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I want to know what affects my recovery.","literal_zh":"我想知道什么影响我的康复。","audio":"audio/0334_perrin.mp3","duration":3.374},{"id":335,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"WHOOP often tells me to go to bed earlier or keep my sleep schedule more consistent.","literal_zh":"WHOOP经常让我早点上床，或者保持睡眠时间的一致.","audio":"audio/0335_perrin.mp3","duration":5.822},{"id":336,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"WHOOP is not great for steps yet, so I still use Apple Watch for that.","literal_zh":"WHOOP对台阶还不太好，所以我仍然使用苹果观察来做这个.","audio":"audio/0336_perrin.mp3","duration":5.222},{"id":337,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"Do you ever use the AI features in WHOOP?","literal_zh":"你有没有使用过WHOOP中的AI功能？","audio":"audio/0337_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.846},{"id":338,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"Sometimes, but not as much as I could.","literal_zh":"有时候，但没我能做多少。","audio":"audio/0338_perrin.mp3","duration":3.662},{"id":339,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I work for a marketing company, and we use AI a lot, so I can get a little overloaded with it.","literal_zh":"我为一家营销公司工作，我们经常使用AI，这样我就可以有点超载.","audio":"audio/0339_perrin.mp3","duration":6.59},{"id":340,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"One way I used WHOOP AI was to add a 10-minute warm-up walk before every lifting day.","literal_zh":"我使用WHOOP AI的方法之一是在每个升起日之前增加一个10分钟的热身步行.","audio":"audio/0340_perrin.mp3","duration":6.134},{"id":341,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"可穿戴设备与健康数据","english":"I told it what I wanted, and it added that warm-up to my WHOOP schedule.","literal_zh":"我告诉它我想要的， 它增加了热身 我的WHOP时间表。","audio":"audio/0341_perrin.mp3","duration":4.982},{"id":342,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"How big is Tonal in your world?","literal_zh":"托纳尔在你的世界里有多大？","audio":"audio/0342_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.486},{"id":343,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"Do people around you use it or talk about it much?","literal_zh":"你周围的人用它或谈论它很多？","audio":"audio/0343_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.254},{"id":344,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"Tonal has a large community, especially on Facebook.","literal_zh":"Tonal有一个庞大的社区，特别是在Facebook上.","audio":"audio/0344_perrin.mp3","duration":4.502},{"id":345,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"When we first started our channel, we wanted to show Tonal users how they could combine Tonal with other home gym equipment and accessories.","literal_zh":"当我们开始频道时，我们想向Tonal用户展示Tonal与其他家庭体育器材和配件如何结合.","audio":"audio/0345_perrin.mp3","duration":8.51},{"id":346,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"We wanted to show a more hybrid setup.","literal_zh":"我们想展示一个更混合的设定。","audio":"audio/0346_perrin.mp3","duration":3.254},{"id":347,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"It did not have to be only Tonal.","literal_zh":"不一定只用Tonal来做","audio":"audio/0347_perrin.mp3","duration":3.158},{"id":348,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"But Tonal is fairly restrictive about what you can share if it is not through them.","literal_zh":"但是，Tonal对于你能够分享的，如果不通过它们，是相当有限的。","audio":"audio/0348_perrin.mp3","duration":5.198},{"id":349,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"So we moved away from focusing on that.","literal_zh":"于是我们不再关注这个问题。","audio":"audio/0349_perrin.mp3","duration":3.494},{"id":350,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"The biggest complaint people have about Tonal is the monthly subscription.","literal_zh":"人们对Tonal最大的抱怨是每月订阅.","audio":"audio/0350_perrin.mp3","duration":5.078},{"id":351,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"If you cancel the membership, you lose many of the smart features.","literal_zh":"如果取消会员资格，就会失去许多智能功能.","audio":"audio/0351_perrin.mp3","duration":4.814},{"id":352,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"You can still use the machine, but it becomes more like an expensive functional trainer on the wall.","literal_zh":"仍然可以使用机器，但变得更像是墙上昂贵的功能教练.","audio":"audio/0352_perrin.mp3","duration":6.374},{"id":353,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"People say similar things about Peloton.","literal_zh":"人们对佩洛顿也有类似的说法.","audio":"audio/0353_perrin.mp3","duration":3.542},{"id":354,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"I understand why companies charge subscriptions.","literal_zh":"我知道为什么公司要收订阅费","audio":"audio/0354_perrin.mp3","duration":4.07},{"id":355,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"They need to maintain programs, coaches and classes.","literal_zh":"他们需要保持程序，教练和班级.","audio":"audio/0355_perrin.mp3","duration":4.334},{"id":356,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"But if you can create a great experience without forcing a monthly fee, that is a strong selling point.","literal_zh":"但是，如果你可以创造一个伟大的经验 而不强制每月收费， 这是一个强大的销售点。","audio":"audio/0356_perrin.mp3","duration":6.854},{"id":357,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"One option is to include a basic set of programs with the machine and then sell extra program bundles.","literal_zh":"一个选项是包含一套与机器一起的基本程序，然后出售额外的程序捆绑.","audio":"audio/0357_perrin.mp3","duration":6.926},{"id":358,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"For example, users could pay for a pack of 10 new workouts if they want more variety.","literal_zh":"例如，用户如果想要更多种类，可以支付一包10个新工作.","audio":"audio/0358_perrin.mp3","duration":6.062},{"id":359,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"That gives you revenue without making everyone pay a subscription.","literal_zh":"这样你就能赚到收入了 不必让每个人都付订金","audio":"audio/0359_perrin.mp3","duration":4.742},{"id":360,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"WHOOP is subscription-based too.","literal_zh":"WHOOP也以订阅为基础.","audio":"audio/0360_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.39},{"id":361,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"How do you feel about that model?","literal_zh":"你觉得那个模特怎么样？","audio":"audio/0361_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.294},{"id":362,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"That is one thing I do not love.","literal_zh":"这是我不爱的一件事。","audio":"audio/0362_perrin.mp3","duration":3.158},{"id":363,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"WHOOP does offer family plans and tiered plans, which helps.","literal_zh":"WHOOP确实提供家庭计划和分层计划，这有帮助。","audio":"audio/0363_perrin.mp3","duration":4.934},{"id":364,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"My husband has a higher tier than I do because he wanted some extra features.","literal_zh":"我丈夫有比我更高的层次 因为他想要一些额外的特征。","audio":"audio/0364_perrin.mp3","duration":5.486},{"id":365,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"I think tiers can work if people clearly understand what they are paying for.","literal_zh":"我认为，如果人们清楚地了解他们付出的代价，等级可以发挥作用。","audio":"audio/0365_perrin.mp3","duration":5.39},{"id":366,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"For JabX, you could have a basic package with the core features.","literal_zh":"对于JabX，你可以有一个具有核心特征的基本包.","audio":"audio/0366_perrin.mp3","duration":4.886},{"id":367,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"Tonal、订阅模式与内容付费","english":"Then you could offer higher tiers for people who want new programs, extra features or ongoing content.","literal_zh":"然后，你可以为需要新程序、额外功能或持续内容的人提供更高层次的服务。","audio":"audio/0367_perrin.mp3","duration":7.118},{"id":368,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Given everything we described, what price range would feel fair for JabX if there were no required subscription?","literal_zh":"鉴于我们所描述的一切，如果没有必要的订阅，JabX会觉得什么价格范围是公平的？","audio":"audio/0368_interviewer.mp3","duration":6.11},{"id":369,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"I do not know your manufacturing cost or margins, so it is hard to say exactly.","literal_zh":"我不知道你的制造成本和利润 所以很难说清楚","audio":"audio/0369_perrin.mp3","duration":6.062},{"id":370,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"But Tonal is around $4,200, and some of what you described feels similar in value.","literal_zh":"但Tonal大约是4200美元， 你描述的一些东西也觉得价值相似。","audio":"audio/0370_perrin.mp3","duration":7.286},{"id":371,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"If JabX includes the hardware, AI features, training programs and game functions you mentioned, around $4,000 sounds reasonable to me.","literal_zh":"如果JabX包含你提到的硬件，AI功能，培训程序和游戏功能，大约4000美元对我来说是合理的.","audio":"audio/0371_perrin.mp3","duration":9.902},{"id":372,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"For coaching, would you rather see AI-generated coaches, real human coaches or maybe both?","literal_zh":"关于教练，你宁愿看AI产生的教练，真正的人类教练，还是两者兼而有之？","audio":"audio/0372_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.27},{"id":373,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"One thing that really sells Tonal is the real coaches.","literal_zh":"真正卖Tonal的是真正的导师","audio":"audio/0373_perrin.mp3","duration":4.31},{"id":374,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Users can watch them, connect with them and feel like they know them.","literal_zh":"用户可以观看它们，与它们连接，并感觉他们了解它们.","audio":"audio/0374_perrin.mp3","duration":4.838},{"id":375,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Tonal also has Facebook groups where coaches interact with users, answer questions and lead challenges.","literal_zh":"Tonal也拥有脸书组，导师与用户互动，回答问题并领导挑战.","audio":"audio/0375_perrin.mp3","duration":7.358},{"id":376,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"That community connection is a big selling point.","literal_zh":"社区联系是一个大卖点。","audio":"audio/0376_perrin.mp3","duration":4.142},{"id":377,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"You do not need a huge number of coaches.","literal_zh":"你不需要很多教练","audio":"audio/0377_perrin.mp3","duration":3.566},{"id":378,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"You could start with one male coach and one female coach.","literal_zh":"你可以从一个男教练和一个女教练开始","audio":"audio/0378_perrin.mp3","duration":4.358},{"id":379,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"But having real people lead programs, run challenges and talk to the community can be powerful.","literal_zh":"但让真人领导节目，主持挑战，与社区交谈，可以很有力量.","audio":"audio/0379_perrin.mp3","duration":6.71},{"id":380,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Some users need that social connection to stay motivated.","literal_zh":"有些用户需要这种社会联系才能保持积极性。","audio":"audio/0380_perrin.mp3","duration":4.31},{"id":381,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Others, like my younger son, just want to get in, do the workout and leave.","literal_zh":"其他人，比如我小儿子， 只想进去，做锻炼和离开。","audio":"audio/0381_perrin.mp3","duration":5.702},{"id":382,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"You need to think about both types of users.","literal_zh":"你需要考虑两种类型的用户.","audio":"audio/0382_perrin.mp3","duration":3.59},{"id":383,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Do those coaches need to be famous, or is credibility the bigger thing?","literal_zh":"这些导师需要出名，还是信誉是更重要的事？","audio":"audio/0383_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.574},{"id":384,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Fame does not matter that much to me.","literal_zh":"名声对我不重要","audio":"audio/0384_perrin.mp3","duration":3.254},{"id":385,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Fame does not always mean someone is good.","literal_zh":"名声并不总是意味着某人是好人。","audio":"audio/0385_perrin.mp3","duration":3.494},{"id":386,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"Credibility matters more.","literal_zh":"可信度更为重要。","audio":"audio/0386_perrin.mp3","duration":2.846},{"id":387,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"If a very skinny person is trying to teach me how to build muscle, that is hard for me to believe.","literal_zh":"如果一个非常瘦的人试图教我如何建立肌肉，那对我来说很难相信.","audio":"audio/0387_perrin.mp3","duration":6.59},{"id":388,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"If someone who appears very out of shape is teaching cardio, some users may struggle to trust them.","literal_zh":"如果某个看起来非常不健全的人在教心术，一些用户可能难以相信他们.","audio":"audio/0388_perrin.mp3","duration":6.686},{"id":389,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"I know appearance is not always a true measure of health.","literal_zh":"我知道外表并不总是真正的健康标准","audio":"audio/0389_perrin.mp3","duration":4.118},{"id":390,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"But from a marketing point of view, image does matter.","literal_zh":"但从营销角度看，形象确实很重要.","audio":"audio/0390_perrin.mp3","duration":4.166},{"id":391,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"The coach does not have to be famous, but they should look credible for what they are teaching.","literal_zh":"教练虽然不必出名，但他们应该以自己所教的东西看起来可信.","audio":"audio/0391_perrin.mp3","duration":5.75},{"id":392,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"设备定价、真实教练与社区运营","english":"They should also come across as supportive and competent.","literal_zh":"他们也应该表现出支持性和胜任性。","audio":"audio/0392_perrin.mp3","duration":4.022},{"id":393,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"You seem really disciplined.","literal_zh":"你看起来很守纪律","audio":"audio/0393_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.126},{"id":394,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"What keeps you going?","literal_zh":"什么让你继续？","audio":"audio/0394_interviewer.mp3","duration":1.79},{"id":395,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"And what could JabX do for people who need a little more help staying consistent?","literal_zh":"JabX能为需要更多帮助的人做些什么？","audio":"audio/0395_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.55},{"id":396,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Gamification can help a lot.","literal_zh":"赌博可以帮助很多。","audio":"audio/0396_perrin.mp3","duration":3.134},{"id":397,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"WHOOP shows streaks and milestones, like how many days you have used it.","literal_zh":"WHOOP显示的历程和里程碑， 就像你用了多少天。","audio":"audio/0397_perrin.mp3","duration":5.03},{"id":398,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"For me, I do not want to break a streak.","literal_zh":"对我来说，我不想打破历史。","audio":"audio/0398_perrin.mp3","duration":3.614},{"id":399,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"If I am at 400 days, I do not want that number to go back to zero.","literal_zh":"如果我在400天，我不希望这个数字回到零。","audio":"audio/0399_perrin.mp3","duration":5.39},{"id":400,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"I am a data person.","literal_zh":"我是一个数据人。","audio":"audio/0400_perrin.mp3","duration":2.582},{"id":401,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"I love numbers.","literal_zh":"我喜欢数字","audio":"audio/0401_perrin.mp3","duration":2.414},{"id":402,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Discipline is not always something you can teach.","literal_zh":"纪律并不总是你能教的","audio":"audio/0402_perrin.mp3","duration":3.782},{"id":403,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"It has to come from inside the person.","literal_zh":"它必须来自人体内。","audio":"audio/0403_perrin.mp3","duration":3.278},{"id":404,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"But motivation can support discipline.","literal_zh":"但动机可以支持纪律。","audio":"audio/0404_perrin.mp3","duration":3.494},{"id":405,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Some people are motivated by streaks.","literal_zh":"有些人的动机是连锁店。","audio":"audio/0405_perrin.mp3","duration":3.518},{"id":406,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Some are motivated by fun.","literal_zh":"有些是出于乐趣","audio":"audio/0406_perrin.mp3","duration":2.942},{"id":407,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Some need a bigger goal.","literal_zh":"有些人需要更大的目标。","audio":"audio/0407_perrin.mp3","duration":2.606},{"id":408,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"For my husband and me, the goal is to live longer for our children and future grandchildren.","literal_zh":"对于我丈夫和我来说，目标是为我们的孩子和未来的孙子们长寿.","audio":"audio/0408_perrin.mp3","duration":6.182},{"id":409,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"That keeps us going, even on days when we do not feel like working out.","literal_zh":"这让我们继续前进，即使在我们不想工作的日子。","audio":"audio/0409_perrin.mp3","duration":5.078},{"id":410,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"If JabX is engaging, fun and personalized, people are more likely to keep using it.","literal_zh":"如果JabX正在参与，有趣和个性化，人们更有可能继续使用.","audio":"audio/0410_perrin.mp3","duration":6.422},{"id":411,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Coach interaction, programs, data, streaks, games and adaptive training could all help.","literal_zh":"教练互动、程序、数据、赛程、比赛和适应性训练都可能有所帮助。","audio":"audio/0411_perrin.mp3","duration":6.758},{"id":412,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Since you are a data person, do you track VO2 max?","literal_zh":"既然你是一个数据人， 你跟踪VO2最大？","audio":"audio/0412_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.566},{"id":413,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Yes.","literal_zh":"对","audio":"audio/0413_perrin.mp3","duration":1.958},{"id":414,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"I have done DEXA scans, RMR tests and VO2 testing.","literal_zh":"我做了DEXA扫描，RMR测试和VO2测试.","audio":"audio/0414_perrin.mp3","duration":5.222},{"id":415,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"A DEXA scan gives information like body mass, body fat, body weight and bone density.","literal_zh":"DEXA扫描给出了身体质量，身体脂肪，体重和骨密度等信息.","audio":"audio/0415_perrin.mp3","duration":6.614},{"id":416,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"RMR testing looks at metabolism.","literal_zh":"RMR测试研究的是新陈代谢.","audio":"audio/0416_perrin.mp3","duration":3.47},{"id":417,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"VO2 testing measures cardio output.","literal_zh":"VO2测试测量心肌输出.","audio":"audio/0417_perrin.mp3","duration":3.782},{"id":418,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"I also track HRV.","literal_zh":"我也追踪HRV","audio":"audio/0418_perrin.mp3","duration":2.894},{"id":419,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"I like data, so the more useful data a machine can give me, the better.","literal_zh":"我喜欢数据，所以机器能给我的更有用的数据越好。","audio":"audio/0419_perrin.mp3","duration":5.342},{"id":420,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Would you ever plan workouts specifically to improve VO2 max?","literal_zh":"你是否打算过特别的 改进VO2最大吗？","audio":"audio/0420_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.358},{"id":421,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Not right now, because my main goal is building muscle.","literal_zh":"现在不行 因为我的主要目标是建立肌肉","audio":"audio/0421_perrin.mp3","duration":4.502},{"id":422,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"But I do want to improve my heart-rate zones and cardio output when I do cardio.","literal_zh":"但我确实想改善心率区 和心肌输出 当我做心肌。","audio":"audio/0422_perrin.mp3","duration":5.558},{"id":423,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"If I improve my cardio through boxing, it should also help my running pace and VO2 max.","literal_zh":"如果我通过拳击来改进我的心律，它也应该帮助我的跑步速度和VO2最大.","audio":"audio/0423_perrin.mp3","duration":6.662},{"id":424,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"I may not train directly for VO2 max, but I would watch the connection.","literal_zh":"我可能不会直接训练 VO2最大， 但我会看连接。","audio":"audio/0424_perrin.mp3","duration":5.51},{"id":425,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"When you do cardio, are you watching your heart-rate zones in real time?","literal_zh":"当你做心跳的时候，你是否在实时观察你的心率区？","audio":"audio/0425_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.142},{"id":426,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"Yes.","literal_zh":"对","audio":"audio/0426_perrin.mp3","duration":1.958},{"id":427,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"I usually keep my WHOOP app open so I can see my strain and heart-rate zone.","literal_zh":"我通常保持我的WOOP应用打开，这样我就能看到我的菌株和心率区.","audio":"audio/0427_perrin.mp3","duration":5.366},{"id":428,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"My WHOOP connects to my treadmill, so it can track my zone.","literal_zh":"我的WOOP连接到我的跑步机， 这样它就可以跟踪我的区域。","audio":"audio/0428_perrin.mp3","duration":4.622},{"id":429,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"I can set the treadmill to keep me in a target heart-rate zone.","literal_zh":"我可以设置跑步机 让我进入目标心率区","audio":"audio/0429_perrin.mp3","duration":4.526},{"id":430,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"自律、动机与数据驱动训练","english":"If my heart rate drops, the treadmill can automatically increase speed or incline to bring it back up.","literal_zh":"如果我的心率下降， 跑步机可以自动增加速度或线条 使其恢复。","audio":"audio/0430_perrin.mp3","duration":6.878},{"id":431,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"If JabX were in your home gym, would it replace something, or would it be more of an add-on?","literal_zh":"如果JabX在你家里的健身房， 它会替换什么， 还是更像是附加？","audio":"audio/0431_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.198},{"id":432,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"It would be an add-on.","literal_zh":"这将是一个附加。","audio":"audio/0432_perrin.mp3","duration":2.462},{"id":433,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"It would not replace anything.","literal_zh":"它不会取代任何东西。","audio":"audio/0433_perrin.mp3","duration":2.87},{"id":434,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"The treadmill is the one cardio machine we use regularly, and we will probably always keep it because it is so versatile.","literal_zh":"跑步机是我们经常使用的一种心肺机，我们可能永远保留它，因为它非常多功能。","audio":"audio/0434_perrin.mp3","duration":7.814},{"id":435,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"We got rid of the bike and rower because we did not use them enough, but the treadmill has always stayed useful.","literal_zh":"我们摆脱了自行车和划船机，因为我们没有充分利用它们，但跑步机一直有用.","audio":"audio/0435_perrin.mp3","duration":6.926},{"id":436,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"We are open to adding equipment if we think we will use it.","literal_zh":"我们愿意增加设备，如果我们想使用它。","audio":"audio/0436_perrin.mp3","duration":4.286},{"id":437,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"If something does not get used much, we usually sell it to someone who will use it more.","literal_zh":"如果用得不多的话，我们通常会把它卖给会多用它的人。","audio":"audio/0437_perrin.mp3","duration":5.846},{"id":438,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"What do you think about a built-in glove dryer?","literal_zh":"内置手套烘干机怎么样？","audio":"audio/0438_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.774},{"id":439,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"It would be an add-on, probably around $50.","literal_zh":"这将是一个附加， 大概50美元左右。","audio":"audio/0439_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.398},{"id":440,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"I think some people would like that.","literal_zh":"我想有些人会喜欢的","audio":"audio/0440_perrin.mp3","duration":3.086},{"id":441,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"For me, the big thing is storage.","literal_zh":"对我来说，大事情是储存。","audio":"audio/0441_perrin.mp3","duration":3.47},{"id":442,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"I do not want to store gloves somewhere else.","literal_zh":"我不想在别处存放手套","audio":"audio/0442_perrin.mp3","duration":3.47},{"id":443,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"I want them on the unit so I can grab them when I am ready to train.","literal_zh":"我要他们加入部队 等我准备好训练时再抓他们","audio":"audio/0443_perrin.mp3","duration":4.694},{"id":444,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"If the unit has glove storage and drying, that is useful.","literal_zh":"如果这个单位有手套储存和干燥，那是有用的.","audio":"audio/0444_perrin.mp3","duration":4.478},{"id":445,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"It also helps with smell because the gloves can dry properly.","literal_zh":"这也有助于嗅觉，因为手套可以适当干燥.","audio":"audio/0445_perrin.mp3","duration":4.55},{"id":446,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"I would pay $50 for that because it is not just drying.","literal_zh":"我愿意为此付出50美元，因为它不仅仅是干燥。","audio":"audio/0446_perrin.mp3","duration":4.598},{"id":447,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"It is also storage.","literal_zh":"它也是储存的。","audio":"audio/0447_perrin.mp3","duration":2.63},{"id":448,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"What about resistance bands as an add-on?","literal_zh":"抵抗乐队作为附加？","audio":"audio/0448_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.99},{"id":449,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"A lot of home gym users already have resistance bands.","literal_zh":"许多家用健身房用户已经拥有了抵抗乐队.","audio":"audio/0449_perrin.mp3","duration":4.502},{"id":450,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"We have a lot of them, so I probably would not buy them as an add-on.","literal_zh":"我们有很多，所以我可能不会买 作为附加。","audio":"audio/0450_perrin.mp3","duration":4.694},{"id":451,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"But for people who do not already have them, it could be useful.","literal_zh":"但是，对于还没有拥有它们的人来说，这可能是有益的。","audio":"audio/0451_perrin.mp3","duration":4.574},{"id":452,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"家庭健身房定位与配件反馈","english":"The price just needs to make sense because you can buy resistance bands on Amazon for around $35.","literal_zh":"价格需要合理 因为你可以在亚马逊购买约35美元的抵抗乐队.","audio":"audio/0452_perrin.mp3","duration":7.262},{"id":453,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"What do you think about body-composition tracking?","literal_zh":"你觉得身体结构跟踪怎么样？","audio":"audio/0453_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.23},{"id":454,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"For example, every time someone turns on JabX, it could scan their body and show how things change over time.","literal_zh":"例如，每当有人打开JabX时，它可以扫描他们的身体，显示事情如何随时间变化.","audio":"audio/0454_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.99},{"id":455,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"I would be careful with accuracy.","literal_zh":"我会小心准确。","audio":"audio/0455_perrin.mp3","duration":3.11},{"id":456,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"There are a lot of scales and devices that claim to measure body composition, but they are not always fully accurate.","literal_zh":"有许多天平和装置声称要测量身体组成，但它们并不总是完全准确的.","audio":"audio/0456_perrin.mp3","duration":7.454},{"id":457,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"I would use that kind of data as a trend, not as an exact number.","literal_zh":"我将使用这种数据作为趋势，而不是确切的数字。","audio":"audio/0457_perrin.mp3","duration":4.934},{"id":458,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"If I scan myself one day and then see the number change consistently over time, that trend can be useful.","literal_zh":"如果有一天我扫描自己，然后看到数字随时间变化而变化，那么这种趋势就可能有用。","audio":"audio/0458_perrin.mp3","duration":7.334},{"id":459,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"But I would not fully trust the exact number.","literal_zh":"但我不会完全相信确切的数字。","audio":"audio/0459_perrin.mp3","duration":3.662},{"id":460,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"One type of body-composition scale uses sensors that you hold, and it sends a small current through the body.","literal_zh":"一种类型的身体结构尺度使用你持有的传感器，它通过身体发出小电流.","audio":"audio/0460_perrin.mp3","duration":7.07},{"id":461,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"That feels more credible to me than just using an image-based scan.","literal_zh":"我觉得比用图像扫描更可信","audio":"audio/0461_perrin.mp3","duration":4.862},{"id":462,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"身体数据扫描与趋势追踪","english":"I reviewed the Arboleaf scale on our YouTube channel, and in that review I talk about exact numbers versus trends.","literal_zh":"我在YouTube频道上回顾了Arboleaf比例表，","audio":"audio/0462_perrin.mp3","duration":7.622},{"id":463,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"You have seen the concept now.","literal_zh":"你现在看到了这个概念。","audio":"audio/0463_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.246},{"id":464,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Any questions for us, or anything you think we should be paying attention to?","literal_zh":"对我们有什么问题吗？ 或者你认为我们应该注意什么？","audio":"audio/0464_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.334},{"id":465,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"My main question is where you are in the launch process.","literal_zh":"我的主要疑问是你们在发射过程中的位置。","audio":"audio/0465_perrin.mp3","duration":4.142},{"id":466,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Do you have a target launch date?","literal_zh":"你有目标发射日期吗？","audio":"audio/0466_perrin.mp3","duration":2.87},{"id":467,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"We are aiming for August.","literal_zh":"我们的目标是8月。","audio":"audio/0467_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.246},{"id":468,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"We are also planning to be at CES in January in Las Vegas.","literal_zh":"我们还计划1月份在拉斯维加斯的CES。","audio":"audio/0468_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.238},{"id":469,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"August is soon.","literal_zh":"八月即时.","audio":"audio/0469_perrin.mp3","duration":2.39},{"id":470,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"CES is a major event.","literal_zh":"CES是一个重大事件。","audio":"audio/0470_perrin.mp3","duration":3.014},{"id":471,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Another event you may want to look at in the future is Home Gym Con.","literal_zh":"你将来可能想看的另外一个事件是Home Gym Con.","audio":"audio/0471_perrin.mp3","duration":4.766},{"id":472,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"It happens around the end of July or beginning of August.","literal_zh":"发生在7月底或8月初左右.","audio":"audio/0472_perrin.mp3","duration":4.406},{"id":473,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Jeff and I go every year.","literal_zh":"Jeff和我每年都去","audio":"audio/0473_perrin.mp3","duration":2.774},{"id":474,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"It has become a pretty large event, and it would be relevant for a product like this.","literal_zh":"它已经成为一个相当大的事件， 它将会与这样的产品有关。","audio":"audio/0474_perrin.mp3","duration":5.606},{"id":475,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"It may be too soon for this year, but it could be worth considering later.","literal_zh":"今年可能为时太早，但值得稍后考虑。","audio":"audio/0475_perrin.mp3","duration":5.174},{"id":476,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"We are not currently scheduled for CES, but my husband has wanted to go to Las Vegas, so we can look into it.","literal_zh":"我们目前没有安排CES， 但我的丈夫已经想去拉斯维加斯， 所以我们可以调查它。","audio":"audio/0476_perrin.mp3","duration":7.742},{"id":477,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"The channel is a second job for both of us, and we both work full-time, so we have to plan events around our main work schedules.","literal_zh":"该频道是我们俩的第二份工作，我们都是全职工作，所以我们必须围绕我们的主要工作时间表规划活动.","audio":"audio/0477_perrin.mp3","duration":8.27},{"id":478,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Would it be okay if we added you to our WhatsApp group and sent occasional updates?","literal_zh":"我们把你加入我们的WhatsApp小组 偶尔发送最新消息可以吗？","audio":"audio/0478_interviewer.mp3","duration":4.79},{"id":479,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Nothing crazy, maybe once a month.","literal_zh":"没什么疯狂的，也许一个月一次。","audio":"audio/0479_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.63},{"id":480,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Yes, that would be fine.","literal_zh":"是的，这将是罚款。","audio":"audio/0480_perrin.mp3","duration":2.99},{"id":481,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"We would love to stay updated.","literal_zh":"我们很乐意随时更新","audio":"audio/0481_perrin.mp3","duration":2.87},{"id":482,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"When the units are ready, if you want to send us one for review, we would be happy to test it.","literal_zh":"等部队准备好了 如果你想派一个来审查 我们很乐意测试一下","audio":"audio/0482_perrin.mp3","duration":6.206},{"id":483,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"When we review equipment, we do not just test it and publish criticism.","literal_zh":"当我们审查设备时，我们不仅测试设备并发表批评意见。","audio":"audio/0483_perrin.mp3","duration":5.246},{"id":484,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"While we are using it, we reach out to the vendor with questions and feedback.","literal_zh":"在我们使用时，我们向供应商提出问题和反馈。","audio":"audio/0484_perrin.mp3","duration":5.15},{"id":485,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"We may ask whether something is working as intended or whether a feature is supposed to work differently.","literal_zh":"我们可以问一问，某种东西是否如预期的那样起作用，或者某种特征是否应该不同地起作用。","audio":"audio/0485_perrin.mp3","duration":6.374},{"id":486,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"That gives the company a chance to explain, fix an issue or tell us if a future version is coming.","literal_zh":"这让公司有机会解释，解决一个问题，或者告诉我们未来的版本是否即将来临.","audio":"audio/0486_perrin.mp3","duration":6.734},{"id":487,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"For us, a review is a collaboration.","literal_zh":"对我们来说，审查是一种合作。","audio":"audio/0487_perrin.mp3","duration":3.734},{"id":488,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"We want to clearly communicate the value of the product and how the company is improving it.","literal_zh":"我们要明确宣传产品的价值和公司如何改进.","audio":"audio/0488_perrin.mp3","duration":5.774},{"id":489,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"One more fun question.","literal_zh":"还有一个有趣的问题。","audio":"audio/0489_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.006},{"id":490,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"If we invited you to Hong Kong to try the equipment in person, would that be something you might consider?","literal_zh":"如果我们邀请你到香港亲自去试设备 你会考虑一下吗？","audio":"audio/0490_interviewer.mp3","duration":5.726},{"id":491,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"I would need to talk to my husband about that, but I can get back to you.","literal_zh":"我需要和我的丈夫谈谈， 但我可以回到你。","audio":"audio/0491_perrin.mp3","duration":5.006},{"id":492,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"It is something we could consider.","literal_zh":"这是我们可以考虑的事情。","audio":"audio/0492_perrin.mp3","duration":2.894},{"id":493,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Thank you for all of this.","literal_zh":"谢谢你的帮助","audio":"audio/0493_interviewer.mp3","duration":2.03},{"id":494,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Seriously, your feedback has been really helpful.","literal_zh":"说真的 你的反馈很有帮助","audio":"audio/0494_interviewer.mp3","duration":3.278},{"id":495,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"I am excited about what you are creating.","literal_zh":"我为你创造的东西感到兴奋","audio":"audio/0495_perrin.mp3","duration":3.494},{"id":496,"speaker":"Perrin","section":"发布计划、展会与后续合作","english":"Feel free to reach out, and I will watch for the WhatsApp invite.","literal_zh":"随便你联系，我会看着WhatsApp的邀请。","audio":"audio/0496_perrin.mp3","duration":4.718}],"xingchen":[{"id":1,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Showroom Visit and Close-Range Teleoperation","section_zh":"一、展厅参观与近程遥操","english":"All right, let's start from the left side so the whole flow is easy to follow. The left side is our R&D area, so please don't take photos there; the right side is the showroom, and you are welcome to take pictures on that side. Next, I'll walk you through the teleoperation setup and show you a bit of what the model can do. For the model demo, I may need to check with my teammate on the exact startup steps, but this part right here is close-range teleoperation, and after I show it once, everyone can try it out.","literal_zh":"我们先从左边开始看。左边是研发区域，不允许拍照；右边是展厅区域，可以拍照。接下来我给大家展示一下技术遥操和模型能力。不过模型这一块如果要启动，我还需要问一下同事具体怎么操作。现在展示的是近程遥操，你们都可以上手试一下。","audio":null},{"id":2,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Showroom Visit and Close-Range Teleoperation","section_zh":"一、展厅参观与近程遥操","english":"You don't have to fully wear the device right now; just hang it around your neck for this part. Stand right here for a second, stay still, and now you're good to start operating.","literal_zh":"你不用把设备戴上，挂在脖子上就行。先站在这个位置，不要动，现在可以开始操作。","audio":null},{"id":3,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Showroom Visit and Close-Range Teleoperation","section_zh":"一、展厅参观与近程遥操","english":"The B button is for calibration, so that is always our first step. Did you feel the device vibrate? If not, calibration has not landed yet, so we need to do it again. Once it is calibrated, press A and the robot hand will come online, and when you need to stop, just press the stop button. If you bend forward, the robot bends forward with you, and it is much easier to feel that connection in person. Side-to-side bending is not supported in this position yet, because this joint can sway but cannot tilt like a human body. Later, with a spherical joint, we can open up more directions of motion.","literal_zh":"B 键是标定键，第一步就是标定。设备震动了吗？如果没有震动，就说明还没有标定成功。标定后按 A 键，手部就会启动。这个时候再按终止键。你往前弯腰，机器人就会跟着弯腰；但是左右方向现在还不行，因为这个位置只能晃动，不能像人一样倾斜。后续如果使用球形关节，就可以实现更多方向的动作。","audio":null},{"id":4,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Showroom Visit and Close-Range Teleoperation","section_zh":"一、展厅参观与近程遥操","english":"From a degrees-of-freedom point of view, it can get pretty close to the effect we want. The body is not really bending by itself; the motion is happening more at the end, and the nice part is that it also supports proportional control.","literal_zh":"从自由度上看，它可以达到类似效果。只是身体本身没有弯，实际弯曲的是末端。它还支持比例控制。","audio":null},{"id":5,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Showroom Visit and Close-Range Teleoperation","section_zh":"一、展厅参观与近程遥操","english":"This part is surprisingly precise, so go ahead and try inserting it here. The overall data-collection experience feels smooth, and once you try it, it is easier to understand than just watching me explain it.","literal_zh":"这个很精密。你可以把它插下去试试。整体数采体验还是比较流畅的。","audio":null},{"id":6,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Showroom Visit and Close-Range Teleoperation","section_zh":"一、展厅参观与近程遥操","english":"Everyone on our team has to pass this operation test, because once you know the posture, the workflow is very learnable. When you tap, hold it like this so the force can push back cleanly. If your hand gets loose, the device starts tilting up and down, so this posture keeps everything much steadier.","literal_zh":"这一套操作我们内部所有人都要考核，因为确实不算复杂。敲击时必须用这种姿势，力才能顶回来；如果松开，就会上下倾斜，所以这样操作会更稳。","audio":null},{"id":7,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Remote Teleoperation and Model Demo","section_zh":"二、远程遥操与模型 Demo","english":"To be honest, I still have not passed the remote teleoperation test myself, because I am not quite smooth enough with it yet. But the exciting part is that remote operation over the public internet does work. We tested Beijing to Shenzhen with latency roughly under 200 milliseconds, and later we also tested a Singapore link, which is basically ultra-long-distance teleoperation.","literal_zh":"实话说，我这个远程遥操考核一直没有通过，因为我自己还没有特别熟练。远程走公网这种方式可以做。我们测试过北京到深圳的公网链路，时延大概在两百毫秒以内；后来也测试过新加坡链路，算是超远程遥操。","audio":null},{"id":8,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Remote Teleoperation and Model Demo","section_zh":"二、远程遥操与模型 Demo","english":"The big thing with remote operation is not just getting the network to connect; it is keeping communication stable and latency under control. A public internet link can run, but that does not automatically make it production-ready. From what I understand, the current setup is more like waking the robot up remotely and letting it do slower actions. To make it truly production-grade, we still need stronger communication, steadier control, closed-loop task handling, and safety protection that you can really trust.","literal_zh":"不过，远程传输的核心问题其实还是通信稳定性和时延控制。公网链路能跑通，不代表它马上就能用于生产。我虽然没有看到完整的生产级实现，但我的理解是，它现在可能更多是把机器人启动起来，再慢慢执行一些动作。要真正达到生产级别，还需要解决通信、控制稳定性、任务闭环和安全保护等问题。","audio":null},{"id":9,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Remote Teleoperation and Model Demo","section_zh":"二、远程遥操与模型 Demo","english":"When you finish the whole operation, just press B, and then you can set the controller down.","literal_zh":"所有操作完成后，按 B 键就可以把手柄放下。","audio":null},{"id":10,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Remote Teleoperation and Model Demo","section_zh":"二、远程遥操与模型 Demo","english":"This robot is pretty tough, so don't be too nervous when you feel the feedback. Turn your wrist a little; yes, exactly like that. Now the reaction force can hold against you. Try pressing all the way down and you will feel the force feedback. Push a little harder and it will vibrate too, although the vibration comes in a bit slower. That reaction force travels through the joints and motors, and the robot body also has its own protective cover.","literal_zh":"我们机器人整体还是比较耐用的。把手腕转一下，对，这样反作用力就能顶住。你可以试着敲到底，它会有力反馈；再用力一点会震动，只是震动反馈会稍微慢一点。反作用力是通过关节和电机传递的，同时机器人本体也有防护罩。","audio":null},{"id":11,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Remote Teleoperation and Model Demo","section_zh":"二、远程遥操与模型 Demo","english":"It is actually hard to make the two hands fully touch. When they get close, you can feel this slight pull, almost like they want to snap together a little.","literal_zh":"两个手很难完全贴合在一起，靠近时会有一点吸附感。","audio":null},{"id":12,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Remote Teleoperation and Model Demo","section_zh":"二、远程遥操与模型 Demo","english":"One demo we have always wanted to build is a juggling demo, like throwing three balls at the same time. It would be such a fun model demo, but right now even manual teleoperation cannot do it cleanly yet, so doing it fully with a model is a much bigger challenge. Still, the long-term idea is exciting: if a human can do a motion, the robot has a real chance of learning it in the future.","literal_zh":"我们一直想做一个耍杂技的 demo，比如同时抛三个球。我们也想用模型做这种 demo，但现在人工遥操都还做不到，更不用说完全依靠模型。理论上，只要人能做到的动作，机器人未来大概率也能做到。","audio":null},{"id":13,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Tendon-Driven Structure and Mechanical Design","section_zh":"三、绳驱结构与机械设计","english":"Now let's switch gears and talk about production and the mechanical structure. You asked whether we have our own factories, and yes, we do: one in Wuxi and one in Bao'an.","literal_zh":"我们再说一下工厂生产和结构方案。你们问是不是自建工厂，我们在无锡有一个工厂，在宝安也有一个工厂。","audio":null},{"id":14,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Tendon-Driven Structure and Mechanical Design","section_zh":"三、绳驱结构与机械设计","english":"This structure uses tendon cables to drive the joints, so the force changes depending on the angle. For example, when the arm is held straight out, the S1 can stay level and keep working steadily. For the T1, the harder part is keeping the arm stable after it bends, and that is where the mechanical design really matters.","literal_zh":"我们这套结构是通过腱绳牵引来完成关节运动的。不同角度下，受力状态不一样。比如手臂平举时，S1 可以保持水平并稳定作业；T1 的难点在于，手臂弯曲之后还要保持稳定工作。","audio":null},{"id":15,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Tendon-Driven Structure and Mechanical Design","section_zh":"三、绳驱结构与机械设计","english":"The big win for a tendon-driven robot is that it is better for long working hours. Motor heat is a huge deal in robot design, because if the motor sits right at the joint, it keeps working whenever the arm moves, and that heat is hard to get rid of. Some designs use air cooling or liquid cooling, but that can hurt dust protection, water protection, and explosion-proof design. In real production environments, heat dissipation and protection are both a big deal.","literal_zh":"我觉得绳驱机器人的最大优势，是可以支持长时间作业。电机发热是机器人设计里的一个大问题。如果电机直接放在关节处，只要手臂运动，电机就要持续运转并发热，热量很难释放。现在很多方案会用风冷或液冷，但这样会影响整机的防尘、防水、防爆能力。对于生产环境来说，散热和防护都很关键。","audio":null},{"id":16,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Tendon-Driven Structure and Mechanical Design","section_zh":"三、绳驱结构与机械设计","english":"With a tendon-driven structure, we can keep the motors inside the body instead of putting them at the wrist or right at the joint end. That makes the end lighter, and it is friendlier for long-hour work. The tradeoff is that tendons can age, loosen, and become annoying to replace after long-term use. Also, tendon drive means you have to deal with multiple degrees of freedom, decoupling, forward kinematics, and inverse kinematics, so the control algorithm and the mechanical design both get more complicated.","literal_zh":"绳驱结构可以把电机放在身体内部，而不是放在手腕或关节末端。这样末端重量更轻，也更适合长时间工作。不过绳驱也有挑战，腱绳长期使用后会老化、松动，更换和维护也比较麻烦。另外，腱绳驱动涉及多个自由度之间的解耦和正逆解计算，控制算法和结构设计都会更复杂。","audio":null},{"id":17,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Tendon-Driven Structure and Mechanical Design","section_zh":"三、绳驱结构与机械设计","english":"Direct drive can definitely handle many tasks, and from a build perspective, it is simpler. You can work with a few factories and assemble a robot that way. But once the space is limited, balancing performance, weight, heat, and cost all at the same time gets tricky. The robot's real performance is not just about tendon drive versus direct drive. It also depends on kinematics, collision detection, interface adaptation, control delay, and how mature the whole system is.","literal_zh":"直驱方案不是不能完成任务。直驱确实更简单，找几个厂子组装一下也能做出一台机器。但要在有限空间里同时兼顾性能、重量、散热和成本，并不容易。真正影响机器人表现的，不只是绳驱还是直驱，还包括正逆解算法、碰撞检测、接口适配、控制延迟和系统整体成熟度。","audio":null},{"id":18,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Protection Modes, Load Capacity, and Safety Limits","section_zh":"四、保护模式、负载能力与安全边界","english":"This robot has built-in protection, kind of like limit protection. Once that protection is turned on, if there is a collision, the robot automatically goes into a protected state. Because this unit is here for showroom demos, we are running it in standard mode right now.","literal_zh":"这台机器人做了保护，类似限位保护。开启保护后，如果发生碰撞，机器人会自动进入保护状态。因为我是做展示用的，所以这台机器人目前使用标准模式。","audio":null},{"id":19,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Protection Modes, Load Capacity, and Safety Limits","section_zh":"四、保护模式、负载能力与安全边界","english":"Besides standard mode, there is an enhanced mode that can boost load, speed, and strength in a big way. Our R&D team told me it can reach around three times the standard mode, but I usually say at least double to keep the estimate conservative. Once the right parameters are set, the motor can run at full power.","literal_zh":"除了标准模式，还有一种增强模式，可以大幅提升负载、速度和力量。研发跟我说，最高可以提升到标准模式的三倍左右；我保守一点说，至少能提升两倍。给到相应参数后，电机就可以满功率运行。","audio":null},{"id":20,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Protection Modes, Load Capacity, and Safety Limits","section_zh":"四、保护模式、负载能力与安全边界","english":"For secondary development, you may not need those accounts at all. You can build on the standard robot-body parameters we provide, and if you stay within those standard parameters, you are totally fine. If a customer wants to push the robot closer to its limit, we can support that too, but the warranty needs a separate conversation. The reason is simple: the motors and related parts will be running much closer to full load, with much higher speed and force.","literal_zh":"如果是二次开发，实际上可能用不到这些账号。所有操作都可以基于我们提供的机器人本体参数标准来做，按照标准参数开发是完全没问题的。如果客户想追求极限性能，我们也可以支持，但质保需要另行约定，因为电机等部件会更接近满负荷运行，速度和力量都会明显提高。","audio":null},{"id":21,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Protection Modes, Load Capacity, and Safety Limits","section_zh":"四、保护模式、负载能力与安全边界","english":"The robot itself is strong, so when I operate it, using both hands together usually feels more natural. Our internal tests also have time targets; for example, the desktop cleaning task has to be finished within nineteen seconds. The showroom robots are mainly for customer demos, and the S1 is basically our flagship. When it reaches a limit position, motions like wrist rotation and arm extension are restricted by protection, and those protections really do work.","literal_zh":"机器人本身力气也很大。我之前用两只手配合操作，会更合适一些。内部考核也有时间要求，比如桌面清扫要在十九秒内完成。展厅里的机器人主要用于客户演示。S1 算是我们的旗舰机型。到达极限位置时，手腕、胳膊伸展等动作都会受到保护限制，这些保护是有效的。","audio":null},{"id":22,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Protection Modes, Load Capacity, and Safety Limits","section_zh":"四、保护模式、负载能力与安全边界","english":"My control setup is pretty easy to understand. The left joystick controls forward, backward, left, and right movement, and the right joystick controls the angle. There is also a mode where the robot follows a person, and so far, I have not run into any major issues with it.","literal_zh":"我的操作方式是：左边摇杆控制前后左右，右边摇杆控制角度。还有一个国内就是让机器人跟人一起走。目前我还没有遇到特别大的问题。","audio":null},{"id":23,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Protection Modes, Load Capacity, and Safety Limits","section_zh":"四、保护模式、负载能力与安全边界","english":"We can also use an electronic scale right here to show the load capacity, which makes the number feel much more real. When we say the T1 can carry about five kilograms, we mean it can still work steadily with the arm fully extended. Of course, the actual performance still depends on posture, speed, the end effector, and the task you are asking it to do.","literal_zh":"现场也可以通过电子秤做负载演示。我们说 T1 最大负载约五公斤，是指在手臂伸直的情况下依然能稳定作业。当然，具体表现还会受姿态、速度、末端执行器和任务类型影响。","audio":null},{"id":24,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Factory Production, Data Collection, and Aging Tests","section_zh":"五、工厂生产、数采与老化测试","english":"For production, R&D, data collection, and aging tests, we use dedicated robots. It is not like the structure team grabs one robot today and the electronics team borrows the exact same one tomorrow. Each type of work has its own relatively fixed machines, so the usage is much cleaner and easier to track.","literal_zh":"我们在生产、研发、数采、老化测试等环节都有固定设备。不会说结构工程师用一台，做板子的同事又把同一台借走。每类任务都有相对固定的机器人。","audio":null},{"id":25,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Factory Production, Data Collection, and Aging Tests","section_zh":"五、工厂生产、数采与老化测试","english":"The data-collection robots work hard, like seriously hard. Our data-collection team runs in three shifts, so one robot can be used continuously by three different operators. Based on the data from this April, some individual robots had already logged around 5,500 working hours, and by now that number should be even higher. Some units have already passed 6,000 hours.","literal_zh":"数采设备的使用强度比较高。我们有数采团队采用三班倒模式，一台机器人对应三名操作人员，持续用于数据采集。按今年四月份的数据，部分单台机器人累计工作时长大概是五千五百小时，现在应该更多。也有单机累计运行超过六千小时的情况。","audio":null},{"id":26,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Factory Production, Data Collection, and Aging Tests","section_zh":"五、工厂生产、数采与老化测试","english":"For aging tests, we have looked at what happens to the tendons after long-term use. The tendons do loosen over time, but we have units that only started losing accuracy after three years and three months of continuous use, and even then, the overall structure was still usable. Some units did not show obvious quality issues until around six years. So yes, tendons are long-term wear parts, but they can be reinforced or replaced during maintenance.","literal_zh":"老化测试方面，我们确实测过腱绳长期使用后的情况。腱绳在长期使用后会出现一定松动。我们有设备连续使用三年三个月后，精度才开始下降，但整体结构仍然可用。也有设备到六年后才出现明显质量问题。腱绳属于长期使用后会受影响的部件，后续可以通过加固或更换维护。","audio":null},{"id":27,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Factory Production, Data Collection, and Aging Tests","section_zh":"五、工厂生产、数采与老化测试","english":"I also asked what kinds of issues have appeared during delivery. For factory yield, if you build ten robots, a hundred robots, or a thousand robots, it is not realistic to expect every single unit to be perfect. Some small bugs or minor issues may leave the factory, and if they are not caught during post-production checks, they show up after delivery. Most other delivery issues are smaller after-sales items, usually around algorithm adaptation or port matching. So far, we have not had large-scale motor replacement or large-scale tendon replacement.","literal_zh":"我也问过交付过程中出现过哪些问题。比如工厂良品率方面，生产十台、一百台、一千台机器人，不可能每一台都完全没有问题。出厂时可能会有一些 bug 或小问题，如果生产后没有检测出来，就会在交付后暴露。其他交付问题多半是算法、端口适配等售后小问题。到目前为止，电机没有大规模更换过，腱绳也没有大规模更换过。","audio":null},{"id":28,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Factory Production, Data Collection, and Aging Tests","section_zh":"五、工厂生产、数采与老化测试","english":"The key parts can all be taken apart. This unit may be an early prototype used for debugging and positioning, so those markings are not random. During production, we add marks like this in many places to prevent assembly mistakes. Why would screws need to be replaced? Because vibration can make them shift. If the tendon or wiring is not aligned during inspection, that can turn into a problem later.","literal_zh":"关键部件都可以拆。这个可能是早期生产的样机，用来调试和定位。生产时为了做防呆定位，很多位置都会有类似标记。螺丝为什么要换？因为在震动过程中可能会偏移。如果检查时发现腱绳或线路对不准，就可能出现问题。","audio":null},{"id":29,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Product Versions, Pricing, and Delivery Schedule","section_zh":"六、产品版本、价格与交付排期","english":"Right now, the two main series worth focusing on are the S1 and the T1.","literal_zh":"现在主要聊 S1 和 T1 两个系列。","audio":null},{"id":30,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Product Versions, Pricing, and Delivery Schedule","section_zh":"六、产品版本、价格与交付排期","english":"The S1 is our flagship series, so it has stronger performance and a higher-end configuration, but of course the cost is higher too. We had a small amount of retail inventory before, and if you had come a few days earlier, you might still have been able to grab one. At the moment, we are focusing our production capacity, so small-batch S1 retail is not the top priority. If you have a clear batch demand later, we can absolutely keep talking about the S1.","literal_zh":"S1 是我们的旗舰系列，性能和配置更高，但成本也更高。之前还有少量零售库存，如果你们早几天来，可能还能买到。现在我们更倾向于集中产能，不太优先支持 S1 的小批量零售。如果后面你们有明确的批量需求，S1 也可以继续沟通。","audio":null},{"id":31,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Product Versions, Pricing, and Delivery Schedule","section_zh":"六、产品版本、价格与交付排期","english":"The T1 is the mass-production product we are pushing the hardest right now. It actually came out last October, and batch delivery started this year. Because it is more affordable than the S1, demand has been really strong, so the delivery schedule is tight. If you place an order now, delivery may land around late August or early September. If it is truly urgent, I can try to coordinate internally and see whether one unit from a batch order can go to you first, but I cannot fully promise that.","literal_zh":"T1 是现在重点推进的量产产品。T1 其实去年十月就已经出来了，今年开始批量交付。因为价格相对 S1 更低，客户需求比较多，所以目前排期比较紧。如果现在下单，可能要排到八月底或九月初才能交付。如果确实紧急，我们可以尝试和同事协调，看批量订单里有没有机器能先交给你们，但这个不能完全保证。","audio":null},{"id":32,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Product Versions, Pricing, and Delivery Schedule","section_zh":"六、产品版本、价格与交付排期","english":"For pricing, we have several versions. The half-body version is around RMB 89,900, and it is mainly for lighter desktop scenarios, like vending or popcorn demos, but it does not include full interfaces. The basic full-body version is around RMB 149,900, and that usually includes one robot and one remote controller, but no secondary development and no API access. The T1 secondary-development version is around RMB 315,270 including tax, and if we go by the public single-unit retail price, it may be higher.","literal_zh":"关于价格，现场有几个版本。半身版大概是 8.99 万元，主要适合桌面售卖、爆米花这类轻量场景，不含完整接口。基础全身版大概 14.99 万元，通常是一台机器人加一个遥控手柄，不含二开能力，也没有 API 接口。T1 二开版含税价格大概是 31.527 万元。如果按公开零售单台口径，价格可能更高。","audio":null},{"id":33,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Product Versions, Pricing, and Delivery Schedule","section_zh":"六、产品版本、价格与交付排期","english":"The exact price depends on the configuration, so this is where we need to match the setup to your real use case. Options like the universal adapter board, automatic charging station, extra computing power, upgraded vision, and depth cameras will all change the final number. If you can first clarify your budget and requirements, I can help you put together a configuration that actually makes sense. The final price can be discussed, but only if you are seriously planning to buy. Feature access and interfaces are all negotiable.","literal_zh":"具体价格还是要看配置。比如万能转接板、自动充电站、额外算力、高配视觉、深度相机等选项，都会影响最终价格。你们要先明确预算和需求，我再帮你们做配置搭配。最终价格可以谈，但前提是你们确实要买。功能开放和接口这些都好谈。","audio":null},{"id":34,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Product Versions, Pricing, and Delivery Schedule","section_zh":"六、产品版本、价格与交付排期","english":"The T1 is really popular right now. Today I can say August delivery might still be possible, but tomorrow I may not be able to say the same thing because we have our weekly meeting on Monday. Right now, the deposit is only RMB 10,000, and I also need to coordinate with the model team. Honestly, for a robot in the two-hundred-thousand-yuan range, the value is pretty solid.","literal_zh":"T1 现在确实很抢手。我今天可以说八月份有可能出货，但明天可能就不能保证，因为周一要开周会。现在只需要一万块钱定金。我还要和模型团队沟通。实话说，一台机器人二十来万，这个价格确实还算划算。","audio":null},{"id":35,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Compute, Vision, Battery, and Interface Configuration","section_zh":"七、算力、视觉、电池与接口配置","english":"The robot uses body-side edge computing plus host-machine computing. The S1 uses Orange Pi, and the T1 mainly uses RK3588. Think of the edge computer as the robot's input-output and relay hub: it handles images, sensors, control commands, data access, and forwarding, and it also does some local computing. For heavier model inference, you can run that on the host machine or on external computing hardware.","literal_zh":"机器人采用的是“本体边缘计算 + 上位机算力”的架构。S1 用的是 Orange Pi，T1 主要用 RK3588。边缘计算平台更像输入输出和中继节点，负责图像、传感器、控制指令等数据的接入和转发，也承担部分本地计算。更重的模型推理，可以放在上位机或外部算力设备上。","audio":null},{"id":36,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Compute, Vision, Battery, and Interface Configuration","section_zh":"七、算力、视觉、电池与接口配置","english":"Inside the company, we talk about the model capability as something like a big brain and a small brain. The small brain is closer to the execution layer: routine task reasoning, action assignment, and safety control. The big brain is more about complex task planning and higher-level decisions. If you buy our robot now, the small-brain system comes with it.","literal_zh":"我们内部把模型能力分成类似“大脑”和“小脑”的层级。“小脑”更偏执行层，负责常规任务的推理、动作分配和安全控制；“大脑”更偏复杂任务规划和高层决策。现在买我们的机器人，会一起交付小脑系统。","audio":null},{"id":37,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Compute, Vision, Battery, and Interface Configuration","section_zh":"七、算力、视觉、电池与接口配置","english":"For vision, the T1 is slightly reduced compared with the S1. For example, the head camera and chest camera setups are different. Depth cameras, head vision, and automatic charging stations can all be selected based on what the customer needs. If you already have your own computing platform, you can choose a lower-compute version and connect your own high-performance GPU or external computing device.","literal_zh":"视觉配置方面，T1 相比 S1 有一定减配，比如头部摄像头和胸部摄像头配置不一样。深度相机、头部视觉、自动充电站等模块可以按客户需求选配。如果你们有自己的算力平台，也可以选择低配算力版本，再自己接高性能显卡或外部计算设备。","audio":null},{"id":38,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Compute, Vision, Battery, and Interface Configuration","section_zh":"七、算力、视觉、电池与接口配置","english":"For battery life, the S1 is rated at about five to six hours, and the T1 is rated at about two to three hours. The T1 supports battery replacement, which gives you more flexibility during longer sessions. Actual battery life will still depend on load, task intensity, and the exact configuration.","literal_zh":"电池方面，S1 标称续航大概五到六小时，T1 标称续航大概两到三小时。T1 支持更换电池。实际续航会受负载、任务强度和具体配置影响。","audio":null},{"id":39,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Compute, Vision, Battery, and Interface Configuration","section_zh":"七、算力、视觉、电池与接口配置","english":"The T1 can be configured with a universal adapter board, which is basically what lets it connect to different hands, grippers, navigation peripherals, and other external devices. The T1 and S1 are similar in hollow wiring, force drive, and transmission structure, but the T1 reduces arm length, body structure, and some configurations. That keeps the cost under control and makes it much better suited for mass production.","literal_zh":"T1 可以配置万能转接板，用来对接灵巧手、夹爪、导航外设等不同末端或外设。T1 和 S1 在中空走线、力的驱动和传输结构上有相似之处，但 T1 在手臂长度、构型和部分配置上做了缩减，这样可以控制成本，也更适合量产。","audio":null},{"id":40,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Compute, Vision, Battery, and Interface Configuration","section_zh":"七、算力、视觉、电池与接口配置","english":"The T1 currently supports secondary development, and the secondary-development version opens API access. If you want to build a production line, whether for data collection or actual production, you will need drivers and control programs on the RK3588. You also need a stable control link between the robot body and the host machine, because that link is what keeps the whole workflow reliable.","literal_zh":"目前 T1 支持二次开发，二开版会开放 API 接口。你们如果要装一条产线，无论是做数采还是实际生产，都需要在 RK3588 上做驱动和控制程序，也需要在机器人本体和上位机之间建立稳定的控制链路。","audio":null},{"id":41,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Operating System and Secondary Development","section_zh":"八、操作系统与二次开发","english":"If you want to build a robot operating system, I actually think that fits really well with our underlying logic. In the future, robots may work more like computers or phones: hardware body first, then an operating system, and then an app ecosystem on top. When users need a function, they download the matching app. For example, a cooking app could let the robot handle certain cooking tasks, and a navigation or shopping app could help it take on more complex outside tasks.","literal_zh":"你们如果想做机器人操作系统，我觉得和我们的底层逻辑是比较一致的。未来机器人可能会像电脑或手机一样，形成“硬件本体 + 操作系统 + 应用生态”的模式。用户需要什么功能，就下载对应应用。比如下载炒菜应用，机器人就能完成某类烹饪任务；下载导航或采购应用，机器人就可以执行更复杂的外部任务。","audio":null},{"id":42,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Operating System and Secondary Development","section_zh":"八、操作系统与二次开发","english":"I think ROS1 and ROS2 are great for R&D and low-level development, but they are not the final user experience for everyday people. A consumer-facing robot system should feel much simpler, more like using phone apps. Users should not have to understand the underlying technology; they should just pick what they want the robot to do, and the system should handle the rest.","literal_zh":"我觉得 ROS1 和 ROS2 更适合作为研发和底层开发框架，不是真正面向大众用户的最终产品形态。面向 C 端用户的系统应该更简单，就像手机应用一样，用户不需要理解底层技术，只需要选择功能。","audio":null},{"id":43,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Operating System and Secondary Development","section_zh":"八、操作系统与二次开发","english":"The T1 system architecture has some compatibility. If you need ROS2, we can help flash it in or do the adaptation work. Right now, the T1 uses Xingchen's own operating system, and my understanding is that it is packaged and improved on top of a ROS-like base. The system can keep evolving into V2, V3, and beyond.","literal_zh":"T1 的系统架构有一定兼容性。如果你们需要 ROS2，我们可以协助刷进去或做适配。现在 T1 用的是星尘自己的操作系统，我理解它是在 ROS 类底座上做了进一步封装和改良。后续系统也可以继续迭代到 V2、V3。","audio":null},{"id":44,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Operating System and Secondary Development","section_zh":"八、操作系统与二次开发","english":"In the future, robots will definitely call different capabilities based on user instructions. The computing demand is huge, and it is not realistic for every home to have its own server sitting there. So future robots may need remote computing support. Computing power may be charged, and different apps may be charged too. Whether that becomes a monthly subscription or a one-time purchase depends on how the whole app ecosystem is designed.","literal_zh":"机器人以后一定会根据指令调用不同能力。因为算力需求很大，每个家庭不可能都配一台服务器，所以未来可能需要远程算力支撑。算力会收费，各种应用也会收费。具体是按月收费，还是一次性购买，要看整个 App 生态怎么设计。","audio":null},{"id":45,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Operating System and Secondary Development","section_zh":"八、操作系统与二次开发","english":"Right now, we still do not have enough data; in a year, we may only collect around 50,000 hours. But once a lot of robots are collecting data at the same time, the scale will eventually get there. It could be 100 million hours, or even 1 billion hours.","literal_zh":"现在数据还不够，一年也只有五万个小时。但以后可以通过大量机器人采集，数据总会达到相应量级，无论是一亿小时还是十亿小时。","audio":null},{"id":46,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"End Effectors and Application Scenarios","section_zh":"九、末端执行器与应用场景","english":"In industrial scenarios, grippers can already cover a lot of tasks. But in the long run, end effectors will probably move more toward dexterous hands, because dexterous hands are much closer to human hands and are better for complex, general-purpose tasks.","literal_zh":"工业场景中，夹爪可以覆盖很多任务。但从长期看，机器人末端形态可能还是会逐渐向灵巧手收敛，因为灵巧手更接近人手，适合更复杂、更泛化的任务。","audio":null},{"id":47,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"End Effectors and Application Scenarios","section_zh":"九、末端执行器与应用场景","english":"That said, dexterous hands also have durability challenges. If customers run them at high intensity for a long time, they wear faster, so dexterous-hand manufacturers still need to keep improving that part. Right now, we have high-degree-of-freedom solutions with twenty degrees of freedom, and we also have simpler options like six-degree-of-freedom hands.","literal_zh":"不过，灵巧手也有耐久性问题。如果客户让灵巧手长期高强度工作，磨损会比较快，这部分需要灵巧手厂家继续提升。我们现在有二十自由度的高自由度方案，也有六自由度这类更简化的方案。","audio":null},{"id":48,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"End Effectors and Application Scenarios","section_zh":"九、末端执行器与应用场景","english":"For force control, the robot is not just doing open and close like a simple clamp. It can control how much force it applies. For example, when it holds a glass cup, the software can limit the maximum force so the robot does not crush it. That kind of control is very important for desktop tasks, retail, food service, and service scenarios.","literal_zh":"力控方面，机器人不是只有“开”和“合”两种状态，而是可以控制夹持力度。比如夹玻璃杯时，可以通过软件限制最大力，避免夹碎物体。这类能力对于桌面操作、零售、餐饮和服务场景都很重要。","audio":null},{"id":49,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"End Effectors and Application Scenarios","section_zh":"九、末端执行器与应用场景","english":"The scenarios we work with most include homes, commercial displays, culture and tourism, retail, and some industrial applications. Home and commercial scenarios show up more often, while industrial scenarios are fewer because they almost always need adaptation. Every factory has its own production lines, tooling, and workflow, so you cannot just copy and paste one solution everywhere.","literal_zh":"目前我们接触和落地比较多的场景，包括家庭、商业展示、文旅、零售和部分工业应用。家庭和商业场景相对更多，工业场景会少一些，因为工业场景都需要适配。不同工厂的产线、工装和流程差异很大，不能简单复制。","audio":null},{"id":50,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"End Effectors and Application Scenarios","section_zh":"九、末端执行器与应用场景","english":"In industrial scenarios, customers may need custom fixtures, tooling, or even a full end-to-end workflow. Even for the same type of factory, the process may differ by region or by production line. So robot applications usually need to be adapted around the exact step where the robot will be used.","literal_zh":"工业场景里，客户可能需要定制夹具、工装或端到端流程。即使是同一类工厂，不同地区或不同产线的工艺流程也可能不同，所以机器人应用往往要按具体环节重新适配。","audio":null},{"id":51,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"End Effectors and Application Scenarios","section_zh":"九、末端执行器与应用场景","english":"We already have customers using the robots in real production, including Xianfeng Lingyu and Jinma Rides. We have a data-collection factory in Guizhou and another one in Ma'anshan, and there are also more than one hundred units in Linyi. We also cooperate with Pai on large models. I do not know the exact details, but I do know the cooperation is real.","literal_zh":"我们目前已经实际应用到生产里的客户，包括先锋领域、金马游乐等。贵州有一个数采厂，马鞍山也有一个数采厂。临沂那边也有一百多台。我们和“派”在大模型方面有合作，但具体合作内容我不太清楚，只知道确实有合作。","audio":null},{"id":52,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"End Effectors and Application Scenarios","section_zh":"九、末端执行器与应用场景","english":"Culture, tourism, and display scenarios also have demand. Some customers buy robots for clubs, showrooms, or stage displays, and they use remote control to create interactive movements. These customers may not need the full secondary-development package; they care more about the look, the interaction, and whether the demo feels impressive in person.","literal_zh":"文旅和展示场景也有需求。有些客户买机器人就是用来做会所、展厅或舞台展示，通过遥控完成互动动作。这类客户不一定需要完整二开能力，更看重外观、互动和演示效果。","audio":null},{"id":53,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"After-Sales, Certifications, and Overseas Compliance","section_zh":"十、售后、认证与海外合规","english":"For after-sales service, if the robot breaks, it can be shipped back for repair. If it is still under warranty, we cover the related shipping costs, and the warranty period is one year. Honestly, after-sales agreements are pretty similar across companies, but shipping a robot this size back and forth is definitely inconvenient. So for some issues, we can also send people on site, depending on what kind of problem it is.","literal_zh":"售后方面，如果机器人坏了，可以寄回来维修。如果在保修期内，我们承担相关运费，保修期是一年。售后协议其实各家都差不多。不过这么大一台机器来回寄确实麻烦，所以有些问题我们也可以派人到现场处理，具体要看问题类型。","audio":null},{"id":54,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"After-Sales, Certifications, and Overseas Compliance","section_zh":"十、售后、认证与海外合规","english":"Many after-sales issues can be solved through online guidance, especially configuration, interface, or operation problems. For customers in other cities, whether we ask them to ship the robot back or send someone on site depends on how complex the issue is.","literal_zh":"很多售后问题可以通过线上指导解决，比如配置、接口或操作问题。对于异地客户，到底是寄修还是上门，要看问题复杂度。","audio":null},{"id":55,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"After-Sales, Certifications, and Overseas Compliance","section_zh":"十、售后、认证与海外合规","english":"For overseas markets, we have not fully built out an overseas after-sales system yet. A French customer previously bought an S1 to replace part of a production process in his factory. We delivered the robot in China, and then he arranged his own freight forwarder to ship it overseas. Because overseas certification and compliance are not fully completed yet, overseas pricing and delivery methods will be different from domestic ones.","literal_zh":"海外方面，我们目前还没有完全建立海外售后体系。之前有一个法国客户买了一台 S1，用来替代工厂里的部分生产环节。他是在国内交货，然后自己找货代运出去。因为海外认证和合规流程还没有完全完成，所以海外售价和交付方式会和国内不同。","audio":null},{"id":56,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"After-Sales, Certifications, and Overseas Compliance","section_zh":"十、售后、认证与海外合规","english":"For certifications, the full robot has not completed explosion-proof, dust-proof, or water-proof certification yet. For key components like batteries, we require compliance certificates when purchasing them, but that does not mean the whole robot has completed every industrial certification. So if the robot is going into factories, chemical sites, outdoor environments, or other high-protection scenarios, we need to confirm the certification requirements case by case.","literal_zh":"认证方面，目前整机还没有完成防爆、防尘、防水认证。电池等关键部件采购时会要求合格证明，但这不等于整机已经完成全部工业认证。所以如果进入工厂、化工、户外或高防护等级场景，还需要进一步确认认证要求。","audio":null},{"id":57,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"After-Sales, Certifications, and Overseas Compliance","section_zh":"十、售后、认证与海外合规","english":"Overseas data compliance is actually a lot like phones going global. The key issues are privacy and data compliance. Directly exporting domestic data to Europe or the U.S. can create compliance risk, but trained skills, model capabilities, or app capabilities can still be exported in a compliant way.","literal_zh":"出海的数据合规问题，和手机出海很像。核心问题是隐私和数据合规。国内数据直接出口到欧美地区会有合规风险，但已经训练好的技能、模型能力或应用能力，可以通过合规方式输出。","audio":null},{"id":58,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"After-Sales, Certifications, and Overseas Compliance","section_zh":"十、售后、认证与海外合规","english":"For example, if I buy a robot and send it to the U.S. to cook three dishes, what I really need is not the raw data; what I need is the trained skill. The premise is that the robot's generalization and autonomy are already good enough to use, so it does not need to collect a huge amount of extra data. Of course, by that stage, the robot may still collect some data, but it can be processed locally through U.S. servers or U.S.-based cloud services. Phones work in a similar way, and Apple's data center in Guizhou was also about meeting compliance requirements.","literal_zh":"比如我买了一台机器人，让它去美国炒三道菜，我需要的不是原始数据，而是已经训练好的技能。这里的前提是，机器人的泛化能力和自主能力已经达到可用程度，不需要再额外收集大量数据。当然，到那个阶段，机器人可能仍然会收集一部分数据，但可以在美国部署服务器或购买云服务，在美国本地处理。手机也是类似逻辑，苹果在贵州设数据中心，也是为了解决合规问题。","audio":null},{"id":59,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Future Cooperation and Shenzhen Supply-Chain Advantage","section_zh":"十一、后续合作与深圳供应链优势","english":"If you want to build a robot operating system or a robot app ecosystem in the future, our robot could be one of the hardware bases. That direction actually matches our thinking pretty well: hardware body, operating system, and app ecosystem.","literal_zh":"如果你们未来想做机器人操作系统或机器人应用生态，我觉得我们家的机器人可以作为硬件底座之一。我们在“硬件本体 + 操作系统 + 应用生态”这个方向上的思路比较接近。","audio":null},{"id":60,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Future Cooperation and Shenzhen Supply-Chain Advantage","section_zh":"十一、后续合作与深圳供应链优势","english":"In the short term, if you only buy one or two robots, it probably will not pull in a lot of R&D resources from our company. But if we confirm product fit and define a clearer cooperation direction, I can help push things forward internally. That means bringing in our R&D team, model team, and after-sales team so we can have a deeper conversation with you.","literal_zh":"短期内，如果你们只采购一两台机器人，可能不会撬动公司太多研发资源。但如果确认产品适配，并且形成更明确的合作方向，我可以推动公司研发、模型、售后等团队和你们做更深入的交流。","audio":null},{"id":61,"speaker":"Xingchen","section":"Future Cooperation and Shenzhen Supply-Chain Advantage","section_zh":"十一、后续合作与深圳供应链优势","english":"I think your team will probably set up a team in Shenzhen later, and the reason is simple. Shenzhen has lower manufacturing costs and an incredibly dense supply chain. Within a ten-kilometer radius, you can source a huge share of the parts needed to build a robot, and that is hard for Shanghai, Hangzhou, or Beijing to match. For robot hardware development and fast iteration, Shenzhen is just a better place to get things built quickly.","literal_zh":"我觉得你们团队后面大概率也会在深圳成立团队。原因很简单：深圳制造成本低，供应链密度高。方圆十公里内，做一台机器人所需的大量零部件基本都能配齐。上海、杭州、北京很难做到这一点。对于机器人硬件开发和快速迭代来说，深圳的供应链环境更适合落地。","audio":null}],"mark":[{"id":1,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Thanks for joining us. We'd love to learn more about you. Could you start by telling us a bit about yourself?","literal_zh":"感谢你参加这次访谈。我们想多了解一下你。你可以先简单介绍一下自己吗？","audio":null},{"id":2,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Sure. Ask me anything you want.","literal_zh":"当然。你们想问什么都可以。","audio":null},{"id":3,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Let's start with your training background. And I realize I should ask first: what's your name?","literal_zh":"我们先从你的训练背景聊起。另外我刚意识到应该先问一下：你叫什么名字？","audio":null},{"id":4,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Oh yeah, sure. Let's see. I trained when I was a youngster at Joe Frazier's Boxing Gym in Philadelphia. I grew up in New Jersey. I'm 55 years old, by the way. I'm retired military, and I'm retired law enforcement. I retired from the Navy in 2015, and then I worked for ten years after that — from 2015 to 2025 — with the Brevard County Sheriff's Office down here.","literal_zh":"哦，对，当然。让我想想。我年轻的时候在费城的 Joe Frazier 拳馆训练过。我是在新泽西长大的。顺便说一下，我今年 55 岁。我是退役军人，也从执法系统退休了。我 2015 年从海军退役，之后又在这边的布里瓦德县警长办公室工作了十年，从 2015 年到 2025 年。","audio":null},{"id":5,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"I was classically trained as a boxer. I did box and I did compete a little bit as a youngster, but my dad didn't want me to pursue a career in boxing, so he kind of started steering me away from it and more towards other sports.","literal_zh":"我接受过传统拳击训练。年轻的时候我确实打过拳，也参加过一些比赛，但我父亲不希望我走职业拳击这条路，所以他慢慢把我从拳击引开，让我更多去参加其他运动。","audio":null},{"id":6,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"But boxing — it's always been something that just… it really… I love boxing because it combines cardiovascular work, muscle work, short anaerobic training as well as aerobic training. You have to have wind, you have to have stamina, you have to have strength. Any form of boxing training can create a total physique.","literal_zh":"但拳击一直都是一种……它真的……我喜欢拳击，因为它结合了心肺训练、肌肉训练、短时间无氧训练和有氧训练。你必须有气息、有耐力、有力量。任何形式的拳击训练都能塑造一个全面的身体素质。","audio":null},{"id":7,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Throughout my career, I was a Navy Rescue Swimmer and a helicopter crew chief. Then when the war started, I worked with the Counter-IED Task Force. I was assigned to the Army and worked with them in Afghanistan and Iraq — helping on the road, making sure people didn't blow up, all that kind of stuff.","literal_zh":"在我的职业生涯里，我曾经是海军救援游泳员，也是直升机机组长。后来战争开始后，我加入了反简易爆炸装置特遣队。我被派到陆军那边，和他们一起在阿富汗和伊拉克工作，在路线上提供支援，确保人员不会被炸到，诸如此类的事情。","audio":null},{"id":8,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"In that time, when I was a rescue swimmer instructor, we would talk to people about getting in shape for rescue swimmer school — it was the third toughest training in the Navy. We would talk about boxing, and we would talk about finding a boxing gym, things like that.","literal_zh":"那段时间里，当我担任救援游泳员教官时，我们会跟别人聊如何为救援游泳员学校做好体能准备——那是海军里第三艰苦的训练。我们会聊拳击，也会聊怎么找拳馆之类的事情。","audio":null},{"id":9,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"The only problem that I've ever seen with boxing is, if you don't belong to a gym, it's very hard to train on your own. You can train on your own, but mitt work and counterpunching and all those fun things that you want to improve upon — it can get a little tedious, hitting the bag all the time.","literal_zh":"我一直觉得拳击唯一的问题是，如果你不属于某个拳馆，自己训练会很难。你可以自己训练，但手靶训练、反击训练，以及那些你真正想提升的有意思的东西，如果只能一直打沙袋，就会变得有点枯燥。","audio":null},{"id":10,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"So one of the things that I've done in my retirement is I joined FightCamp. I use that program — it's kind of interactive, and I really think that is a great program. I wish FightCamp and Peloton would kind of combine forces, because the idea of Peloton where you can go to classes and you can interact and train with instructors, but physically from your house — that's a great idea.","literal_zh":"所以我退休后做的一件事就是加入 FightCamp。我在用那个项目，它有一定互动性，我真的觉得那是个很棒的项目。我希望 FightCamp 和 Peloton 能某种程度上结合起来，因为 Peloton 的理念是你可以上课，可以互动，可以跟教练训练，但身体上是在自己家里完成，这个想法非常好。","audio":null},{"id":11,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"FightCamp did a really great job of creating a Facebook community. You can compare your results, you can kind of compete with other people, you can compete with the averages, and you can measure your progress. I think measuring progress is very important to people in this generation, because they want to be able to see via data what they're doing. You don't always see it physically right off the bat, but if you're starting to see that you're doing really well or that you're improving, it's really important.","literal_zh":"FightCamp 在建立 Facebook 社群方面做得很好。你可以比较自己的成绩，可以和别人有点竞争，也可以和平均水平竞争，还能衡量自己的进步。我觉得对这一代人来说，衡量进步非常重要，因为他们希望通过数据看到自己在做什么。身体上的变化不一定马上能看出来，但如果你开始看到自己表现很好，或者看到自己正在进步，那就非常重要。","audio":null},{"id":12,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"FightCamp really created a great community, and they found really great instructors to work with you and to do these training videos. They have a program that takes people from \"never picked up a pair of boxing gloves in their life\" to being able to throw multi-punch combinations and things like that.","literal_zh":"FightCamp 确实建立了一个很棒的社群，而且找到了非常优秀的教练来带你训练、录制这些训练视频。他们有一套课程，可以把一个“一辈子都没拿过拳套”的人，带到能够打出多拳组合之类的水平。","audio":null},{"id":13,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"But again, one of the downsides is counterpunching and mitt work — those are a bit challenging. You have to find different pieces of equipment to do those things.","literal_zh":"但还是一样，其中一个缺点就是反击训练和手靶训练，这些比较难。你必须找不同的设备来做这些事情。","audio":null},{"id":14,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Regarding pricing — the monthly membership is a little more than I like to spend, but at the same time I consider it to be a good value.","literal_zh":"关于价格，月费比我愿意花的稍微高一点，但同时我也认为它物有所值。","audio":null},{"id":15,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"The other thing I did was I bought the Nexersys system — the interactive system with the computer screen. I call it the \"Fight Bot.\" I don't know if you've ever seen one of those.","literal_zh":"我做的另一件事是买了 Nexersys 系统，就是带电脑屏幕的互动系统。我叫它“Fight Bot”。不知道你们有没有见过那种东西。","audio":null},{"id":16,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Wait, could we see it right now?","literal_zh":"等一下，我们现在可以看一下吗？","audio":null},{"id":17,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"It's in the garage. You'll have to excuse the mess, I've been working on my car and stuff. (shows the machine) That's the Nexersys machine. It's very interactive, very, very cool, because it provides data as well as that interactive element. One of the things they did was kind of create a sparring sequence where you're ducking — and the computer screen is far enough away so you don't have to worry about hitting it — but at the same time you can kind of use that virtual sparring partner to work and do that kind of thing.","literal_zh":"它在车库里。你们得原谅一下有点乱，我最近一直在修车之类的。(展示机器) 这就是 Nexersys 机器。它互动性很强，非常非常酷，因为它既提供数据，也提供互动元素。他们做的一件事是设计了一种类似实战对练的序列，你需要下潜躲闪——电脑屏幕离得够远，所以你不用担心打到屏幕——但同时你又可以把那个虚拟陪练当作对手来训练，做那类动作。","audio":null},{"id":18,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"That machine looks really interesting. Do you have a manual or any information about it? I'm curious how it works.","literal_zh":"那台机器看起来很有意思。你有说明书或相关资料吗？我很好奇它是怎么工作的。","audio":null},{"id":19,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Oh, sure. It's by a company called Nexersys. I can send you all the information. I don't have the instruction manual handy, but what I can do is, later on this week when I'm doing a workout, I can shoot a video and then I can email it to you.","literal_zh":"哦，当然。它是一家叫 Nexersys 的公司做的。我可以把所有信息发给你们。我手边没有说明书，但我可以这样做：这周晚些时候我训练的时候，拍一段视频，然后发邮件给你们。","audio":null},{"id":20,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"That would be amazing. Honestly, it looks a little like our JabX, almost like a related product.","literal_zh":"那太好了。说实话，它看起来有点像我们的 JabX，像是相关类型的产品。","audio":null},{"id":21,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"It's a similar product, but it's by a company called Nexersys. Generally speaking, you don't find those in people's homes very often. I'm just ridiculously silly about things — if I want it, I don't want to have to go to a gym to use it. I'm a home gym kind of guy. A lot of that is just because when you're in the military, you spend so much time training with other people that you just want to train by yourself. You don't want to do group PT, you don't want to do that kind of thing. Although I do see the advantages of going to a gym, I prefer to train at home, because my gym is ten feet that way — I just go outside and go to work.","literal_zh":"它是类似的产品，但来自一家叫 Nexersys 的公司。一般来说，你不太会在普通人家里看到这种东西。我对这些东西就是有点离谱地执着——如果我想用它，我就不想为了用它还得去健身房。我是那种家庭健身房型的人。很大一部分原因是，当你在军队里时，你花了太多时间和别人一起训练，所以你会只想自己训练。你不想做集体体能训练，不想搞那种东西。虽然我确实看得到去健身房的好处，但我更喜欢在家训练，因为我的健身房就在那边十英尺外——我直接出去就能开练。","audio":null},{"id":22,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"Since you brought up FightCamp, I have to ask: roughly how much did that whole setup cost?","literal_zh":"既然你提到了 FightCamp，我想问一下：整套设备大概花了多少钱？","audio":null},{"id":23,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"The Nexersys machine was about $4,000. The FightCamp setup — because it included a heavy bag, the sensors, and that's what's really kind of neat about FightCamp, they have the velocity sensors — the sensors that show your punching power and all that kind of stuff, the interactive feedback — all of that was about $2,500 for the bag, the sensors, and some of the other stuff. The nice thing was I was able to finance it through Afterpay, so I just kind of paid monthly for 24 months, and I didn't really worry about it too much.","literal_zh":"Nexersys 机器大概 4000 美元。FightCamp 那套，因为包含重沙袋、传感器，而且 FightCamp 很有意思的一点就是他们有速度传感器，那些传感器能显示你的出拳力量等等，还有互动反馈。沙袋、传感器以及其他一些东西加起来大概 2500 美元。好处是我可以通过 Afterpay 分期，所以我就差不多按月付了 24 个月，也没太担心。","audio":null},{"id":24,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"The only thing that I think is a little pricey is the monthly — I think $49 a month is a little much. Again, if it's the only thing you're doing, I could see that. But I train in different aspects — I do calisthenics and bodyweight work and things like that. For the most part, I think they could have done a little better on that price. But again, if you offer financing, people like me will buy it. We're just that way. It's like, I want to be able to train in my house.","literal_zh":"我唯一觉得有点贵的是月费——我觉得每月 49 美元有点多。当然，如果这是你唯一在做的训练，我能理解。但我会做不同方面的训练，比如健身操、自重训练等等。总体来说，我觉得他们在价格上本可以做得更好。不过话说回来，只要你提供分期，像我这样的人就会买。我们就是这样。我想要能够在自己家里训练。","audio":null},{"id":25,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"One of the neat things I saw was the JabX machine — when I was looking at it, the fact that you had arms that kind of move, I think that's really going to be helpful. If they're moving and we can practice interactive — because that mitt work, that interacting with the machine, is very helpful. I don't know how far along you guys are with that, but it's definitely something that I think would do really well for people like myself.","literal_zh":"我看到 JabX 机器时觉得很有意思的一点是，你们有会动的手臂。我觉得这会非常有帮助。如果它们能动，我们就能做互动练习，因为手靶训练、和机器互动这种东西非常有帮助。我不知道你们现在做到什么程度了，但我确实觉得这类东西会很适合像我这样的人。","audio":null},{"id":26,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 1","english":"People who want to train — and the other thing is, you could start looking at places like Planet Fitness and places like that, where somebody wants to do boxing training and the only thing there is a heavy bag. If you put that machine in there — I think people would get memberships just because the gym had that machine. Because then we can do interactive boxing training without having to join a boxing gym. We can go to Planet Fitness, get our workout in, and then go. I call the Nexersys my \"Fight Bot\" — I would probably call this the same thing — and just go there and get a great workout on top of everything else.","literal_zh":"对于想训练的人来说，另一点是，你们可以开始考虑 Planet Fitness 这类地方。有人想做拳击训练，但那里唯一有的就是一个重沙袋。如果你们把这台机器放进去，我觉得人们会仅仅因为健身房有这台机器就办会员。因为这样我们就可以做互动式拳击训练，而不必加入真正的拳馆。我们可以去 Planet Fitness，完成训练，然后离开。我把 Nexersys 叫作我的“Fight Bot”——我可能也会把这个叫同样的名字——然后去那里，在其他训练之外再完成一次很棒的训练。","audio":null},{"id":27,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 2","english":"Since you're really focused on home-gym training, I want to ask about space. Our JabX is about 16 feet across. Would that be a dealbreaker?","literal_zh":"既然你很重视家庭健身房训练，我想问一下空间问题。我们的 JabX 宽大约 16 英尺，这会不会成为一个决定性障碍？","audio":null},{"id":28,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 2","english":"16 feet might be a little hard. I have a one-car garage, so I would have to convert my one-car garage into my gym — which is what a lot of people do. If you look at YouTube, there are a lot of people who will take a two-car garage and just turn it into a home gym.","literal_zh":"16 英尺可能会有点困难。我的是单车位车库，所以我得把这个单车位车库改成健身房——很多人确实会这么做。你去 YouTube 上看，有很多人会把双车位车库直接改成家庭健身房。","audio":null},{"id":29,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 2","english":"But what a lot of people really like is things like the Mirror — I don't know if you've ever heard of that — where it's on the wall, and things that can be retracted or made smaller when they're not in use. Nobody minds setting up, I mean, it takes me about 15 to 20 minutes to set up for a workout because I've got a mat, I've got to hang the bags, I've got to do all that kind of stuff. I don't mind doing that — I call that my \"commute to the gym.\" I go set up all my equipment and then I start working out.","literal_zh":"但很多人真正喜欢的是像 Mirror 这样的东西——不知道你们有没有听过——它装在墙上，或者是不用的时候可以收起来、变小的东西。没人介意做一点准备。我的意思是，我每次训练前大概需要 15 到 20 分钟布置，因为我要铺垫子，要挂沙袋，要做这些事情。我不介意这么做——我把这叫作我的“去健身房通勤”。我去把所有设备布置好，然后开始训练。","audio":null},{"id":30,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 2","english":"But yeah, 16 feet might be a little big. I'm not saying it's too big — somebody with a two-car garage, yes. But they would have to prioritize, they would have to say, \"Okay, this is going to be the thing I'm doing the most,\" versus having that as one of several pieces of equipment.","literal_zh":"但对，16 英尺可能有点大。我不是说它太大——如果有人有双车位车库，那可以。但他们必须做优先级选择，他们得说：“好，这会是我最常用的东西”，而不是把它当成众多设备之一。","audio":null},{"id":31,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 2","english":"Again, if you're looking at boxers — guys who enjoy boxing and guys who enjoy training — you go in their garage, there's a heavy bag hanging in the middle of it, there's a speed bag in the corner. Boxing equipment is just generally going to take up space. You're not going to have the convenience of opening your closet and pulling out your little NordicTrack, because if you want to box, it's just not that way.","literal_zh":"再说，如果你们看拳击爱好者——那些喜欢拳击、喜欢训练的人——你走进他们车库，中间会挂着一个重沙袋，角落里会有一个速度球。拳击设备通常就是会占地方。你不会像打开衣柜拿出一台小 NordicTrack 那样方便，因为如果你想练拳击，它就不是那样的。","audio":null},{"id":32,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 2","english":"We were thinking about whether wheels might help with storage or movement, but we're not sure whether that would actually be useful.","literal_zh":"我们在考虑轮子是否能帮助收纳或移动，但还不确定这是否真的有用。","audio":null},{"id":33,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 2","english":"The machine that I just showed you, the Nexersys machine — that doesn't move. It's very heavy, because it has to be heavy in order for it not to walk while you're punching. It's pretty stable. I wouldn't say wheels would be necessary, but definitely if it could save space when it's not in use, that might be a selling point. I don't know.","literal_zh":"我刚才给你们看的那台 Nexersys 机器是不会移动的。它非常重，因为它必须重，这样你出拳时它才不会自己跑。它相当稳定。我不会说轮子是必要的，但如果它在不用的时候能节省空间，那绝对可能成为一个卖点。我也不确定。","audio":null},{"id":34,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 3","english":"How long have you been using that Fight Bot, and what does a typical session look like? Is it 10 minutes, an hour, or something more intense?","literal_zh":"你用了那台 Fight Bot 多久？一次典型训练大概是什么样的？是 10 分钟、一小时，还是更高强度？","audio":null},{"id":35,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 3","english":"I'm usually doing a 30-minute workout on that, and then I do a 20-minute workout with FightCamp. So I'll do a cardio or calisthenic workout, and then I'll do 20 minutes on FightCamp. When I finish that workout, then I'll do 30 minutes on that machine in 3-minute rounds — so I'll do 10 or 12 three-minute rounds. And then in between those 3-minute rounds, I'll go hit the speed bag, I'll go hit the double-end bag — those various other things.","literal_zh":"我通常会在那台机器上做 30 分钟训练，然后用 FightCamp 做 20 分钟。所以我会先做心肺或者健身操训练，然后在 FightCamp 上做 20 分钟。完成之后，我会在那台机器上按 3 分钟一回合做 30 分钟，也就是做 10 到 12 个三分钟回合。然后在这些三分钟回合之间，我会去打速度球，打双端球，还有其他各种东西。","audio":null},{"id":36,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 3","english":"You train every day?","literal_zh":"你每天都训练吗？","audio":null},{"id":37,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 3","english":"I'm pretty much a daily guy. I run every day, I swim every day, and then I work out about 3 to 4 times a week — usually Monday, Wednesday, Friday, or Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday. You know, just trying to stay in shape at 55. You've got to keep moving, you've got to move fast.","literal_zh":"我基本上是每天都动的人。我每天跑步，每天游泳，然后每周大概训练 3 到 4 次，通常是周一、周三、周五，或者周二、周四、周六。你知道，就是 55 岁还想保持身材。你必须一直动，而且要动得快。","audio":null},{"id":38,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 3","english":"That is impressive. You look in great shape, so your current training routine seems to be working.","literal_zh":"这很厉害。你看起来状态很好，说明你现在的训练方式确实有效。","audio":null},{"id":39,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 3","english":"Well, thank you. Thank you, I appreciate it.","literal_zh":"嗯，谢谢。谢谢你，我很感激。","audio":null},{"id":40,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 4","english":"What is your home setup like? Do you live with a partner, kids, or roommates, or is it mainly you and the training equipment?","literal_zh":"你家里的情况是怎样的？有伴侣、孩子或室友吗？还是主要就是你和训练设备？","audio":null},{"id":41,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 4","english":"It's just me and my dog. Her name is Eva. (to the dog) Eva, people are talking to you, pay attention.","literal_zh":"就我和我的狗。她叫 Eva。(对狗说) Eva，有人在跟你说话呢，注意听。","audio":null},{"id":42,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 4","english":"Does Eva join any of the training, or is she mainly your running partner?","literal_zh":"Eva 会参与训练吗，还是主要陪你跑步？","audio":null},{"id":43,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 4","english":"No, she runs with me, though. She runs with me in the mornings.","literal_zh":"不会，不过她会跟我一起跑步。早上她会跟我一起跑。","audio":null},{"id":44,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 5","english":"Do you ever invite friends over for boxing sessions, or do you mostly train by yourself?","literal_zh":"你会邀请朋友来一起练拳吗，还是主要自己训练？","audio":null},{"id":45,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 5","english":"Pretty much solo. A lot of people get a little intimidated by boxing — a lot of people, they either get into it or they don't. Most of the guys I know, they like to go to the gym and push the weights, and that's what they do, and that's fine with me. But that's not how I was raised. You know, I was raised to be ready.","literal_zh":"基本都是单练。很多人会被拳击吓到一点，很多人要么喜欢上它，要么完全不碰。我认识的大多数人喜欢去健身房推铁，他们就做那个，我觉得也没问题。但我不是那样成长起来的。你知道，我从小被教育的是要随时准备好。","audio":null},{"id":46,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 5","english":"One of the big slogans about CrossFit when it was in its heyday is, \"You're training for life.\" You're training to be ready, training to be physically ready for anything that life throws at you — work-wise, threat-wise, anything like that. One of the nice things about boxing is it gives you a skill set. Even if you've never stepped in the ring and boxed with anybody — if you know how to throw an effective punch, or if you know how to counterpunch, or you know how to do these things, in a panic situation instinct will take over and you will be able to probably survive that situation.","literal_zh":"CrossFit 鼎盛时期有一句很大的口号是：“你是在为生活而训练。”你训练是为了准备好，让身体准备好应对生活中丢给你的任何事情——工作方面、威胁方面，或者任何类似情况。拳击很棒的一点是，它给你一套技能。即使你从来没有上过擂台和别人真正打过拳，只要你知道如何有效出拳，或者知道如何反击，知道如何做这些事情，在恐慌情境下本能就会接管，你很可能就能从那个情况中活下来。","audio":null},{"id":47,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 5","english":"My boxing skills have benefited me throughout my life. When I was in the military, it was really helpful. When I was in law enforcement, it was extremely helpful. Because most people don't know how to engage. They want to sit there and throw windmills, or they want to pretend like they watched a couple Bruce Lee movies and throw a kick or two. And if you know how to counterpunch, or you know how to actually throw a punch, and you've learned how to develop power — you can get out of a lot of situations with just one quick touch, or one or two quick punches. Many times in law enforcement, that has saved my life.","literal_zh":"我的拳击技能一生都让我受益。我在军队里的时候，它非常有帮助。我在执法系统工作时，它尤其有帮助。因为大多数人不知道如何真正交手。他们只会站在那里乱抡，或者假装自己看过几部李小龙电影，然后踢一两脚。如果你懂得如何反击，或者懂得如何真正出拳，而且学会了如何发力，那你用一次快速接触，或者一两记快拳，就能脱离很多情况。在执法工作中，这很多次救了我的命。","audio":null},{"id":48,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 5","english":"You're training for situations. You're training for being physically confident enough that you can handle anything. It can help you in your work, it can help you in your personal life. It can help you when you're walking to your car in the middle of the night and you're a little nervous — knowing that you've been punching that bag every day, or you've been working with that machine every day and you know how to throw an effective punch. Whatever happens, you could probably handle it. Probably do enough to get away from problems. That's what I've always told people. But I don't generally train with anybody — I just train by myself.","literal_zh":"你是在为各种情境训练。你是在训练自己拥有足够的身体自信，相信自己能处理任何情况。它能帮到你的工作，也能帮到你的个人生活。当你半夜走向自己的车、心里有点紧张时，它也能帮到你——因为你知道自己每天都在打沙袋，或者每天都在用那台机器训练，你知道如何有效出拳。不管发生什么，你大概都能应对。至少能做出足够的反应，让自己脱离麻烦。我一直都是这样告诉别人的。不过我通常不和别人一起练，我就是自己练。","audio":null},{"id":49,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 6","english":"Did you ever compete in the ring, with a referee and formal matches?","literal_zh":"你以前参加过正式拳击比赛吗？就是有裁判、在拳台上的那种。","audio":null},{"id":50,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 6","english":"I boxed a little bit as a youth — you know, 10, 12, 13 years old. I competed a little bit. My record was, I think, 5 and 4. It wasn't great. I was a Philadelphia fighter, which means we led with our faces. If you know anything about boxing, the Philadelphia fighter fights with their hands down. But I was never knocked out — got all TKOs and decisions. I did pretty well.","literal_zh":"我小时候打过一点拳，差不多 10 岁、12 岁、13 岁那会儿。我参加过一些比赛。我的战绩我记得大概是 5 胜 4 负。不算很好。我是费城风格拳手，意思就是我们用脸开路。如果你懂一点拳击，费城拳手是放低双手打的。但我从来没有被击倒过，那些结果都是技术性击倒或者判定。我打得还不错。","audio":null},{"id":51,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 6","english":"But again, when my dad started seeing that I was really enjoying it, he — not that he took it away from me — he just said, \"I want you to focus on other sports. I don't want you to become a professional boxer.\" Because we knew a couple of professional boxers, and he just didn't want the effects of that kind of thing. If you look at it, it's a very short career, or it can lead to some problems later on in life.","literal_zh":"但还是那样，当我父亲开始发现我真的很喜欢拳击时，他并不是把它从我身边拿走，而是说：“我希望你专注于其他运动。我不希望你成为职业拳手。”因为我们认识几个职业拳手，他不想让我承受那种影响。你看职业拳击，那是一个非常短暂的职业生涯，或者可能会在以后的人生里带来一些问题。","audio":null},{"id":52,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 6","english":"However, I played football, so I basically used my body as a human battering ram for eight years while I played football in high school and college. So it's the same thing — you just make collisions. It's the same concept.","literal_zh":"不过我打过橄榄球，所以我在高中和大学打橄榄球的八年里，基本上把自己的身体当成人肉攻城锤用。所以其实差不多，你就是不断碰撞。概念是一样的。","audio":null},{"id":53,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 6","english":"But I have always felt like boxing is something that you can do to develop great fitness and confidence in a lot of situations in life — especially as a man, or even as a woman — out in the world. If you know you can physically protect yourself, or you have this little tool in your toolbox, it gives you the ability to do things that you might not normally do — travel places you might not normally go. And it also gives you a lot of confidence because you're building something that people just don't really have. There's not a lot of boxers in the world. There should be more, because it's a great sport.","literal_zh":"但我一直觉得，拳击是一件能让你培养出很强体能和自信的事情，在生活中很多情境下都有用——尤其是作为男性，甚至女性也是一样，在这个世界上。如果你知道自己身体上可以保护自己，或者你工具箱里有这么一个小工具，它会让你有能力去做一些平常可能不会做的事，去一些平常可能不会去的地方。它也会给你很多自信，因为你在建立一种很多人并不真正拥有的东西。世界上的拳击手其实不多。应该有更多，因为这是一项很棒的运动。","audio":null},{"id":54,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 7","english":"Is boxing popular in Florida, or is it still a fairly niche activity?","literal_zh":"拳击在佛罗里达流行吗，还是仍然比较小众？","audio":null},{"id":55,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 7","english":"In Florida, there are three new boxing gyms that have opened up, but I don't know how long they'll last. I know there's a Mayweather Gym over in Rockledge, and then there's a Rock Box gym. But they're more kind of boutique boxing places, which is great — they're trying to attract a total marketplace.","literal_zh":"在佛罗里达，最近开了三家新的拳馆，但我不知道它们能坚持多久。我知道罗克利奇那边有一家 Mayweather Gym，还有一家 Rock Box。不过它们更像精品拳击馆，这也很好，它们是在努力吸引更广泛的市场。","audio":null},{"id":56,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 7","english":"The boxing gyms I trained in were sweaty, smelly, not climate-controlled, full of guys who were wanting to turn it into a career. But I think these boutique gyms are great, because people can get introduced to boxing and they can enjoy the benefits of the sport. Like I said, the benefits are just far-reaching. They reached so much further than just being able to throw a punch. You develop stamina, you develop wind, you develop that cardiovascular ability to be able to outlast a lot of people in many situations. It's helped me with swimming, you know, because I can hold my breath and all that kind of stuff. So when I swim, I know after a workout you've really put yourself through it. And it helps across the board, as far as I'm concerned.","literal_zh":"我当年训练的拳馆都是汗味很重、气味不好、没有空调的地方，里面全是想把拳击变成职业的人。但我觉得这些精品拳馆很好，因为人们可以通过它们接触拳击，享受这项运动带来的好处。就像我说的，它的好处影响很广。远远不只是会出拳。你会培养耐力，培养气息，培养心肺能力，让你在很多情况下比很多人坚持得更久。它也帮到了我的游泳，因为我能憋气，诸如此类。所以我游泳时知道，训练之后你是真的把自己逼了一把。在我看来，它对各方面都有帮助。","audio":null},{"id":57,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 8","english":"For JabX, should we lean more into the cardio angle, given that you run and swim, or should we keep the positioning more focused on pure boxing?","literal_zh":"对于 JabX 来说，考虑到你跑步和游泳，我们应该更强调心肺训练，还是更专注于纯拳击定位？","audio":null},{"id":58,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 8","english":"Well, I think — if one of the things I would say is, if you can focus on the counterpunching aspect, the moving, the body movements, and that kind of thing, I think that's really going to help.","literal_zh":"嗯，我觉得——如果要我说的话，如果你们能专注在反击、移动、身体动作这些方面，我觉得那会非常有帮助。","audio":null},{"id":59,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 8","english":"Cardio in general — you know, those 3-minute rounds where you're pushing yourself for three minutes, and you take a minute off, and you push yourself for another three minutes — that is amazing. And the farther you can go with that — because you're going to develop strength. It's just a natural byproduct. As you're throwing those punches with those 16-ounce gloves, you're going to develop what they call muscle endurance. And muscle endurance is always going to benefit you, in my opinion, more than just strength. Being able to do three reps of 200 pounds is not as important as muscular endurance, where you've thrown 5,000 punches with 16-ounce gloves on. Your muscles can handle things for much longer, and you personally can handle things for much longer. You can take that longer hike when you're on vacation, you can go do those things because you've been working your body and you developed that muscle endurance. That is a benefit that people overlook. People want to train for aesthetics, and they don't want to train for that overall ability to outlast. I always think that's important.","literal_zh":"心肺本身——你知道，那种 3 分钟一回合，你逼自己连续练三分钟，休息一分钟，再逼自己练三分钟——非常棒。而且你能在这个方向上走得越远越好，因为你会发展力量。这只是自然副产品。当你戴着 16 盎司拳套不断出拳时，你会发展出他们所谓的肌肉耐力。在我看来，肌肉耐力永远比单纯力量更能让你受益。能用 200 磅做三次，不如戴着 16 盎司拳套打出 5000 拳所形成的肌肉耐力重要。你的肌肉能承受更长时间，你本人也能承受更长时间。度假的时候你可以去走更长的徒步路线，可以去做那些事情，因为你一直在锻炼身体，并且发展出了这种肌肉耐力。这是人们忽视的一个好处。人们想为了外形训练，却不想为了那种整体的持久能力训练。我一直认为那很重要。","audio":null},{"id":60,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"You mentioned Mayweather and Rock Box — have you actually stepped foot in either?","literal_zh":"你提到了 Mayweather 和 Rock Box，你真的去过其中任何一家吗？","audio":null},{"id":61,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"The Mayweather Gym — yes, I've been to that one. I haven't been to the Rock Box over in Rockledge, it's relatively new, I haven't been over there. They're very… I would say, what's the word I'm looking for… unisex. They're catering to both men and women, they're catering to the family. It's a very family-oriented environment.","literal_zh":"Mayweather Gym——去过，我去过那家。我还没去过罗克利奇那边的 Rock Box，它比较新，我还没过去看过。它们非常……我该怎么说……偏男女皆宜。它们同时服务男性和女性，也服务家庭。那是非常面向家庭的环境。","audio":null},{"id":62,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"I think very few people would be interested in going to the place that I went to, or there's a place down in Miami called the Hit Pit. It's like a CrossFit box — I don't know if you've ever been in a CrossFit gym. No air conditioning, it's usually a warehouse with hangar doors, and it's just bare bones. Some people don't go for that.","literal_zh":"我觉得很少有人会想去我以前去的那种地方，或者迈阿密有个地方叫 Hit Pit。它就像 CrossFit box 一样——不知道你们有没有去过 CrossFit 健身房。没有空调，通常是带大卷门的仓库，非常基础。有些人不吃这一套。","audio":null},{"id":63,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"What I've seen with these new boxing gyms is they lead with cardio classes, there's all kinds of neat stuff going on. They're very much a kind of boutique boxing gym, and there's nothing wrong with that — I'm not judging it. But if you wanted to train to be a boxer, you would have to go down to one of those other gyms where there are coaches, and trainers, and people who are going to work with you on dealing with an opponent, as opposed to just general fitness.","literal_zh":"我在这些新拳馆里看到的是，它们主打心肺课程，有各种很有意思的东西。它们很明显是一种精品拳击馆，这没什么错——我不是在评判它。但如果你想训练成一个真正的拳手，你就得去那些别的拳馆，那里有教练、训练师，有人会和你一起练如何应对对手，而不只是一般健身。","audio":null},{"id":64,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"You can throw a punch, you can do all kinds of cool stuff. I think Bruce Lee said, \"I'm never worried about a man who can throw 10,000 punches. I'm worried about the one man who's thrown one punch 10,000 times.\"","literal_zh":"你可以出拳，可以做各种很酷的动作。我记得李小龙说过：“我不怕会打一万种拳的人，我怕的是把一种拳练了一万次的人。”","audio":null},{"id":65,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"Yes, I know that quote. It's such a classic.","literal_zh":"对，我知道那句话。那是一句很经典的话。","audio":null},{"id":66,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"It's a very interesting concept. If you can throw a jab and a cross, and you've done that enough times, then that's all you're ever going to need.","literal_zh":"这是一个很有意思的概念。如果你会打刺拳和直拳，而且练过足够多次，那基本上就是你所需要的一切。","audio":null},{"id":67,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"\"Be water, my friend.\"","literal_zh":"“像水一样，我的朋友。”","audio":null},{"id":68,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"I'm a big fan. I'm a big fan.","literal_zh":"我是他的超级粉丝。真的很喜欢。","audio":null},{"id":69,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"I trained in Arnis de Mano in college — the Filipino art — under Dr. Tim Sheehan, who was a student of Remy Presas. He was a big fan of keeping it simple — very simple stuff. But I always admired Bruce because he was willing to do what most martial arts instructors at the time wouldn't do, which is teach Gweilo — teach round-eyes. He was willing to teach anybody who was willing to listen, and he was looking at the art in a way that asked what makes sense and what doesn't.","literal_zh":"我大学时练过 Arnis de Mano——菲律宾武术——师从 Tim Sheehan 博士，他是 Remy Presas 的学生。他非常推崇保持简单，非常简单的东西。但我一直很佩服 Bruce，因为他愿意做当时大多数武术老师不愿意做的事，也就是教“鬼佬”、教白人。他愿意教任何愿意听的人，而且他看待武术的方式是不断问：什么有意义，什么没有意义。","audio":null},{"id":70,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 9","english":"His understanding of anatomy — and the fact that he was reading about Greco-Roman wrestling before the MMA scene came into play, and all the ground fighting and Jiu-Jitsu. He was studying Greco-Roman wrestling because he was asking, \"What happens if we fall on the ground? What do we do then?\" Well, Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu wasn't all there yet. He was an innovator — he was so far ahead of his time. It was amazing, and it was a tragedy when he died. We miss him.","literal_zh":"他对人体结构的理解，以及在 MMA 场景真正兴起之前、在地面格斗和柔术普及之前，他就已经在阅读希腊罗马摔跤的资料。他研究希腊罗马摔跤，是因为他在问：“如果我们摔到地上会怎样？那时我们该怎么办？”那时巴西柔术还没有完全进入视野。他是一个创新者，领先自己的时代太多了。那非常了不起，而他的离世也是一场悲剧。我们都很怀念他。","audio":null},{"id":71,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 10","english":"When you went to the Mayweather gym, was it busy, or was it fairly quiet?","literal_zh":"你去 Mayweather Gym 的时候，那里人多吗，还是比较安静？","audio":null},{"id":72,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 10","english":"When they were hosting the classes — like the 7 a.m. classes and the 5 p.m. classes, before people go to work or after people get home from work — it was busy. Very busy, for a while. I think they picked a location that was probably a little too expensive for the gym owner. Rather than find a location that might have been a little more out of the way, a little better priced — I think it was the cost of the building that was causing problems, because it was busy. They were getting members, and people were showing up and training.","literal_zh":"当他们开课的时候，比如早上 7 点的课和下午 5 点的课，也就是人们上班前或者下班后，那时很忙。曾经有一段时间非常忙。我觉得他们选的地点对馆主来说可能有点太贵了。他们没有找一个稍微偏一点、价格更合适的地方——我觉得问题是楼宇成本太高，因为它本身是有人气的。他们确实在获得会员，也有人来训练。","audio":null},{"id":73,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 10","english":"I think there's a real future for something like your system in those gyms, because then somebody can come in — maybe not during a class, but they can come in and they can hit that thing, or use it between classes or after classes or before classes.","literal_zh":"我觉得像你们这样的系统在那些健身房里很有前景，因为有人可以进来，也许不是在上课期间，但他们可以来打那个东西，或者在课间、课后、课前使用它。","audio":null},{"id":74,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 10","english":"I would definitely look at — if I was marketing it — I would market it to Planet Fitness, I would market it to Crunch, I would market it to all these gyms in America that are in the overall fitness space. Just say, \"Hey, you need this in your gym. It's going to bring people in.\"","literal_zh":"如果是我来做市场推广，我肯定会考虑 Planet Fitness、Crunch，以及美国所有这些综合健身领域的健身房。就告诉他们：“嘿，你们的健身房需要这个。它会把人带进来。”","audio":null},{"id":75,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 11","english":"How much does Mayweather charge for a membership?","literal_zh":"Mayweather Gym 的会员费是多少？","audio":null},{"id":76,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 11","english":"Membership at Mayweather, I think, was $29 a month. It wasn't that expensive. It wasn't Planet Fitness where you pay five, but at the same time, they're having to pay trainers to come in and teach these classes, and they're having to pay people to be there. So I understood the cost, and it wasn't that exorbitant to me.","literal_zh":"Mayweather 的会员费我记得是每月 29 美元。不算很贵。它不是 Planet Fitness 那种你付 5 美元就行的地方，但同时他们得付钱请教练来上课，也得付钱让员工在场。所以我理解这个成本，对我来说不算太离谱。","audio":null},{"id":77,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 11","english":"But Planet Fitness — it's a self-guided thing. You go in, you work out, you go home. There's one guy in the place, so they don't have that much overhead, so they can charge what they charge.","literal_zh":"但 Planet Fitness 是自助式的。你进去，训练，然后回家。场馆里就一个工作人员，所以他们没有那么多运营成本，因此可以收他们那个价格。","audio":null},{"id":78,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 11","english":"I think JabX would be great in a gym like Planet Fitness or Crunch, as an addition to what's already there. But at the same time, if you put it in the Mayweather, if you put it in the Rock Box, or these boutique boxing gyms, people are going to love it, because they're going to be able to go in there and train by themselves if they want. They won't have to go to the class — they can use JabX and get just as good a workout. Then they can go hit the bag, or they can use it as an augment to hitting the bag. \"Okay, I hit the bag — now let me go work with the Fight Bot and have it tell me what to do.\"","literal_zh":"我觉得 JabX 放在 Planet Fitness 或 Crunch 这样的健身房会很棒，作为现有设备的补充。但同时，如果你们把它放进 Mayweather、Rock Box，或者这些精品拳击馆，人们也会喜欢，因为他们想的话可以进去自己训练。他们不一定非得上课，可以使用 JabX，并获得同样好的训练效果。然后他们可以去打沙袋，或者把它作为打沙袋的补充。“好，我打完沙袋了，现在让我去跟 Fight Bot 练，让它告诉我该做什么。”","audio":null},{"id":79,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 12","english":"When you visit the boutique gym this week, would you be able to take a few photos for us? That would be really helpful.","literal_zh":"你这周去那家精品拳馆的时候，方便帮我们拍几张照片吗？那会很有帮助。","audio":null},{"id":80,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 12","english":"Yeah, I can take some pictures.","literal_zh":"可以，我可以拍一些照片。","audio":null},{"id":81,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 12","english":"Thank you. Also, what kind of combat-sports equipment do they have there?","literal_zh":"谢谢。另外，他们那里有哪些格斗训练设备？","audio":null},{"id":82,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 12","english":"The new one, I haven't investigated, but I'll go check it out for you. I'll take some photos and kind of get you a look at the setup and all that kind of stuff. I'm happy to do that for you. Because I want to go check it out anyway, so it's just my excuse to check it out. It'll probably be Friday morning that I'll go over there. I'll go check it out Friday morning, and I'll send you a bunch of pictures — maybe take a video or two for you.","literal_zh":"新开的那家我还没调查过，但我会去帮你们看一下。我会拍些照片，让你们大概看看它的布置和各种东西。我很乐意帮你们做这个。因为我本来也想去看看，所以这正好给了我一个去看的理由。我大概会周五早上过去。周五早上我会去看一下，然后给你们发一堆照片，也许还拍一两个视频给你们。","audio":null},{"id":83,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 12","english":"If you send me your email address, I'll send you an email and I'll get you all the information on the Nexersys machine as well.","literal_zh":"如果你们把邮箱地址发给我，我会给你们发邮件，也会把 Nexersys 机器的所有信息一起发过去。","audio":null},{"id":84,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 12","english":"I think we already have your WhatsApp. We'll send the email there.","literal_zh":"我想我们已经有你的 WhatsApp 了。我们会把邮箱发到那里。","audio":null},{"id":85,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 12","english":"That'd be perfect.","literal_zh":"那就完美了。","audio":null},{"id":86,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 13","english":"This may be a good moment to show you JabX. Full disclosure, what we have right now is still a render; we haven't launched yet.","literal_zh":"现在可能正好可以给你看一下 JabX。先说明一下，目前我们手上还是渲染图，还没有正式发布。","audio":null},{"id":87,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 13","english":"I'd love to see it. I saw a couple of pictures, and it was very cool to look at.","literal_zh":"我很想看。我看过几张图片，看起来非常酷。","audio":null},{"id":88,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 13","english":"Let me walk you through it. (shows JabX images) Here's the head target, the stomach target, and the screen. Both arms can swing through different angles, so they're not locked in place.","literal_zh":"我来给你介绍一下。（展示 JabX 图片）这里是头部目标、腹部目标和屏幕。两个手臂都可以以不同角度摆动，不是固定不动的。","audio":null},{"id":89,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 13","english":"I've seen other products where the arms are fixed — like six fixed positions. But yours can go through every angle?","literal_zh":"我见过其他产品，手臂是固定的，比如六个固定位置。但你们这个可以经过每个角度？","audio":null},{"id":90,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 13","english":"Yes, every angle. The idea is to make it feel closer to fighting a real person, so you can throw a wide range of combinations.","literal_zh":"对，各种角度都可以。我们的想法是让它更接近和真人对练的感觉，这样用户可以打出更丰富的组合。","audio":null},{"id":91,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 13","english":"Very cool. And the height — can you adjust it?","literal_zh":"非常酷。那高度呢，可以调吗？","audio":null},{"id":92,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 13","english":"Yes, it has a camera that scans your height and auto-adjusts, so whether someone is 5'2\" or 6'5\", the system can fit them.","literal_zh":"对，它有摄像头可以扫描身高并自动调整，所以无论用户是 5 英尺 2 英寸还是 6 英尺 5 英寸，系统都能适配。","audio":null},{"id":93,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 13","english":"Oh wow. That is really cool. Very cool. I can't wait till you guys get it off the ground.","literal_zh":"哦，哇。这个真的很酷。非常酷。我等不及看到你们把它做起来了。","audio":null},{"id":94,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"(JabX team demonstrates the arm movement and light feedback system)","literal_zh":"(JabX 团队演示手臂运动和灯光反馈系统)","audio":null},{"id":95,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"Our teammate is about to do a quick demo. It's still a little rough, but it should give you the idea.","literal_zh":"我们的同事会做一个快速演示。目前还比较早期，但应该能让你理解大概效果。","audio":null},{"id":96,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"(watching the demo) I'm pretending he's the machine. I got it.","literal_zh":"(看演示) 我就假装他是机器。我懂了。","audio":null},{"id":97,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"This is the head side. I can parry, and when I throw a punch, lights show me where to hit next. Then I can duck and counter, so the system gives real-time feedback.","literal_zh":"这是头部这一侧。我可以格挡；出拳后，灯光会提示下一拳打哪里。然后我可以下潜并反击，所以系统会给实时反馈。","audio":null},{"id":98,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"Oh wow. Okay. So the lights show you where to punch and reflect your hits?","literal_zh":"哦，哇。好。所以灯会显示你该打哪里，也会反馈你打中了哪里？","audio":null},{"id":99,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"We probably shouldn't kick it too hard yet, because the current motor is still an early version and might not be strong enough.","literal_zh":"现在可能还不能太用力踢，因为当前电机还是早期版本，强度可能还不够。","audio":null},{"id":100,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"Very cool. I'm excited. You're absolutely onto something, because the fact that you can move and pivot —","literal_zh":"非常酷。我很兴奋。你们绝对抓到了一个好方向，因为它能够移动和转动——","audio":null},{"id":101,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"Exactly. We'll have much more content later, including different training modes. There's also a massage mode: after the workout, it can help relax your shoulders and back.","literal_zh":"没错。后续我们会有更多内容，包括不同训练模式。还有一个按摩模式：训练结束后，它可以帮助放松肩膀和背部。","audio":null},{"id":102,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"If you give me till next week — I tore my lawn apart because I want to put zoysia grass in, so it's very brown right now while we're waiting for the grass to come in. I'd rather take pictures and do all that kind of stuff when it's in better shape. But what you're talking about — where it moves, and you have to maneuver as well as strike — that's an element that the Nexersys does digitally. If you're doing it physically, it's going to… you guys are so onto something. It's going to be really cool, because it makes it interactive. It gives you an opponent, for lack of a better term. You don't have to imagine — like, imagine doing… you're physically moving away from, you're physically working with that opponent.","literal_zh":"如果你们给我到下周——我把草坪翻了一遍，因为我想铺结缕草，所以现在草还没长出来，看起来很黄。我更愿意等它状态好一点的时候再拍照片和做那些事情。但你们说的这个——它会动，你既要移动也要击打——这是 Nexersys 以数字方式实现的元素。如果你们用实体方式实现，那会……你们真的抓到东西了。这会非常酷，因为它让训练变得互动。它给了你一个对手，姑且这么说。你不需要想象，比如想象自己在做什么……你是在身体上真正躲开，真正和那个对手互动。","audio":null},{"id":103,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 14","english":"Very good. Digital approval — very good.","literal_zh":"很好。线上批准——非常好。","audio":null},{"id":104,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"Is there anything you would like to ask us? We've been asking you questions the whole time.","literal_zh":"你有什么想问我们的吗？一直都是我们在问你问题。","audio":null},{"id":105,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"Is there anything you would like to ask us? We've been asking you questions the whole time.","literal_zh":"你有什么想问我们的吗？一直都是我们在问你问题。","audio":null},{"id":106,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"If we think of more questions later, would it be okay if we reach out on WhatsApp?","literal_zh":"如果我们后面想到更多问题，可以通过 WhatsApp 再联系你吗？","audio":null},{"id":107,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"I'll happily answer any questions you've got.","literal_zh":"你们有任何问题，我都很乐意回答。","audio":null},{"id":108,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"One more thing about the FightCamp sensors: do you still use them?","literal_zh":"还有一个关于 FightCamp 传感器的问题：你现在还在用它们吗？","audio":null},{"id":109,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"Yes.","literal_zh":"在用。","audio":null},{"id":110,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"What kind of data do they actually give you?","literal_zh":"它们实际会给你什么数据？","audio":null},{"id":111,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"The thing that I've noticed — they call them accelerometers. I hit a pretty heavy bag, so I don't use their FightCamp bag. I use a water bag, or kind of like a bag like you have behind you. And so it doesn't determine punching power as well — there's not as much give. But I think the punch count was really good. It was kind of rudimentary about three or four years ago when I first started using it, but it's gotten much more accurate.","literal_zh":"我注意到的是——他们叫它们加速度计。我打的是相当重的沙袋，所以我不用他们的 FightCamp 沙袋。我用的是水袋，或者有点像你们身后那种袋子。因此它对出拳力量的判断没那么好，因为沙袋没有那么多形变。但我觉得出拳次数统计做得很好。我三四年前刚开始用的时候，它还有点基础，但现在准确多了。","audio":null},{"id":112,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"That's a really useful point. We were thinking about sensors as well, maybe in the gloves or on the machine itself.","literal_zh":"这个点很有用。我们也在考虑传感器，可能放在手套里，也可能放在机器本体上。","audio":null},{"id":113,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"But I think the punching power on the accelerometer is a little… it's not as accurate as I would like it to be. Other than that, I think that whole sensor feedback thing is just awesome, because it helps you understand that you're improving while you're doing it. You don't have to look at your data afterwards — you know your goal, you know you're doing your thing. Also, it allows you the opportunity to shadow box if you really want to, because you still have the accelerometer. So you can use FightCamp to kind of shadow box as well. That's an aspect of boxing that gets overlooked a lot.","literal_zh":"但我觉得加速度计测出的出拳力量有点……没有我希望的那么准确。除此之外，我觉得整个传感器反馈系统非常棒，因为它帮助你在训练过程中就理解自己正在进步。你不用等训练后再看数据——你知道自己的目标，也知道自己正在做什么。另外，如果你真的想，它也让你有机会做空击，因为你身上仍然有加速度计。所以你也可以用 FightCamp 做某种空击训练。这是拳击中经常被忽视的一方面。","audio":null},{"id":114,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 15","english":"I think if somebody built the sensors into a pair of gloves that they were going to sell with the product, it would be much easier. Because now you have to tuck them into your wraps, and you can only use their wraps — it makes it proprietary. But if you put the accelerometers into a pair of boxing gloves, that would be one more thing you could sell with the system. You could sell the accelerometers, or you could say, \"If you pay $99.95 for the combo, you get the JabX boxing gloves with the accelerometer built in.\" Someone might think, \"That would be worth buying.\"","literal_zh":"我觉得如果有人把传感器直接做进一副拳套里，并随产品一起销售，那会方便得多。因为现在你得把它们塞进缠手带里，而且只能用他们的缠手带，这就变成了专有系统。但如果你把加速度计放进一副拳击手套里，那就是你可以和系统一起销售的另一个东西。你可以卖加速度计，也可以说：“如果你花 99.95 美元买组合包，就能得到内置加速度计的 JabX 拳套。”用户可能会觉得：“这个值得买。”","audio":null},{"id":115,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 16","english":"How hard do you usually punch? Do you have a number for that?","literal_zh":"你通常出拳力量有多大？有具体数据吗？","audio":null},{"id":116,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 16","english":"I hit harder than most, but I don't have an exact number. I've worked with people — mitt work. I have a very heavy left hook. It has saved me in a lot of situations, let's put it that way. It's because when I studied Arnis, it was very big on hip movement. Boxing is about — you don't punch with your arms, you punch with your body. You punch with your hips. It's about your hip movements, your torque. Developing power — you develop power through rotating and all that. So everything I do is about rotating and about footwork.","literal_zh":"我比大多数人打得重，但没有确切数字。我和别人练过手靶。我有一记很重的左勾拳。可以这么说，它在很多情况下救过我。这是因为我学习 Arnis 的时候，非常强调髋部动作。拳击讲的是——你不是用胳膊出拳，而是用身体出拳。你用髋部出拳。关键在于髋部动作、扭矩。发展力量，就是通过旋转等等来发展力量。所以我做的一切都围绕旋转和步法。","audio":null},{"id":117,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 17","english":"Have you ever used one of those force-plate systems, the kind of sensor that measures exactly how hard you hit?","literal_zh":"你用过那种测力板系统吗？就是可以精确测量击打力量的传感器。","audio":null},{"id":118,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 17","english":"Yes, I've used those.","literal_zh":"用过，我用过。","audio":null},{"id":119,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 17","english":"What if we built that into JabX, so it could show your punch pressure or impact for every punch?","literal_zh":"如果我们把这个能力内置到 JabX 里，让它显示每一拳的压力或冲击力，你觉得怎么样？","audio":null},{"id":120,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 17","english":"Oh, that would be cool. It would give you meaningful feedback on punching power.","literal_zh":"哦，那会很酷。它会给你关于出拳力量的有意义反馈。","audio":null},{"id":121,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 17","english":"That's the direction we want to go: sensors in the arms and real performance numbers.","literal_zh":"这正是我们想做的方向：把传感器放进手臂里，提供真实的表现数据。","audio":null},{"id":122,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 17","english":"You want to be able to hit 750 pounds per square inch. \"I want a 750 PSI punch\" — and that's what you work towards. So every punch you're throwing, you're trying to hit that 750 pounds, because that's generally what a professional fighter will hit — between 750 and 950. Most people will hit between the 200 to 300 PSI range, because they're arm punching, until they learn how to turn over the punch — getting your hips behind you, rotating off your back foot.","literal_zh":"你会想达到每平方英寸 750 磅。“我想打出 750 PSI 的拳”——这就是你努力的方向。所以你打出的每一拳，都在尝试达到那 750 磅，因为职业拳手通常能打到那个水平，大概 750 到 950 之间。大多数人会在 200 到 300 PSI 的范围，因为他们是在用胳膊打，直到他们学会如何把拳翻出去，也就是让髋部带上来，从后脚旋转发力。","audio":null},{"id":123,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 17","english":"One of the things about boxing is everything's backwards. If you want to generate power, you've got to rotate off your back foot versus your front foot. You've got to learn that nothing is what you think it's going to be — and then let your body develop naturally.","literal_zh":"拳击里有一点是，一切都和直觉相反。如果你想产生力量，你必须从后脚而不是前脚旋转。你必须学会，事情并不会像你以为的那样，然后让身体自然发展出来。","audio":null},{"id":124,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"Do you still have a few minutes, or are we keeping you too long?","literal_zh":"你现在还有几分钟吗？还是我们已经占用你太久了？","audio":null},{"id":125,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"Oh, sure. I thought this was the interview. Yeah, I've got a few more minutes.","literal_zh":"哦，当然。我以为这就是访谈。对，我还有几分钟。","audio":null},{"id":126,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"Besides punch power, what other data would matter to you? What kind of feedback would feel genuinely useful?","literal_zh":"除了出拳力量之外，还有哪些数据对你重要？什么样的反馈会让你觉得真正有用？","audio":null},{"id":127,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"I would say punch count is really important. Setting those goals — because what's going to help you cardiovascularly, and what's going to help you with muscle endurance, is setting, \"Okay, for this round you want to punch 500 times,\" throughout the different combinations that we're going to do.","literal_zh":"我会说出拳次数非常重要。设定这些目标，因为真正能帮助你心肺、帮助你肌肉耐力的是设定：“好，这一回合你要出 500 拳”，并且在我们要做的不同组合里完成它。","audio":null},{"id":128,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"The other thing is introducing combinations — teaching people how to throw a 4, 5, 6-punch combination and ripping it, and repeating that. So, \"We're going to do 2, 4, 6, 3,\" and 2, 4, 6, 3, and 2, 4, 6, 3 — until everything becomes muscle memory.","literal_zh":"另一个是引入组合拳，教人们如何打出 4 拳、5 拳、6 拳的组合，并且快速打出来、不断重复。所以比如“我们要做 2、4、6、3”，然后 2、4、6、3，再 2、4、6、3，直到一切变成肌肉记忆。","audio":null},{"id":129,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"One of the things that we learned is it takes 250 repetitions of a particular task to make it muscle memory. In other words, you don't think about shaking someone's hand, because you've done that 250 times. You don't think, \"Extend arm, open palm, turn slightly, shake, release, return.\" You don't think about it — it's instinctive. You've repeated that thing.","literal_zh":"我们学到的一件事是，一个特定动作需要重复 250 次才能变成肌肉记忆。换句话说，你不会去思考怎么和别人握手，因为你已经做过 250 次。你不会想：“伸出手臂，打开手掌，稍微转动，握手，松开，收回。”你不会去想，它是本能。因为你重复过那件事。","audio":null},{"id":130,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"So when you're learning combinations — if you think about a 1-2 punch combination, you're going to have to do that 250 times before somebody can say \"1-2\" and you know exactly what to do. Those lessons, when you're looking at going from a novice to a boxer who can throw multiple punch combinations — which is ultimately what you want. You want to look cool, and you want to be able to throw all those cool punches — it's repetition, repetition, repetition. While making it fun at the same time. Not feeling like you're going crazy.","literal_zh":"所以当你学习组合拳时，如果你想的是 1-2 组合，你得做 250 次，别人才一说“1-2”，你就知道该怎么做。从新手到能够打出多拳组合的拳手，这些课程就是关键，而这最终也是你想要的。你想看起来很酷，也想能打出那些很酷的拳——这靠的是重复、重复、重复。同时还要让它有趣，不要让人觉得自己快疯了。","audio":null},{"id":131,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"And with the arm movement — now you can throw… you're not just ducking for ducking's sake. You're actually trying to get out of the way of something. Something they do in FightCamp is \"1, 2 — duck! Pull back. 1, 2 — duck.\" You're having to do all that by command. Whereas with your machine, you'll actually physically have to do it, because that thing's going to move over top of you. That's just something that's going to be really, really innovative with your system. I'm very excited to see it.","literal_zh":"再加上手臂运动，现在你可以打……你不是为了下潜而下潜。你是真的在试图躲开某个东西。FightCamp 里会做类似“1、2——下潜！后撤。1、2——下潜”的内容。你是根据口令做所有动作。而你们的机器会让你在身体上真的不得不去做，因为那个东西会从你头上方移动过去。这会是你们系统里非常非常创新的一点。我很期待看到它。","audio":null},{"id":132,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"Punch goals, repetitions, repeating those repetitions so that you can develop those instinctive, quick combinations that you can throw — and then take advantage of the fact that you can do counterpunching. You're slipping, you're ducking, you're trying to get out of the way of a cross, and now you're counterpunching. That's something that, based on what you physically designed — boxers will go, \"Oh man!\" Because they're going to want to utilize that, they're going to want to learn.","literal_zh":"出拳目标、重复次数，不断重复这些动作，让你能发展出本能的、快速的组合拳——然后再利用你可以做反击这一点。你在闪躲，你在下潜，你在试图躲开一记直拳，然后你开始反击。基于你们已经做出的实体设计，拳击手会说：“哇，兄弟！”因为他们会想利用这个，会想学习。","audio":null},{"id":133,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 18","english":"Counterpunching is something that you can only learn with a real partner. Normally a person is calling out numbers, you're throwing those punches, and they're swinging their arms over your head — you have to physically get out of the way. You've created something where it's basically like doing mitt work with combinations, and you're having to physically move, as opposed to going through the motions. Because let's face it — when you're tired, you're not going to duck as low as you should, you're not going to keep your eyes on the target like you should. You're going to lower your head, you're going to lower your chin, you're going to leave yourself exposed. You can do all those things that you're not supposed to do when you're boxing — things you would normally have to have the discipline to do yourself every time. With that machine, you physically have to do it. It's really cool.","literal_zh":"反击通常是只能和真实伙伴一起学的。一般会有一个人喊数字，你打出那些拳，同时对方会把手臂从你头上挥过去，你必须身体上真的躲开。你们创造出来的东西，基本上就像是在做带组合拳的手靶训练，而且你必须真正移动，而不是只是走过场。因为说实话，当你累的时候，你下潜不会像应该的那样低，你不会像应该的那样盯住目标。你会低头，会收下巴过度，会让自己暴露。你会做出所有拳击时不该做的事情，而这些通常需要你每次都靠自律去完成。用那台机器，你身体上不得不去做。真的很酷。","audio":null},{"id":134,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 19","english":"I have two more questions, and then we'll let you go. First, if JabX could track speed and reaction time, and rank users by level, would that be useful?","literal_zh":"我还有两个问题，然后就不继续占用你时间了。第一个，如果 JabX 能追踪速度和反应时间，并按水平给用户分级，这会有用吗？","audio":null},{"id":135,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 19","english":"Oh, absolutely. Because then you could set levels — beginner, intermediate, and advanced — and you can work towards those. At the beginner level, things are moving rather slowly. It's kind of like that progressive training purpose. Then as you get into the intermediate level, things are moving a little faster — so when you've got to move, you've got to move. And when you get to the advanced level, it's almost like you're fighting an opponent.","literal_zh":"哦，绝对会。因为那样你们就可以设置等级：初级、中级、高级，然后用户可以朝这些等级努力。在初级阶段，东西移动得比较慢。这就像渐进式训练的目的。然后到了中级阶段，东西移动得更快一些，所以当你该动的时候，你就必须动。到了高级阶段，它几乎就像你在和一个对手交手。","audio":null},{"id":136,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 19","english":"That is a great idea — to either interactively match your speed, in other words, how you move, and then I would even give some form of negative feedback. If it pops you in the head because you don't get low enough — not so much negative feedback like punishment, but like how a coach would talk to you: \"Get your head down. Make sure you're looking at your target. Get a little faster, come on!\" Have that positive and negative motivation where the system is kind of coaching you.","literal_zh":"这是个很棒的想法——它可以互动式地匹配你的速度，也就是根据你的移动方式来调整。我甚至会加入某种负反馈。如果因为你没有蹲得足够低，它轻轻碰到你的头——不是那种惩罚式的负反馈，而是像教练跟你说话一样：“把头低下去。确保你看着目标。再快一点，来！”让系统以一种教练的方式给你正向和负向激励。","audio":null},{"id":137,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 19","english":"Something I might suggest: find a pro boxer to do like they did in Madden with the video game — where a pro boxer is talking to you while you're training, or a trainer. You're getting feedback from a pro, from someone you might recognize, rather than a computer buzzing at you.","literal_zh":"我可能会建议一件事：找一个职业拳手来做，就像 Madden 橄榄球游戏里那样——让职业拳手或训练师在你训练时跟你说话。你得到的是来自专业人士、来自你可能认识的人的反馈，而不是一台电脑对你嗡嗡响。","audio":null},{"id":138,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 19","english":"I can think of a couple people in the business. Tony Jeffries is a British boxer who does a lot of YouTube and TikTok on boxing — coaching, virtual coaching, reviews of fights. He was a former Olympic boxer. The list is endless of retired boxers who probably would love to get on board with your project and be the voice.","literal_zh":"我能想到这个行业里几个人。Tony Jeffries 是一位英国拳手，他在 YouTube 和 TikTok 上做很多拳击内容，包括教学、线上指导、比赛点评。他曾经是奥运拳击手。退役拳手的名单很长，他们可能会很愿意加入你们项目，成为那个声音。","audio":null},{"id":139,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 19","english":"As you said, interactive or reactive movement — and then setting movement goals. You want to get from beginner to intermediate where you're moving faster, and then to that advanced level. It's that next level you're trying to get to, where it's moving faster and faster, you have to move faster and faster, and you have to punch quicker, and you have to improve.","literal_zh":"就像你们说的，互动式或反应式移动，然后设置移动目标。你想从初级到中级，在那里你移动得更快，然后再到高级水平。你要追求的是下一个等级，机器越来越快，你必须越来越快地移动，也必须更快出拳，并且不断提升。","audio":null},{"id":140,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 19","english":"That's going to be something — because especially with boxing, you're going to be looking at Type A, competitive people. They're Type A personalities, and they're competitive because they love competition. So having challenges and benchmarks — you put something in front of them that says, \"You know, you have to train to get here\" — they're going to be like, \"Whoa, I've got to get that.\"","literal_zh":"这会很有价值——因为尤其是在拳击里，你们面对的是 A 型人格、喜欢竞争的人。他们是 A 型人格，而且有竞争心，因为他们热爱竞争。所以有挑战、有基准——你在他们面前放一个目标，说“你知道，你必须训练到这里”——他们会想：“哇，我一定要拿到那个。”","audio":null},{"id":141,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 20","english":"What if JabX included training games, such as a rhythm mode where you punch to the beat, or a simulation mode where you train against Mike Tyson-style punches?","literal_zh":"如果 JabX 加入训练游戏，比如跟着节奏出拳的节奏模式，或者模拟和 Mike Tyson 风格拳路对练的模式，你觉得怎么样？","audio":null},{"id":142,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 20","english":"100%. Both of those functions would be great, especially with Tyson, because then all the Gen Xers will remember Punch-Out from when we were kids — the Nintendo game where it was Mike Tyson and you were the little drawing of a boxer. And that was us! And then you had Mike Tyson, who was like nine feet tall. All of us Generation X types who played those video games as kids would be like, \"Yeah, this is just like the video game — only better.\"","literal_zh":"百分之百。那两个功能都会很棒，尤其是泰森那个，因为所有 X 世代的人都会想起我们小时候玩的 Punch-Out，就是任天堂那个游戏，里面有迈克·泰森，而你是一个小小的拳击手图像。那就是我们！然后你面前是像九英尺高一样的迈克·泰森。我们这些小时候玩过那些电子游戏的 X 世代都会说：“对，这就像那个游戏，只是更好。”","audio":null},{"id":143,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"We're thinking about an AI coach that watches through the camera, analyzes your form, and gives tips. What would you want it to do for you?","literal_zh":"我们在考虑 AI 教练功能，通过摄像头观察动作、分析姿势并给出建议。你希望它为你做什么？","audio":null},{"id":144,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"I think it would really help, because then you could analyze — especially if AI is interactive and you have a camera that's watching. You can say, \"Hey, you didn't keep your chin up six times in the last two minutes. You've got to work on that.\" You get real feedback from the AI actually analyzing your punches. \"You're having trouble keeping your hands up at the end of the round. You need to work on that.\" All that feedback at the end.","literal_zh":"我觉得它真的会有帮助，因为那样你就可以分析——尤其是如果 AI 是互动式的，而且有摄像头在看。它可以说：“嘿，过去两分钟里你有六次没有保持下巴位置。你得练这个。”你会从真正分析你出拳的 AI 那里得到真实反馈。“你在回合末段很难保持双手抬起。你需要练这个。”这些都是回合结束后的反馈。","audio":null},{"id":145,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"Especially from an AI that can analyze what you've been doing and what they expect. \"Your hands drop four inches from the beginning of the first round to the end of the third round — that's something we need to work on.\" And then it can even analyze and create a training program — a boxing program where you're working on keeping your hands up, keeping your guard up. It can spot those inconsistencies in your boxing and help you improve.","literal_zh":"尤其是 AI 能分析你一直在做什么，以及它期望你做到什么。“从第一回合开始到第三回合结束，你的双手下降了四英寸——这是我们需要练的东西。”然后它甚至可以分析并创建一个训练计划，一个拳击计划，专门让你练保持双手抬起、保持防守架势。它可以发现你拳击动作中的不一致之处，并帮助你提高。","audio":null},{"id":146,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"That's just going to be icing on the cake. Especially, \"Hey, at the end of the round we noticed the following…\" And you're like, \"Oh man, I can't believe you saw that.\"","literal_zh":"那会是锦上添花。尤其是那种：“嘿，在这一回合结束时，我们注意到以下几点……”然后你会想：“天啊，我不敢相信你连这个都看到了。”","audio":null},{"id":147,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"We're thinking about an AI coach that can watch through the camera, analyze your form, and give tips. What would you actually want it to do for you?","literal_zh":"我们在考虑 AI 教练功能，通过摄像头观察动作、分析姿势并给出建议。你实际希望它为你做什么？","audio":null},{"id":148,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"I'm a self-coacher, so I think AI… I'm embracing AI. It's something I think is going to be part of our lives forever — right up until it decides we're no longer important, and then Cyberdyne Systems takes over. Until Miles Dyson starts Cyberdyne Corporation, I'm not going to worry.","literal_zh":"我是那种会自己指导自己的人，所以我觉得 AI……我是接受 AI 的。我认为它会永远成为我们生活的一部分——直到它决定我们不再重要，然后 Cyberdyne Systems 接管一切。在 Miles Dyson 创立 Cyberdyne Corporation 之前，我不会担心。","audio":null},{"id":149,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"But one of the things I think is interesting — especially with people my age — is it's very interesting what technology we embrace versus what technology we reject. The biggest thing I would say is, if you're going to use AI coaching, try to introduce it slowly into the program — slowly into the training factors. Because there are guys my age who don't like AI. They're afraid of it. So having dual options might be something that you need to look into, and then maybe testing it.","literal_zh":"但我觉得有意思的一件事，尤其是对我这个年龄的人来说，就是我们会接受什么技术、又会拒绝什么技术，这很有意思。我最想说的是，如果你们要使用 AI 教练，尽量慢慢把它引入课程里，慢慢引入训练要素里。因为有些我这个年龄的男人不喜欢 AI，他们害怕它。所以提供双选项可能是你们需要考虑的事情，然后也许测试一下。","audio":null},{"id":150,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"The twenty-year-olds and thirty-year-olds are going to love it — they're going to be all about AI. When you get into the forty- and fifty-year-olds, and even the sixty-year-olds — because some of us are still out there doing this stuff — it's going to be interesting as to what technology they've embraced and what technology they will embrace.","literal_zh":"二十多岁和三十多岁的人会喜欢它，他们会非常拥抱 AI。当你进入四十多岁、五十多岁，甚至六十多岁的人群时——因为我们当中有些人还在做这些事情——他们已经接受了什么技术、还会接受什么技术，就会很有意思。","audio":null},{"id":151,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"Exactly. The goal is to make the feedback specific and useful, not just generic encouragement.","literal_zh":"没错。目标是让反馈具体、有用，而不是泛泛地鼓励。","audio":null},{"id":152,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"I also think that would be something that you want to work on, too — creating a Facebook community, or a TikTok community, a social network community where people can post their workouts. Especially if the machine has a camera on it — now we can just say, \"Do you want to upload your video? Do you want to share this workout with the community?\" \"Hey, I just did level 15 on intermediate boxing level — look at my video!\" People will just go gaga over that, because it beats having to set up a camera at the end of the gym and videotape yourself boxing. You've got it already there.","literal_zh":"我也觉得这会是你们应该做的一件事：创建一个 Facebook 社群，或者 TikTok 社群，一个社交网络社群，让人们可以发布自己的训练。尤其是如果机器上有摄像头，那我们就可以直接说：“你想上传你的视频吗？你想把这次训练分享给社群吗？”“嘿，我刚完成中级拳击第 15 级，看看我的视频！”人们会为此兴奋起来，因为这比在健身房尽头架一台相机录自己打拳方便多了。你们已经把它放在那里了。","audio":null},{"id":153,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 21","english":"That makes sense. Between an AI coach and a real human coach giving feedback, which would feel more useful to you?","literal_zh":"这很有道理。在 AI 教练和真人教练反馈之间，哪一种对你来说更有用？","audio":null},{"id":154,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"Let me ask about another version we're considering. It would be shaped more like a human upper body, without legs, and it might cost around $10,000. What would you think of that?","literal_zh":"我想问一下我们正在考虑的另一个版本。它更像人的上半身，没有腿，价格可能在 1 万美元左右。你怎么看？","audio":null},{"id":155,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"I would say the system that you already have — because it looks like it might be a little bit more user-friendly. I can envision everything else. But the human form might be a little creepy. I might not want a robot in my house.","literal_zh":"我会说，你们现在已有的这个系统更好，因为它看起来可能更容易被用户接受。我能想象其他所有东西。但人体形态可能有点吓人。我可能不想在家里放一个机器人。","audio":null},{"id":156,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"The idea is that you could physically train against a robot. Do you think that would be exciting for users?","literal_zh":"核心想法是用户可以和一个机器人进行实体对练。你觉得这会让用户兴奋吗？","audio":null},{"id":157,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"I wouldn't say no to it. I think it's something I'd have to see, I guess, to kind of interact with. I don't see a problem — I just think it would be a little strange to walk into your garage and see the shape of a person in the middle of the night.","literal_zh":"我不会直接否定它。我觉得这可能是我得亲眼看到、实际互动一下才知道的东西。我不觉得它有问题，只是我觉得半夜走进车库，看到一个人形东西站在那里，会有点奇怪。","audio":null},{"id":158,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"Between the JabX you just saw and the human-shaped version, which one would you be more likely to buy?","literal_zh":"在你刚看到的 JabX 和人形上半身版本之间，你更可能买哪一个？","audio":null},{"id":159,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"I prefer the one you've already got — the JabX that you've shown me. I think that makes a lot of sense. The human form might be a little too much. It's just my instinct. I'm just giving you my feedback, but again, I'm just one person.","literal_zh":"我更喜欢你们已经有的那个，也就是你们刚给我看的 JabX。我觉得那个很合理。人体形态可能有点过头了。这只是我的直觉。我只是给你们我的反馈，但还是那句话，我只是一个人。","audio":null},{"id":160,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"That makes sense. A human-shaped machine in a garage at night could feel a little strange.","literal_zh":"这很合理。晚上在车库里看到一个人形机器，确实可能会让人觉得有点奇怪。","audio":null},{"id":161,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"One angle we're thinking about is social sharing. Would it matter to you if you could post your workout results or clips online?","literal_zh":"我们正在考虑的一个方向是社交分享。如果你可以在线发布训练结果或片段，这对你重要吗？","audio":null},{"id":162,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"(The JabX team shows a photo of the human-form version)","literal_zh":"(JabX 团队展示人形版本的照片)","audio":null},{"id":163,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"Well, that's not as bad as I thought. I mean, I'd give it a shot. But I would say the initial one looks great for the startup. Make the human form Round 2 — you know what I'm saying? When the sales are starting to drop, then you start working on that one, and initiate that as the 2.0 of the original. Because people will already be interested in it, and then it won't be… if you understand what I'm saying.","literal_zh":"嗯，这比我想象的没那么糟。我的意思是，我愿意试一试。但我会说，初始版本对创业公司来说看起来很棒。把人形版本做成第二轮产品——你明白我的意思吧？等销量开始下降时，你们再开始做那个，把它作为原始版本的 2.0 推出。因为那时人们已经对它感兴趣了，然后它就不会那么……如果你们理解我的意思。","audio":null},{"id":164,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 22","english":"The interesting part is that you could physically train against a robot. Do you think that idea would excite people?","literal_zh":"有意思的地方是用户可以和机器人进行实体对练。你觉得这个想法会让人感兴趣吗？","audio":null},{"id":165,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 23","english":"Since you've been training for so long, how do you usually plan your workouts? Do you decide in advance or choose on the day?","literal_zh":"你训练这么多年，通常是怎么安排训练的？你会提前计划，还是当天决定？","audio":null},{"id":166,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 23","english":"I'm a morning trainer. I get up at 5:30 or 4:30 in the morning, depending on what I'm doing that day. I do road work in the morning — I go for a run, then I'll go hit the pool, and then I'll come back here. Between 7 and 10 a.m. is when I do my workouts. Because in Florida it gets really hot by midday — especially in the summer, we're talking 98, 99 degrees and 98, 99% humidity. You've got to be a tough son of a gun to work out outside in that weather, or in the garage. So I try to get my stuff done before 10 a.m. That way I have the rest of the day to do all the things I need to do.","literal_zh":"我是早上训练的人。我早上 5:30 或 4:30 起床，取决于当天要做什么。我早上做路跑训练，先去跑步，然后去游泳池，然后再回到这里。我通常在上午 7 点到 10 点之间训练。因为佛罗里达中午会非常热，尤其是夏天，我们说的是 98、99 华氏度，湿度 98%、99%。在那种天气里，或者在车库里室外训练，你得非常硬。所以我尽量在上午 10 点前把训练完成。这样我一天剩下的时间就能做其他需要做的事。","audio":null},{"id":167,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 23","english":"So that's generally when I do my workouts — in the mornings. And then I schedule those workouts basically Monday, Wednesday, Friday, or Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday, depending on my week. If I get off to a slow Monday — but I'm also 90% retired. I do a couple of things here and there. My schedule probably won't be indicative of what you would expect from regular folks. Most folks are going to come home from work, go into the gym room in the house, and do the workouts in the evening — or do them in the mornings before they go to work. Things like that. But like I said, I don't really have a schedule, so it's kind of cool.","literal_zh":"所以我一般就是早上训练。然后我基本上把这些训练安排在周一、周三、周五，或者周二、周四、周六，取决于我那一周的情况。如果周一开始得比较慢也没关系——不过我现在也算 90% 退休了。我偶尔做点这个那个。我的时间安排可能不能代表普通人的情况。大多数人会下班回家，进家里的健身房房间，晚上训练，或者早上上班前训练。类似这样。但就像我说的，我其实没有真正的固定日程，所以这还挺好。","audio":null},{"id":168,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 24","english":"On a specific boxing day, how do you decide what to train? For example, how would you choose between hooks, footwork, or combinations?","literal_zh":"在专门练拳的日子里，你怎么决定具体练什么？比如勾拳、步法或组合拳之间怎么选择？","audio":null},{"id":169,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 24","english":"One of the things I like about FightCamp for that purpose is they have a progression. They have the novice progression, and then the intermediate progression, and then the advanced progression. Every day you do a different workout. There's a track. And then once you've decided what you want to work on, they also have extra workouts — \"I want to do a speed workout today, I want to do a focus workout today, I want to do a hard punch workout today.\" So you can pick and choose what workouts you want to do. But they have a path that you can follow, so you don't have to decide. You just go, \"Hey, stage two of this block of training.\"","literal_zh":"为了这个目的，我喜欢 FightCamp 的一点是它有进阶体系。它有新手进阶，然后是中级进阶，再到高级进阶。每天你做不同训练。有一条路径。然后当你决定自己想练什么之后，他们也有额外训练，比如“我今天想做速度训练，我今天想做专注训练，我今天想做重拳训练。”所以你可以选择自己想做的训练。但他们也有一条你可以遵循的路径，这样你就不用自己决定。你只需要说：“好，这个训练模块的第二阶段。”","audio":null},{"id":170,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 24","english":"So they set it up in a beginner block — I think they call it the \"Prospect Path,\" like you're a boxing prospect. They have a six-week program where you're just doing those workouts every day — 15, 20-minute workouts — and they vary in length and duration and what you're doing. It does the changing of things for you. And then if I wanted to do a hard punching workout after that, I can do that.","literal_zh":"所以他们会设置一个初学者模块，我记得他们叫它“Prospect Path”，就像你是一个拳击新秀。他们有一个六周项目，你每天做那些训练，15 分钟、20 分钟的训练，长度、时长和内容都会变化。它替你完成变化。然后如果我在那之后想做一个重拳训练，也可以做。","audio":null},{"id":171,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 24","english":"With the Nexersys machine, it's very similar. They have a progression or a series of workouts that I can do for the next six months. Just going, \"Okay, number two. Okay, number three. Okay, number four.\" It also gives you the ability to measure your success, because you're moving through these workouts, and if you're achieving your goals, they're getting progressively more complicated and progressively harder. They're adding more combinations, and they're teaching the skills in a relatable format.","literal_zh":"Nexersys 机器也非常类似。他们有一个进阶体系，或者一系列训练，我可以接下来六个月都照着做。就是“好，第二个。好，第三个。好，第四个。”它也让你能够衡量自己的成功，因为你在推进这些训练，如果你达成目标，它们就会逐渐变得更复杂、更困难。它们会加入更多组合拳，并用容易理解的形式教技能。","audio":null},{"id":172,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 24","english":"So you start out just working on 1-2, 1-2. Then you start throwing hooks, then you start throwing overhand rights, then you're throwing uppercuts, and they involve all these things. It's like algebra, where everything is based on what you've learned before. They reiterate the stuff you've already learned, and then they introduce a new skill. And they just keep introducing new skills and new skills.","literal_zh":"所以你一开始只是练 1-2、1-2。然后开始打勾拳，再开始打后手摆拳，然后打上勾拳，它们把所有这些东西都加入进来。这就像代数，一切都建立在你之前学过的东西之上。它们会重复你已经学过的内容，然后引入一个新技能。然后不断引入新技能、新技能。","audio":null},{"id":173,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 24","english":"I like that structure. I don't have to think about what I'm going to be doing. I don't have to write, \"I'm going to do 500 of this and 200 of that.\" I just move from the FightCamp workout to the speed bag, to the double-end bag, and then back to FightCamp. And then I go inside and I work on the Nexersys machine — I do three-minute rounds on that, and I just push play and say, \"Alright, man, tell me what I'm doing.\"","literal_zh":"我喜欢这种结构。我不需要思考自己要做什么。我不需要写下“我要做 500 个这个、200 个那个”。我只是从 FightCamp 训练切到速度球，再到双端球，然后回到 FightCamp。然后我进屋用 Nexersys 机器训练，在上面做三分钟回合。我只要按下播放，然后说：“好，兄弟，告诉我该做什么。”","audio":null},{"id":174,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 25","english":"FightCamp is mostly boxing combinations, right? Do you also mix in strength training, or do you treat that separately?","literal_zh":"FightCamp 主要是拳击组合训练，对吗？你会把力量训练混进去，还是单独安排？","audio":null},{"id":175,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 25","english":"I do calisthenics and bodyweight work. So I do four sets of 25 push-ups, four sets of 25 sit-ups — that kind of training. I do that in between the boxing workouts.","literal_zh":"我会做健身操和自重训练。所以我做四组每组 25 个俯卧撑，四组每组 25 个仰卧起坐，这类训练。我会把这些放在拳击训练之间。","audio":null},{"id":176,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 25","english":"What I would say is, most people would probably do their workout and then they would go do the boxing thing, or vice versa. For me, I do it after each round. So I'm adding boxing to every round of training that I do. And then I go out and try to skip rope and not trip over myself.","literal_zh":"我会说，大多数人可能会先完成自己的训练，然后去做拳击，或者反过来。对我来说，我会在每个回合后做。所以我把拳击加入到我每一轮训练里。然后我出去试着跳绳，并尽量不要绊倒自己。","audio":null},{"id":177,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 26","english":"On a dedicated boxing day, how do you decide what to train? For example, how would you choose between hooks, footwork, or combinations?","literal_zh":"在专门练拳的日子里，你怎么决定具体练什么？比如勾拳、步法或组合拳之间怎么选择？","audio":null},{"id":178,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 26","english":"Body combat is really important. A progressive training schedule, I think, is really important. I think the games would follow slightly behind that, because that's going to create a fun aspect — basically a kind of freeform. And then strength and punching power would fall behind those.","literal_zh":"身体格斗非常重要。渐进式训练计划，我觉得也非常重要。我觉得游戏会稍微排在后面，因为它会创造有趣的元素，基本上是一种自由形式。然后力量和出拳力量会排在它们后面。","audio":null},{"id":179,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 26","english":"Having a progressive workout schedule that you can follow — and then having those games that you can add. So you do a three or four-minute round of the progressive thing, and then you have this game that you play, and then you do another workout — or you do that as a reward for going through those training elements. You can then get to play the game.","literal_zh":"有一个你可以遵循的渐进式训练计划，然后有可以加入的游戏。比如你做一个三四分钟的渐进式训练回合，然后玩一个游戏，再做另一个训练——或者把游戏作为完成那些训练要素后的奖励。之后你就可以玩游戏。","audio":null},{"id":180,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 26","english":"What would really be cool is if you could incorporate the workout that you've done into that game, where the AI computer is teaching you, reinforcing the training that you did. \"I'm going to learn how to throw a hook. I'm going to learn how to throw a two-punch combo.\" And they start working those things into the game. That'd be kind of cool. I'm just speculating. But yeah, I would say the game would be fun as a reward for the progressive training. And then all the other elements, priority-wise, would fall behind that.","literal_zh":"真正酷的是，如果你们能把你已经完成的训练融入游戏，让 AI 电脑在游戏中继续教你、强化你刚做过的训练。“我要学习如何打勾拳。我要学习如何打两拳组合。”然后它们开始把这些东西融入游戏。那会挺酷的。我只是随便设想。但对，我会说游戏作为渐进式训练后的奖励会很有趣。然后其他所有元素在优先级上会排在那之后。","audio":null},{"id":181,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 27","english":"What about movement correction, where the machine watches your form and helps fix it? Would that be important, or just a nice extra feature?","literal_zh":"动作纠正呢？也就是机器观察你的姿势并帮助修正。这个重要吗，还是只是一个锦上添花的功能？","audio":null},{"id":182,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 27","english":"Yes. I would actually think that would probably be very important. Because one of the things about boxing — and this is something that you always have to pay attention to — is improper punching can lead to very serious injuries. You can break your hand. Now you don't have the use of your hand. So learning proper punching techniques, and having that computer be able to see, analyze, and correct — that's going to be a big factor. It's going to be a safety factor.","literal_zh":"重要。我实际上觉得那可能非常重要。因为拳击有一件事——也是你必须一直注意的事——就是不正确的出拳可能导致非常严重的伤害。你可能会打断自己的手。那你就不能使用那只手了。所以学习正确的出拳技术，并让电脑能够观察、分析和纠正，这会是一个重要因素。它会是一个安全因素。","audio":null},{"id":183,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 27","english":"It will make sure that the person isn't doing more than they should, that they're not trying to overwork themselves. But more importantly, if it's analyzing punching techniques, that's going to be beneficial because it will prevent someone from hurting themselves.","literal_zh":"它会确保用户没有做超过自己该做的量，没有试图过度训练。但更重要的是，如果它在分析出拳技术，那会很有益，因为它能防止用户伤到自己。","audio":null},{"id":184,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 27","english":"The biggest impediment to people achieving their fitness goals is injuries. You get injured, you're off for two weeks — you lose 70% of your physical gains in that two-week period. A hand injury where you can't punch for a week or two — you're going to lose all that momentum you've developed over that time.","literal_zh":"人们实现健身目标的最大障碍是受伤。你一受伤，就要停两周，在这两周里你会失去 70% 的身体进步。手部受伤导致你一两周不能出拳，你会失去那段时间里积累起来的所有势头。","audio":null},{"id":185,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 27","english":"Correcting behavior, being able to move and get out of the way of things — that's great stuff. But really, just teaching people how to punch effectively, and showing how to wrap your hands, and making sure your fist is closed — all those fundamental things.","literal_zh":"纠正行为，能够移动并躲开东西，这些都很棒。但真正重要的是教人们如何有效出拳，展示如何缠手，确保拳头握紧，所有这些基础东西。","audio":null},{"id":186,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 28","english":"What if JabX had electronic resistance built in, so after boxing you could also do curls, rows, and full strength training on the same machine? Would that make it more compelling?","literal_zh":"如果 JabX 内置电子阻力，让用户在拳击之后还可以在同一台机器上做弯举、划船和完整力量训练，这会更有吸引力吗？","audio":null},{"id":187,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 28","english":"Well, that would make it an all-in-one, and that's really going to help the home gym sales. Because then I can say, \"Hey, I don't need this other equipment.\" I can do resistance training — especially if it weighs enough, you could do suspension training using the resistance features. I think that's a great idea. I think that should definitely be incorporated. And that could be part of the workout. So you do your boxing workout, and it says, \"Okay, let's roll into our strength workout for today.\" Bicep curls, you can do deltoid raises — because you can do all that with straps and resistance.","literal_zh":"嗯，那会让它变成一体化设备，而这对家庭健身房销售会非常有帮助。因为那样我就可以说：“嘿，我不需要这些其他设备了。”我可以做阻力训练，尤其是如果它本身够重，你还可以利用阻力功能做悬挂训练。我觉得这是个很棒的想法。我觉得这绝对应该被加入。而且它可以成为训练的一部分。所以你完成拳击训练后，它说：“好，我们进入今天的力量训练。”二头弯举，你可以做三角肌侧平举，因为你可以用带子和阻力完成所有这些动作。","audio":null},{"id":188,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 29","english":"Let's talk about price. If electronic resistance added around $1,000, while regular resistance bands added around $100, which option would you prefer?","literal_zh":"我们聊一下价格。如果电子阻力会增加大约 1000 美元，而普通阻力带大约增加 100 美元，你会更倾向哪一种？","audio":null},{"id":189,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 29","english":"Well, I'm thinking of it as — if I'm going to invest in this particular piece of equipment, I'm someone who's going to be willing to spend the money. So I wouldn't want resistance bands. I would want that electronic resistance, tracking all I'm doing — so it can add more weight electronically, do all those things.","literal_zh":"嗯，我是这样想的：如果我要投资这件特定设备，我就是愿意花钱的人。所以我不会想要阻力带。我会想要电子阻力，追踪我做的一切，这样它可以通过电子方式增加重量，做所有这些事情。","audio":null},{"id":190,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 29","english":"I would say the extra $1,000 is not going to be the reason somebody doesn't buy it. Because they're already committed to investing a significant amount of money into this thing. As long as they're getting the results that they expect and it's meeting their expectations, they're not going to be afraid to spend the money.","literal_zh":"我会说，额外 1000 美元不会成为某人不买它的原因。因为他们已经决定要在这个东西上投入一大笔钱。只要他们能得到预期结果，并且它符合他们的期待，他们不会害怕花这笔钱。","audio":null},{"id":191,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 29","english":"Because you're looking at people who have disposable income, people who are pretty well established, and they're willing to invest in a piece of gym equipment that's going to work. These are not people who are trying to buy the little boxing dummy on TikTok or Temu and just hit the wall real soft, because if you hit it too hard you'll break it. These are people who are willing to invest serious money in your product.","literal_zh":"因为你们面对的是有可支配收入的人，是比较稳定的人，而且他们愿意投资一件真正有效的健身设备。这些人不是那种想在 TikTok 或 Temu 上买个小拳击靶、轻轻打墙的人，因为你打重一点就会把它打坏。这些人愿意在你们的产品上投入真正的钱。","audio":null},{"id":192,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 30","english":"Do you think people in your circle would be interested in JabX? Roughly how many of your friends might actually buy one?","literal_zh":"你觉得你身边的人会对 JabX 感兴趣吗？大概有多少朋友可能真的会买？","audio":null},{"id":193,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 30","english":"I have one friend who's really getting back into boxing — he would go ape over it. Excuse my language. He's a bigger guy. We were cops together, and he kind of put on some weight when he left the force. So he's trying to get back into it. I actually put a heavy bag in his office, and he's now starting to train again. He comes over and uses the Fight Bot, and I've got him on FightCamp, so we're working him through all that kind of stuff. He would think it was the cat's pajamas, for sure.","literal_zh":"我有一个朋友现在真的在重新开始练拳击，他会为这个疯狂。不好意思用词有点夸张。他是个块头比较大的人。我们以前一起当警察，他离开警队后有点发胖。所以他现在想重新练起来。我实际上在他的办公室里装了一个重沙袋，他现在又开始训练了。他会来我这里用 Fight Bot，我也让他用 FightCamp，所以我们正在带他做这些东西。他绝对会觉得这东西棒极了。","audio":null},{"id":194,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 31","english":"Is he completely new to boxing, or does he already know his way around a boxing gym?","literal_zh":"他是完全的拳击新手，还是已经比较了解拳馆训练？","audio":null},{"id":195,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 31","english":"I think he was a guy who got boxing training in the police academy, and probably boxed as a kid here and there — but never formal boxing training. He knows enough about the sport to want to pursue it as a form of fitness.","literal_zh":"我觉得他是在警校接受过拳击训练的人，可能小时候也零零散散打过一点，但从来没有接受过正式拳击训练。他对这项运动了解得足够多，所以会想把它作为一种健身方式继续做。","audio":null},{"id":196,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 31","english":"Again, I think one of the things you're looking at is — you're not looking at potentially training boxers. You're looking at people who want to use boxing as a way to get fit. I think that's kind of your niche market, because people trying to be boxers are going to have coaches, they're going to have trainers. They're going to be in places like the Hit Pit, working eight to ten hours a day — interacting with other people, getting coaching and feedback.","literal_zh":"再说一遍，我觉得你们要看的一个方向是：你们并不是在试图训练潜在拳手。你们面对的是想用拳击来健身的人。我觉得这就是你们的细分市场，因为那些想成为拳手的人会有教练，会有训练师。他们会在 Hit Pit 这样的地方，一天练八到十个小时，和其他人互动，接受教练和反馈。","audio":null},{"id":197,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 31","english":"The people that you're kind of steering towards are people like myself. I don't want to go… I'm not training for a fight. I want to stay in shape, and I want to do that via boxing, because I understand how significant boxing is to fitness — and how all-encompassing it is.","literal_zh":"你们真正面向的人更像我这样。我不想去……我不是为了打一场比赛而训练。我想保持身材，而且想通过拳击来保持身材，因为我理解拳击对健身有多重要，也理解它有多全面。","audio":null},{"id":198,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"I just realized we never got your first name. What should we call you? Sorry about that.","literal_zh":"我刚意识到我们还没问你的名字。我们应该怎么称呼你？不好意思。","audio":null},{"id":199,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"Mark. My friends call me Mac, because when I was a kid, one of my teachers thought the \"r\" was a \"c\" — so she called me Mac, and it stuck. So everybody calls me Mac.","literal_zh":"Mark。我的朋友们叫我 Mac，因为我小时候，有个老师把我名字里的 “r” 看成了 “c”，所以她叫我 Mac，然后这个名字就留下来了。所以大家都叫我 Mac。","audio":null},{"id":200,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"Mac, great. Do you have any questions or suggestions for us? We're very open to feedback.","literal_zh":"Mac，很好。你有什么问题或建议想给我们吗？我们非常愿意听反馈。","audio":null},{"id":201,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"I think you guys have asked enough questions that I don't have any real suggestions, other than — get it going, so we can start seeing this thing. I can't wait till you get done with it.","literal_zh":"我觉得你们已经问了足够多的问题，所以我没有什么真正的建议，除了——赶快把它做起来，这样我们就能开始看到这个东西。我等不及你们把它完成了。","audio":null},{"id":202,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"We're planning to launch in August.","literal_zh":"我们计划在八月发布。","audio":null},{"id":203,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"Oh, really? Oh, cool.","literal_zh":"哦，真的吗？哦，酷。","audio":null},{"id":204,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"That's the plan, at least. We'll keep you posted, ideally about once a month.","literal_zh":"至少目前计划是这样。我们会持续同步进展，理想情况下大约每月一次。","audio":null},{"id":205,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"If I may make a suggestion — and I'm not sure who you would need to contact — but military bases all have gyms. Navy bases, Air Force bases. I'm just down the street from Patrick Air Force Base, and they have a gym.","literal_zh":"如果我可以提一个建议——我不确定你们需要联系谁——但军事基地都有健身房。海军基地、空军基地都有。我就在 Patrick 空军基地附近，他们有一个健身房。","audio":null},{"id":206,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"If you offered a military discount to put it in those gyms, I think you'd get a lot of veterans interested in this, because we've all had combat training at some level.","literal_zh":"如果你们提供军人折扣，把它放进那些健身房，我觉得会有很多退伍军人对此感兴趣，因为我们都在某种程度上接受过格斗训练。","audio":null},{"id":207,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"MWR — Morale, Welfare and Recreation — is responsible for the base gyms. If you go to the military — Navy, Air Force, Marines, Army — they're going to have an MWR. Usually MWR is responsible for the base gyms. Talk to them about this product and see if you can launch it into there, offering a potential military discount or a law enforcement discount — because, again, sheriff's offices, police departments, fire departments — they all have gyms. They would like something like this, because it can reinforce a lot of the training that we do. The Brevard County Sheriff's Office — every precinct has a gym.","literal_zh":"MWR，也就是 Morale, Welfare and Recreation，士气、福利与娱乐部门，负责基地健身房。如果你去军方系统，无论是海军、空军、海军陆战队还是陆军，他们都会有 MWR。通常 MWR 负责基地健身房。你们可以跟他们聊这个产品，看看能不能把它放进去，提供潜在的军人折扣或执法人员折扣。因为同样，警长办公室、警察局、消防部门都有健身房。他们会喜欢这种东西，因为它可以强化我们很多训练。布里瓦德县警长办公室每个分局都有健身房。","audio":null},{"id":208,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"Offering a special rate to get it in — because if you get it into these places, these people will talk about it. These people are like, \"Man, this needs to be over here.\" So yeah, talking to Army, Navy, Air Force, Marines Morale, Welfare and Recreation departments — trying to get someone who is responsible for purchasing equipment for those gyms — is going to be a great spot for you to look at as far as selling it.","literal_zh":"可以提供一个特殊价格先让它进去，因为如果你们把它放进这些地方，这些人会讨论它。他们会说：“兄弟，这东西也得放到我们那边。”所以，是的，去和陆军、海军、空军、海军陆战队的 MWR 部门谈，找到负责为这些健身房采购设备的人，这会是你们销售时很值得看的方向。","audio":null},{"id":209,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"You think about it — there are probably a hundred bases in the U.S. alone that you could put one of these in. These are not half-ass gyms. The Air Force base gym — it's like treadmill heaven in there. It's ridiculous. I go there to swim in the pool, I don't use the gym, but they really do have top-shelf equipment. So whoever's purchasing that…","literal_zh":"你们想想，光美国可能就有上百个基地可以放一台。这些可不是随便凑合的健身房。空军基地健身房里面简直是跑步机天堂，夸张得很。我去那里是为了游泳池游泳，不用那里的健身房，但他们真的有顶级设备。所以负责采购那些设备的人……","audio":null},{"id":210,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"Also — looking online and finding the big fitness influencers, and sending them one as a demo to test out the product, would be a great idea, because that boosts your social media profile and gets your product out there. I'm not a big fan of all these guys who do the fitness thing, because some of them talk more than they do. But finding a fitness influencer who matches what you think — again, I would say Tony Jeffries. I'll get his information. He's a boxer, he owns a boxing gym, and he's a social media influencer. Letting him test one out for you might be a big help, because it would definitely promote your product.","literal_zh":"另外，在线上找大型健身影响者，给他们寄一台样机测试产品，也会是个很好的想法，因为这会提升你们的社交媒体曝光，让产品传播出去。我不是所有健身博主的粉丝，因为有些人说得比做得多。但找一个符合你们理念的健身影响者——我还是会说 Tony Jeffries。我会把他的信息找给你们。他是拳手，有自己的拳馆，也是社交媒体影响者。让他帮你们测试一台可能会很有帮助，因为这肯定会推广你们的产品。","audio":null},{"id":211,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"But definitely look at military, definitely look at law enforcement, firefighters — people like that. Getting it into their gyms. I'm not saying give it away — just talk to them about getting it in there, even as a test. \"Hey, if people don't like it, we'll take it back.\" But I guarantee people will be like, \"Oh my god, this is the coolest thing ever.\" Because it's interactive, and it does the things that a heavy bag doesn't. It interacts with you, and it's going to give feedback.","literal_zh":"但一定要看看军方，一定要看看执法部门、消防员这些人。把它放进他们的健身房。我不是说免费送，只是跟他们谈谈把它放进去，哪怕是测试。“嘿，如果大家不喜欢，我们就拿回来。”但我保证人们会说：“天啊，这是最酷的东西。”因为它是互动的，它能做重沙袋做不到的事。它会和你互动，也会给反馈。","audio":null},{"id":212,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 32","english":"We love feedback. Guys who train love — I mean, I have 15 logbooks of all the workouts I used to do when I was in the military, where I wrote it down: \"Did this many push-ups, did this many sit-ups, ran this far.\" I kept a logbook, because we want to track our progress, see how we're doing. So having all that digitally — it's going to save a lot of writing.","literal_zh":"我们喜欢反馈。训练的人都喜欢——我的意思是，我有 15 本训练日志，记录了我在军队时做过的所有训练。我会写下来：“做了多少个俯卧撑，做了多少个仰卧起坐，跑了多远。”我保留训练日志，因为我们想追踪自己的进步，看看自己表现如何。所以如果所有这些都能数字化，那会省下很多书写。","audio":null},{"id":213,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"Mac, this is extremely valuable. Thank you. Also, we'll be at CES in Las Vegas this January, from January 6th through 9th. We'd be happy to have you come by.","literal_zh":"Mac，这些信息非常有价值。谢谢。另外，我们今年一月会去拉斯维加斯参加 CES，时间是 1 月 6 日到 9 日。我们很欢迎你过来看看。","audio":null},{"id":214,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"Oh, I'll come out. Send me the dates, and I'll be there. I'm retired, I've got nothing to do — you tell me when, and I'll show up.","literal_zh":"哦，我会去的。把日期发给我，我就去。我退休了，没什么事做——你们告诉我时间，我就出现。","audio":null},{"id":215,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"We'll send you all the details. Can't wait to actually meet you in person.","literal_zh":"我们会把所有细节发给你。等不及真正线下见到你了。","audio":null},{"id":216,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"Absolutely. And if you need anything else, feel free to reach out. You have my WhatsApp — if you just send me a message saying, \"We'd like to talk to you some more,\" I'm always willing to talk, because — in case you haven't noticed — I'm a little bit chatty.","literal_zh":"当然。如果你们还需要其他任何东西，随时联系我。你们有我的 WhatsApp，只要给我发消息说“我们想再跟你聊聊”，我一直都愿意聊，因为——如果你们还没注意到的话——我有点话多。","audio":null},{"id":217,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"We appreciate that. One last thing: when you have time, could you send the Nexersys workout video? No rush.","literal_zh":"非常感谢。最后一件事：你方便的时候可以把 Nexersys 训练视频发给我们吗？不着急。","audio":null},{"id":218,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"Yep, the Nexersys machine. And then on Friday, I'll probably go down to Rock Box, and I'll take some photos, and I'll take some video of one of the classes. I'm happy to.","literal_zh":"没问题，Nexersys 机器。然后周五我大概会去 Rock Box，拍一些照片，也拍一个课程的视频。我很乐意。","audio":null},{"id":219,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"That'll be Friday. And I will probably have the Nexersys workout video too, because I've got to get the garage cleaned out. We were working on a motorcycle — I have two custom motorcycles — and we had one completely torn apart, so there wasn't a lot of working out this week. But we got it all back together, so I'm going to get everything cleaned out so I can get back in there and start working again.","literal_zh":"那会是周五。我可能也会拍好 Nexersys 训练视频，因为我得把车库清理出来。我们之前在修摩托车——我有两辆定制摩托——其中一辆被完全拆开了，所以这周没怎么训练。但我们已经把它重新装好了，所以我会把所有东西清理出来，这样我就能回到那里重新开始训练。","audio":null},{"id":220,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"Absolutely — and please keep me posted when you guys are getting ready to launch. I'll definitely come out to Vegas, and I look forward to meeting you guys in person.","literal_zh":"绝对没问题。你们准备发布时请一定持续告诉我。我肯定会去拉斯维加斯，也期待和你们线下见面。","audio":null},{"id":221,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"This has been incredibly helpful. You have no idea how useful this is for us.","literal_zh":"这对我们非常有帮助。你可能不知道这些信息对我们有多有用。","audio":null},{"id":222,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"It has been my pleasure, and I hope I helped.","literal_zh":"这是我的荣幸，也希望我确实帮上忙了。","audio":null},{"id":223,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"Thank you so much, and sorry we kept you for so many questions. We got a little carried away.","literal_zh":"非常感谢，也抱歉我们问了这么多问题。我们确实有点聊得太投入了。","audio":null},{"id":224,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"No worries. I'm happy to help, because I think what you guys are doing is great. You're producing a product, and you need as much information as you can get. If you can run across somebody like me who's been doing it most of his life — it might help a little bit. So I'm happy to help. Anything I can do, just let me know.","literal_zh":"没关系。我很乐意帮忙，因为我觉得你们正在做的事情很棒。你们在做一个产品，需要尽可能多的信息。如果你们碰到像我这样大半辈子都在做这类事的人，可能会有一点帮助。所以我很乐意帮忙。我能做的任何事，告诉我就行。","audio":null},{"id":225,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"Thank you again. Have a great day, Mac.","literal_zh":"再次感谢。祝你今天过得愉快，Mac。","audio":null},{"id":226,"speaker":"Mark","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"You too. Everyone — nice meeting you. Bye.","literal_zh":"你们也是。各位，很高兴认识你们。再见。","audio":null},{"id":227,"speaker":"Interviewer","section":"Mark Interview - Part 33","english":"Bye! Nice meeting you too!","literal_zh":"再见！我们也很高兴认识你！","audio":null}]};
